65 // returns a float in range of..
66 float rand_float(float low, float high)
67 {
68  return (rand() / (static_cast<float>(RAND_MAX) + 1.0)) * (high - low) + low;
69 }

77 // ChatHandler already implements some useful commands the master can call on bots
78 // These commands are protected inside the ChatHandler class so this class provides access to the commands
79 // we'd like to call on our bots
80 class PlayerbotChatHandler : protected ChatHandler
81 {
82  public:
83  explicit PlayerbotChatHandler(Player* pMasterPlayer) : ChatHandler(pMasterPlayer) {}
84  bool revive(Player& botPlayer) { return HandleReviveCommand((char*) botPlayer.GetName()); }
85  bool teleport(Player& botPlayer) { return HandleNamegoCommand((char*) botPlayer.GetName()); }
86  void sysmessage(const char* str) { SendSysMessage(str); }
87  bool dropQuest(char* str) { return HandleQuestRemoveCommand(str); }
88 };

90 PlayerbotAI::PlayerbotAI(PlayerbotMgr &mgr, Player* const bot, bool debugWhisper) :
91  m_mgr(mgr), m_bot(bot), m_classAI(0), m_ignoreAIUpdatesUntilTime(CurrentTime()),
92  m_combatOrder(ORDERS_NONE), m_ScenarioType(SCENARIO_PVE),
93  m_CurrentlyCastingSpellId(0), m_CraftSpellId(0), m_spellIdCommand(0),
94  m_targetGuidCommand(ObjectGuid()),
95  m_taxiMaster(ObjectGuid()),
96  m_ignoreNeutralizeEffect(false),
97  m_bDebugCommandChat(false),
98  m_debugWhisper(debugWhisper)
99 {
100  // set bot state
101  m_botState = BOTSTATE_LOADING;
102 
103  // reset some pointers
104  m_targetChanged = false;
105  m_targetType = TARGET_NORMAL;
106  m_targetCombat = nullptr;
107  m_targetAssist = nullptr;
108  m_targetProtect = nullptr;
109 
110  // set collection options
111  m_collectionFlags = 0;
112  m_collectDist = m_mgr.m_confCollectDistance;
113  if (m_mgr.m_confCollectCombat)
114  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_COMBAT);
115  if (m_mgr.m_confCollectQuest)
116  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_QUEST);
117  if (m_mgr.m_confCollectProfession)
118  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_PROFESSION);
119  if (m_mgr.m_confCollectLoot)
120  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_LOOT);
121  if (m_mgr.m_confCollectSkin && m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_SKINNING))
122  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_SKIN);
123  if (m_mgr.m_confCollectObjects)
124  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_NEAROBJECT);
125 
126  // set needed item list
127  SetQuestNeedItems();
128  SetQuestNeedCreatures();
129 
130  // start following master (will also teleport bot to master)
131  m_dropWhite = false;
132  m_AutoEquipToggle = false;
133  m_FollowAutoGo = FOLLOWAUTOGO_OFF; //turn on bot auto follow distance can be turned off by player
134  DistOverRide = 0; //set initial adjustable follow settings
135  IsUpOrDown = 0;
136  gTempDist = 0.5f;
137  gTempDist2 = 1.0f;
138  SetMovementOrder(MOVEMENT_FOLLOW, GetMaster());
139  BotDataRestore();
140  m_DelayAttackInit = CurrentTime();
141

158 bool PlayerbotAI::CanReachWithSpellAttack(Unit* target)
159 {
160  bool inrange = false;
161  float dist = m_bot->GetDistance(target, true, DIST_CALC_COMBAT_REACH_WITH_MELEE);
162 
163  for (SpellRanges::iterator itr = m_spellRangeMap.begin(); itr != m_spellRangeMap.end(); ++itr)
164  {
165  uint32 spellId = itr->first;
166 
167  // ignore positive spells
168  if (IsPositiveSpell(spellId))
169  continue;
170 
171  // ignore active auras
172  if (target->HasAura(spellId, EFFECT_INDEX_0))
173  continue;
174 
175  const SpellEntry* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
176  if (!spellInfo)
177  continue;
178 
179  // ignore non-ranged spells
180  if (!spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_USES_RANGED_SLOT))
181  continue;
182 
183  float maxrange = itr->second;
184 
185  // DEBUG_LOG("[%s] spell (%s) : dist (%f) < maxrange (%f)",m_bot->GetName(), spellInfo->SpellName[0], dist, maxrange);
186 
187  if (dist < maxrange)
188  {
189  inrange = true;
190  break;
191  }
192  }
193  return inrange;
194 }
195 
196 bool PlayerbotAI::In_Reach(Unit* Target, uint32 spellId)
197 {
198  if (!Target)
199  return false;
200 
201  float range = 0;
202  float dist = m_bot->GetDistance(Target, true, DIST_CALC_COMBAT_REACH_WITH_MELEE);
203  SpellRanges::iterator it;
204  it = m_spellRangeMap.find(spellId);
205  (it != m_spellRangeMap.end()) ? range = it->second : range = 0;
206 
207  // DEBUG_LOG("spell (%u) : range (%f)", spellId, range);
208 
209  if (dist > range)
210  return false;
211 
212  return true;
213 }

215 // finds spell ID for matching substring args
216 // in priority of full text match, spells not taking reagents, and highest rank
217 uint32 PlayerbotAI::getSpellId(const char* args, bool master) const
218 {
219  if (!*args)
220  return 0;
221 
222  std::string namepart = args;
223  std::wstring wnamepart;
224 
225  if (!Utf8toWStr(namepart, wnamepart))
226  return 0;
227 
228  // converting string that we try to find to lower case
229  wstrToLower(wnamepart);
230 
231  int loc = 0;
232  if (master)
233  loc = GetMaster()->GetSession()->GetSessionDbcLocale();
234  else
235  loc = m_bot->GetSession()->GetSessionDbcLocale();
236 
237  uint32 foundSpellId = 0;
238  bool foundExactMatch = false;
239  bool foundMatchUsesNoReagents = false;
240 
241  for (PlayerSpellMap::iterator itr = m_bot->GetSpellMap().begin(); itr != m_bot->GetSpellMap().end(); ++itr)
242  {
243  uint32 spellId = itr->first;
244 
245  if (itr->second.state == PLAYERSPELL_REMOVED || itr->second.disabled || IsPassiveSpell(spellId))
246  continue;
247 
248  const SpellEntry* pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
249  if (!pSpellInfo)
250  continue;
251 
252  const std::string name = pSpellInfo->SpellName[loc];
253  if (name.empty() || !Utf8FitTo(name, wnamepart))
254  continue;
255 
256  bool isExactMatch = (name.length() == wnamepart.length()) ? true : false;
257  bool usesNoReagents = (pSpellInfo->Reagent[0] <= 0) ? true : false;
258 
259  // if we already found a spell
260  bool useThisSpell = true;
261  if (foundSpellId > 0)
262  {
263  if (isExactMatch && !foundExactMatch) {}
264  else if (usesNoReagents && !foundMatchUsesNoReagents) {}
265  else if (spellId > foundSpellId) {}
266  else
267  useThisSpell = false;
268  }
269  if (useThisSpell)
270  {
271  foundSpellId = spellId;
272  foundExactMatch = isExactMatch;
273  foundMatchUsesNoReagents = usesNoReagents;
274  }
275  }
276 
277  return foundSpellId;
278 }

280 uint32 PlayerbotAI::getPetSpellId(const char* args) const
281 {
282  if (!*args)
283  return 0;
284 
285  Pet* pet = m_bot->GetPet();
286  if (!pet)
287  return 0;
288 
289  std::string namepart = args;
290  std::wstring wnamepart;
291 
292  if (!Utf8toWStr(namepart, wnamepart))
293  return 0;
294 
295  // converting string that we try to find to lower case
296  wstrToLower(wnamepart);
297 
298  int loc = GetMaster()->GetSession()->GetSessionDbcLocale();
299 
300  uint32 foundSpellId = 0;
301  bool foundExactMatch = false;
302  bool foundMatchUsesNoReagents = false;
303 
304  for (PetSpellMap::iterator itr = pet->m_spells.begin(); itr != pet->m_spells.end(); ++itr)
305  {
306  uint32 spellId = itr->first;
307 
308  if (itr->second.state == PETSPELL_REMOVED || IsPassiveSpell(spellId))
309  continue;
310 
311  const SpellEntry* pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
312  if (!pSpellInfo)
313  continue;
314 
315  const std::string name = pSpellInfo->SpellName[loc];
316  if (name.empty() || !Utf8FitTo(name, wnamepart))
317  continue;
318 
319  bool isExactMatch = (name.length() == wnamepart.length()) ? true : false;
320  bool usesNoReagents = (pSpellInfo->Reagent[0] <= 0) ? true : false;
321 
322  // if we already found a spell
323  bool useThisSpell = true;
324  if (foundSpellId > 0)
325  {
326  if (isExactMatch && !foundExactMatch) {}
327  else if (usesNoReagents && !foundMatchUsesNoReagents) {}
328  else if (spellId > foundSpellId) {}
329  else
330  useThisSpell = false;
331  }
332  if (useThisSpell)
333  {
334  foundSpellId = spellId;
335  foundExactMatch = isExactMatch;
336  foundMatchUsesNoReagents = usesNoReagents;
337  }
338  }
339 
340  return foundSpellId;
341 }

343 uint32 PlayerbotAI::initSpell(uint32 spellId)
344 {
345  // Check if bot knows this spell
346  if (!m_bot->HasSpell(spellId))
347  return 0;
348 
349  uint32 next = 0;
350  SpellChainMapNext const& nextMap = sSpellMgr.GetSpellChainNext();
351  for (SpellChainMapNext::const_iterator itr = nextMap.lower_bound(spellId); itr != nextMap.upper_bound(spellId); ++itr)
352  {
353  SpellChainNode const* node = sSpellMgr.GetSpellChainNode(itr->second);
354  // If next spell is a requirement for this one then skip it
355  if (node->req == spellId)
356  continue;
357  if (node->prev == spellId)
358  {
359  next = initSpell(itr->second);
360  break;
361  }
362  }
363  if (next == 0)
364  {
365  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
366  if (!pSpellInfo)
367  return spellId;
368 
369  DEBUG_LOG("[PlayerbotAI]: initSpell - Playerbot spell init: %s is %u", pSpellInfo->SpellName[0], spellId);
370 
371  // Add spell to spellrange map
372  Spell* spell = new Spell(m_bot, pSpellInfo, false);
373  SpellRangeEntry const* srange = sSpellRangeStore.LookupEntry(pSpellInfo->rangeIndex);
374  float range = GetSpellMaxRange(srange, IsPositiveSpell(spellId));
375  if (Player* modOwner = m_bot->GetSpellModOwner())
376  modOwner->ApplySpellMod(pSpellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_RANGE, range);
377  m_spellRangeMap.insert(std::pair<uint32, float>(spellId, range));
378  delete spell;
379  }
380  return (next == 0) ? spellId : next;
381 }
382 
383 // Pet spells do not form chains like player spells.
384 // One of the options to initialize a spell is to use spell icon id
385 uint32 PlayerbotAI::initPetSpell(uint32 spellIconId)
386 {
387  Pet* pet = m_bot->GetPet();
388 
389  if (!pet)
390  return 0;
391 
392  for (PetSpellMap::iterator itr = pet->m_spells.begin(); itr != pet->m_spells.end(); ++itr)
393  {
394  const uint32 spellId = itr->first;
395 
396  if (itr->second.state == PETSPELL_REMOVED || IsPassiveSpell(spellId))
397  continue;
398 
399  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
400  if (!pSpellInfo)
401  continue;
402 
403  if (pSpellInfo->SpellIconID == spellIconId)
404  return spellId;
405  }
406 
407  // Nothing found
408  return 0;
409 }

411 /*
412 * Send list of the equipment in bot's inventory not currently equipped.
413 * This is called when the master is inspecting the bot.
414 */
415 void PlayerbotAI::SendNotEquipList(Player& /*player*/)
416 {
417  // find all unequipped items and put them in
418  // a vector of dynamically created lists where the vector index is from 0-18
419  // and the list contains Item* that can be equipped to that slot
420  // Note: each dynamically created list in the vector must be deleted at end
421  // so NO EARLY RETURNS!
422  // see enum EquipmentSlots in Player.h to see what equipment slot each index in vector
423  // is assigned to. (The first is EQUIPMENT_SLOT_HEAD=0, and last is EQUIPMENT_SLOT_TABARD=18)
424  std::list<Item*>* equip[19];
425  for (uint8 i = 0; i < 19; ++i)
426  equip[i] = nullptr;
427 
428  // list out items in main backpack
429  for (uint8 slot = INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START; slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; slot++)
430  {
431  Item* const pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slot);
432  if (!pItem)
433  continue;
434 
435  uint16 dest;
436  InventoryResult msg = m_bot->CanEquipItem(NULL_SLOT, dest, pItem, !pItem->IsBag());
437  if (msg != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
438  continue;
439 
440  // the dest looks like it includes the old loc in the 8 higher bits
441  // so casting it to a uint8 strips them
442  int8 equipSlot = uint8(dest);
443  if (!(equipSlot >= 0 && equipSlot < 19))
444  continue;
445 
446  // create a list if one doesn't already exist
447  if (equip[equipSlot] == nullptr)
448  equip[equipSlot] = new std::list<Item*>;
449 
450  std::list<Item*>* itemListForEqSlot = equip[equipSlot];
451  itemListForEqSlot->push_back(pItem);
452  }
453 
454  // list out items in other removable backpacks
455  for (uint8 bag = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; bag < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++bag)
456  {
457  const Bag* const pBag = (Bag*) m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, bag);
458  if (pBag)
459  for (uint8 slot = 0; slot < pBag->GetBagSize(); ++slot)
460  {
461  Item* const pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(bag, slot);
462  if (!pItem)
463  continue;
464 
465  uint16 dest;
466  InventoryResult msg = m_bot->CanEquipItem(NULL_SLOT, dest, pItem, !pItem->IsBag());
467  if (msg != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
468  continue;
469 
470  int8 equipSlot = uint8(dest);
471  if (!(equipSlot >= 0 && equipSlot < 19))
472  continue;
473 
474  // create a list if one doesn't already exist
475  if (equip[equipSlot] == nullptr)
476  equip[equipSlot] = new std::list<Item*>;
477 
478  std::list<Item*>* itemListForEqSlot = equip[equipSlot];
479  itemListForEqSlot->push_back(pItem);
480  }
481  }
482 
483  ChatHandler ch(GetMaster());
484  bool bAnyEquippable = false;
485 
486  const std::string descr[] = { "head", "neck", "shoulders", "body", "chest",
487  "waist", "legs", "feet", "wrists", "hands", "finger1", "finger2",
488  "trinket1", "trinket2", "back", "mainhand", "offhand", "ranged",
489  "tabard"
490  };
491 
492  // now send client all items that can be equipped by slot
493  for (uint8 equipSlot = 0; equipSlot < 19; ++equipSlot)
494  {
495  if (equip[equipSlot] == nullptr)
496  continue;
497 
498  if (!bAnyEquippable)
499  {
500  TellMaster("Here's all the items in my inventory that I can equip:");
501  bAnyEquippable = true;
502  }
503 
504  std::list<Item*>* itemListForEqSlot = equip[equipSlot];
505  std::ostringstream out;
506  out << descr[equipSlot] << ": ";
507  for (std::list<Item*>::iterator it = itemListForEqSlot->begin(); it != itemListForEqSlot->end(); ++it)
508  if ((*it))
509  MakeItemLink((*it), out, true);
510  ch.SendSysMessage(out.str().c_str());
511 
512  delete itemListForEqSlot; // delete list of Item*
513  }
514 
515  if (!bAnyEquippable)
516  TellMaster("There are no items in my inventory that I can equip.");
517 }
518 
519 void PlayerbotAI::FollowAutoReset()
520 {
521  if (m_FollowAutoGo != FOLLOWAUTOGO_OFF)
522  {
523  m_FollowAutoGo = FOLLOWAUTOGO_RESET;
524  SetMovementOrder(MOVEMENT_FOLLOW, GetMaster());
525  WorldObject* distTarget = m_followTarget;
526  for (uint8 i = 0; i < 1; ++i)
527  {
528  if (m_bot->GetDistance(distTarget) < 3.0f)
529  i = 1;
530  else
531  i = 0;
532  }
533  }
534 }
535 
536 void PlayerbotAI::AutoUpgradeEquipment() // test for autoequip
537 {
538  if (!m_AutoEquipToggle)
539  return;
540 
541  ChatHandler ch(GetMaster());
542  std::ostringstream out;
543  std::ostringstream msg;
544 
545  // Find equippable items in main backpack one at a time
546  for (uint8 slot = INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START; slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; slot++)
547  {
548  Item* const pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slot);
549 
550  if (!pItem)
551  continue;
552 
553  uint32 spellId = 0;
554 
555  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS; ++i)
556  {
557  if (pItem->GetProto()->Spells[i].SpellId > 0)
558  {
559  spellId = pItem->GetProto()->Spells[i].SpellId;
560  break;
561  }
562  }
563 
564  if (pItem->GetProto()->Flags & ITEM_FLAG_HAS_LOOT && spellId == 0)
565  {
566  // TODO: std::string oops = "Opening " + [ITEM] + " to see what's inside.";
567  std::string oops = "Oh... Look! Theres something inside!!!";
568  m_bot->Say(oops, LANG_UNIVERSAL);
569  UseItem(pItem);
570  continue;
571  }
572 
573  if (uint32 questid = pItem->GetProto()->StartQuest)
574  {
575  // TODO: if quest failed, auto-drop and auto-pickup
576  //if (m_bot->GetQuestStatus(questid) == QUEST_STATUS_FAILED)
577  if (m_bot->GetQuestStatus(questid) == QUEST_STATUS_COMPLETE
578  || m_bot->GetQuestStatus(questid) == QUEST_STATUS_UNAVAILABLE)
579  continue;
580  else
581  {
582  Quest const* qInfo = sObjectMgr.GetQuestTemplate(questid);
583  if (!m_bot->CanTakeQuest(qInfo, false))
584  {
585  // TODO: make clear which item should be thrown away
586  std::string oops = "Great, more junk... Can I get rid of this please?";
587  m_bot->Say(oops, LANG_UNIVERSAL);
588  continue;
589  }
590  }
591  UseItem(pItem);
592  }
593 
594  uint16 equipSlot;
595  InventoryResult msg = m_bot->CanEquipItem(NULL_SLOT, equipSlot, pItem, !pItem->IsBag());
596  if (msg != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
597  continue;
598 
599  // do we have anything equipped of this type?
600  Item* const pItem2 = m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, (uint8)equipSlot);
601  if (!pItem2) // no item to compare to see if has stats useful for this bots class/style so check for stats and equip if possible
602  {
603  ItemPrototype const* pProto2 = pItem->GetProto();
604  if (pProto2->StatsCount > 0)
605  {
606  if (!ItemStatComparison(pProto2, pProto2))
607  continue;
608  }
609  EquipItem(pItem); // no item equipped so equip new one and go to next item.
610  continue;
611  }
612 
613  // we have an equippable item, so lets send it to the comparison function to see if it's better than we have on
614  AutoEquipComparison(pItem, pItem2); // pItem is new item, pItem2 is equipped item.
615  }
616 
617  // list out items in other removable backpacks
618  for (uint8 bag = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; bag < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++bag)
619  {
620  const Bag* const pBag = (Bag*) m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, bag);
621  if (pBag)
622  for (uint8 slot = 0; slot < pBag->GetBagSize(); ++slot)
623  {
624  Item* const pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(bag, slot);
625  if (!pItem)
626  continue;
627 
628  uint16 dest;
629  InventoryResult msg = m_bot->CanEquipItem(NULL_SLOT, dest, pItem, !pItem->IsBag());
630  if (msg != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
631  continue;
632 
633  uint8 equipSlot = uint8(dest);
634  Item* const pItem2 = m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, equipSlot); // do we have anything equipped of this type?
635  if (!pItem2)
636  {
637  ItemPrototype const* pProto2 = pItem->GetProto();
638  if (pProto2->StatsCount > 0)
639  {
640  if (!ItemStatComparison(pProto2, pProto2))
641  continue;
642  }
643 
644  EquipItem(pItem); //no item equipped so equip new one if useable stats and go to next item.
645  continue;
646  }
647 
648  // we have an equippable item but something else is equipped so lets send it to the comparison function to see if it's better than we have on
649  AutoEquipComparison(pItem, pItem2); //pItem is new item, pItem2 is equipped item.
650  }
651  }
652  InspectUpdate();
653 }
654 
655 void PlayerbotAI::AutoEquipComparison(Item* pItem, Item* pItem2)
656 {
657  const static uint32 item_armor_skills[MAX_ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR] =
658  {
659  0, SKILL_CLOTH, SKILL_LEATHER, SKILL_MAIL, SKILL_PLATE_MAIL, 0, SKILL_SHIELD, 0, 0, 0, 0
660  };
661  ItemPrototype const* pProto = pItem2->GetProto(); // equipped item if any
662  ItemPrototype const* pProto2 = pItem->GetProto(); // new item to compare
663  // DEBUG_LOG("Item Class (%s)",(pProto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON ? "Weapon" : "Not Weapon"));
664  switch (pProto->Class)
665  {
666  case ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON:
667  {
668  // DEBUG_LOG("Current Item DPS (%f) Equippable Item DPS (%f)",pProto->getDPS(),pProto2->getDPS());
669  // m_bot->GetSkillValue(pProto->RequiredSkill) < m_bot->GetSkillValue(pProto2->RequiredSkill)
670  if (pProto->getDPS() < pProto2->getDPS()) // if new item has a better DPS
671  {
672  EquipItem(pItem);
673  pProto = pProto2; // ensure that the item with the highest DPS is equipped
674  }
675  break;
676  }
677  case ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR:
678  {
679  // now in case they are same itemlevel, but one is better than the other..
680  if (pProto->ItemLevel == pProto2->ItemLevel && pProto->Quality < pProto2->Quality && pProto->Armor <= pProto2->Armor &&
681  m_bot->HasSkill(item_armor_skills[pProto2->SubClass]) && !m_bot->HasSkill(item_armor_skills[pProto2->SubClass + 1])) // itemlevel + armour + armour class
682  {
683  // First check to see if this item has stats, and if the bot REALLY wants to lose its old item
684  if (pProto2->StatsCount > 0)
685  {
686  if (!ItemStatComparison(pProto, pProto2))
687  return; // stats on equipped item are better, OR stats are not useful for this bots class/style
688  }
689  EquipItem(pItem);
690  break;
691  }
692  if (pProto->ItemLevel <= pProto2->ItemLevel && pProto->Quality < pProto2->Quality && pProto->Armor > pProto2->Armor &&
693  m_bot->HasSkill(item_armor_skills[pProto2->SubClass]) && !m_bot->HasSkill(item_armor_skills[pProto2->SubClass + 1])) // itemlevel + armour + armour class
694  {
695  // First check to see if this item has stats, and if the bot REALLY wants to lose its old item
696  if (pProto2->StatsCount > 0)
697  {
698  if (!ItemStatComparison(pProto, pProto2))
699  return; // stats on equipped item are better, OR stats are not useful for this bots class/style
700  }
701  EquipItem(pItem);
702  break;
703  }
704  if (pProto->ItemLevel <= pProto2->ItemLevel && pProto->Armor <= pProto2->Armor && m_bot->HasSkill(item_armor_skills[pProto2->SubClass]) &&
705  !m_bot->HasSkill(item_armor_skills[pProto2->SubClass + 1])) // itemlevel + armour + armour class
706  {
707  // First check to see if this item has stats, and if the bot REALLY wants to lose its old item
708  if (pProto2->StatsCount > 0)
709  {
710  if (!ItemStatComparison(pProto, pProto2))
711  return; // stats on equipped item are better, OR stats are not useful for this bots class/style
712  }
713  EquipItem(pItem);
714  break;
715  }
716  }
717  }
718  InspectUpdate();
719 }
720 
721 bool PlayerbotAI::ItemStatComparison(const ItemPrototype* pProto, const ItemPrototype* pProto2)
722 {
723  uint8 isclass = 0; // 1= caster 2 = hybrid 3 = melee
724  uint8 ishybrid = 0;
725  uint8 olditemscore = 0;
726  uint8 newitemscore = 0;
727  // get class and style to make it easier to compare later
728  switch (m_bot->getClass())
729  {
730  case CLASS_PRIEST:
731  case CLASS_MAGE:
732  case CLASS_WARLOCK:
733  isclass = 1;
734  break;
735 
736  case CLASS_PALADIN:
737  case CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT:
738  case CLASS_SHAMAN:
739  case CLASS_DRUID:
740  isclass = 2;
741  ishybrid = 1;
742  break;
743 
744  case CLASS_WARRIOR:
745  case CLASS_ROGUE:
746  isclass = 3; // melee
747  break;
748 
749  case CLASS_HUNTER:
750  isclass = 2;
751  ishybrid = 2;
752  break;
753  }
754 
755  for (int i = 0; i < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_STATS; ++i) // item can only have 10 stats. We check each stat slot available for stat and type.
756  {
757  uint32 itemmod = pProto->ItemStat[i].ItemStatType; // equipped item stats if any
758  uint32 itemmod2 = pProto2->ItemStat[i].ItemStatType; // newitem stats
759  if (!itemmod) // if no stat type in this slot, continue to next slot
760  {
761  if (!itemmod2)
762  continue;
763  }
764  // caster stats
765  if (itemmod == ITEM_MOD_MANA || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_INTELLECT || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_SPIRIT || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HIT_SPELL_RATING ||
766  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_SPELL_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HASTE_SPELL_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_SPELL_DAMAGE_DONE ||
767  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_MANA_REGENERATION || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_SPELL_POWER || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_SPELL_PENETRATION ||
768  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_MANA || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_INTELLECT || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_SPIRIT || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HIT_SPELL_RATING ||
769  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_SPELL_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HASTE_SPELL_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_SPELL_DAMAGE_DONE ||
770  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_MANA_REGENERATION || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_SPELL_POWER || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_SPELL_PENETRATION)
771  {
772  switch (isclass) // 1 caster, 2 hybrid, 3 melee
773  {
774  case 1:
775  {
776  uint32 itemmodval = pProto->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // equipped item stats if any
777  uint32 itemmodval2 = pProto2->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // newitem stats
778  if (itemmod == itemmod2) //same stat type
779  {
780  if (pProto == pProto2) // same item
781  {
782  if (olditemscore > 0)
783  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
784  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
785  }
786  if (itemmodval < itemmodval2) // which one has the most
787  {
788  if (olditemscore > 0)
789  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
790  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
791  }
792  else if (itemmodval > itemmodval2)
793  {
794  if (newitemscore > 0)
795  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
796  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
797  }
798  }
799  else
800  {
801  if (itemmod > 0)
802  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
803  if (itemmod2 > 0)
804  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
805  }
806  break;
807  }
808  case 2:
809  {
810  uint32 itemmodval = pProto->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // equipped item stats if any
811  uint32 itemmodval2 = pProto2->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // newitem stats
812  if (ishybrid != 2) //not a hunter
813  {
814  if (itemmod == itemmod2) //same stat type
815  {
816  if (pProto == pProto2) // same item
817  {
818  if (olditemscore > 0)
819  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
820  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
821  }
822  if (itemmodval < itemmodval2) // which one has the most
823  {
824  if (olditemscore > 0)
825  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
826  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
827  }
828  else if (itemmodval > itemmodval2)
829  {
830  if (newitemscore > 0)
831  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
832  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
833  }
834  }
835  else
836  {
837  if (itemmod > 0)
838  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
839  if (itemmod2 > 0)
840  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
841  }
842  }
843  else //is a hunter
844  {
845  if (itemmod > 0)
846  {
847  if (olditemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
848  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
849  }
850  if (itemmod2 > 0)
851  {
852  if (newitemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
853  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
854  }
855  }
856  break;
857  } // pure melee need nothing from this list.
858  case 3:
859  {
860  if (itemmod > 0)
861  {
862  if (olditemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
863  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
864  }
865  if (itemmod2 > 0)
866  {
867  if (newitemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
868  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
869  }
870  break;
871  }
872  default:
873  break;
874  }
875  }
876  // melee only stats (warrior/rogue) or stats that only apply to melee style combat
877  if (itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HEALTH || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_AGILITY || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_STRENGTH ||
878  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_DEFENSE_SKILL_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_DODGE_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_PARRY_RATING ||
879  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_BLOCK_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HIT_MELEE_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_MELEE_RATING ||
880  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HIT_TAKEN_MELEE_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HIT_TAKEN_RANGED_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HIT_TAKEN_SPELL_RATING ||
881  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_TAKEN_MELEE_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_TAKEN_RANGED_RATING ||
882  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_TAKEN_SPELL_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HASTE_MELEE_RATING ||
883  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HIT_TAKEN_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_TAKEN_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_ATTACK_POWER ||
884  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_BLOCK_VALUE || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HEALTH || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_AGILITY || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_STRENGTH ||
885  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_DEFENSE_SKILL_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_DODGE_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_PARRY_RATING ||
886  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_BLOCK_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HIT_MELEE_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_MELEE_RATING ||
887  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HIT_TAKEN_MELEE_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HIT_TAKEN_RANGED_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HIT_TAKEN_SPELL_RATING ||
888  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_TAKEN_MELEE_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_TAKEN_RANGED_RATING ||
889  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_TAKEN_SPELL_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HASTE_MELEE_RATING ||
890  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HIT_TAKEN_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_TAKEN_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_ATTACK_POWER ||
891  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_BLOCK_VALUE)
892  {
893  switch (isclass) // 1 caster, 2 hybrid, 3 melee
894  {
895  case 1:
896  {
897  if (itemmod > 0)
898  {
899  if (olditemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
900  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
901  }
902  if (itemmod2 > 0)
903  {
904  if (newitemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
905  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
906  }
907  break;
908  }
909  case 2:
910  {
911  uint32 itemmodval = pProto->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // equipped item stats if any
912  uint32 itemmodval2 = pProto2->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // newitem stats
913  if (itemmod == itemmod2) //same stat type
914  {
915  if (pProto == pProto2) // same item
916  {
917  if (olditemscore > 0)
918  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
919  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
920  }
921  if (itemmodval < itemmodval2) // which one has the most
922  {
923  if (olditemscore > 0)
924  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
925  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
926  }
927  else if (itemmodval > itemmodval2)
928  {
929  if (newitemscore > 0)
930  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
931  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
932  }
933  }
934  else
935  {
936  if (itemmod > 0)
937  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
938  if (itemmod2 > 0)
939  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
940  }
941  break;
942  }
943  case 3:
944  {
945  uint32 itemmodval = pProto->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // equipped item stats if any
946  uint32 itemmodval2 = pProto2->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // newitem stats
947  if (itemmod == itemmod2) //same stat type
948  {
949  if (pProto == pProto2) // same item
950  {
951  if (olditemscore > 0)
952  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
953  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
954  }
955  if (itemmodval < itemmodval2) // which one has the most
956  {
957  if (olditemscore > 0)
958  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
959  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
960  }
961  else if (itemmodval > itemmodval2)
962  {
963  if (newitemscore > 0)
964  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
965  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
966  }
967  }
968  else
969  {
970  if (itemmod > 0)
971  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
972  if (itemmod2 > 0)
973  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
974  }
975  break;
976  }
977  default:
978  break;
979  }
980  }
981  // stats which aren't strictly caster or melee (hybrid perhaps or style dependant)
982  if (itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HIT_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_RATING ||
983  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_RESILIENCE_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HASTE_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_EXPERTISE_RATING ||
984  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_ARMOR_PENETRATION_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HEALTH_REGEN || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_STAMINA ||
985  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HIT_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_RESILIENCE_RATING ||
986  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HASTE_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_EXPERTISE_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_ARMOR_PENETRATION_RATING ||
987  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HEALTH_REGEN || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_STAMINA)
988  {
989  switch (isclass) // 1 caster, 2 hybrid, 3 melee
990  {
991  case 1:
992  {
993  uint32 itemmodval = pProto->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // equipped item stats if any
994  uint32 itemmodval2 = pProto2->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // newitem stats
995  if (itemmod == itemmod2) //same stat type
996  {
997  if (pProto == pProto2) // same item
998  {
999  if (olditemscore > 0)
1000  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
1001  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1002  }
1003  if (itemmodval < itemmodval2) // which one has the most
1004  {
1005  if (olditemscore > 0)
1006  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
1007  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1008  }
1009  else if (itemmodval > itemmodval2)
1010  {
1011  if (newitemscore > 0)
1012  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
1013  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
1014  }
1015  }
1016  else
1017  {
1018  if (itemmod > 0)
1019  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
1020  if (itemmod2 > 0)
1021  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1022  }
1023  break;
1024  }
1025  case 2:
1026  {
1027  uint32 itemmodval = pProto->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // equipped item stats if any
1028  uint32 itemmodval2 = pProto2->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // newitem stats
1029  if (itemmod == itemmod2) //same stat type
1030  {
1031  if (pProto == pProto2) // same item
1032  {
1033  if (olditemscore > 0)
1034  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
1035  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1036  }
1037  if (itemmodval < itemmodval2) // which one has the most
1038  {
1039  if (olditemscore > 0)
1040  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
1041  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1042  }
1043  else if (itemmodval > itemmodval2)
1044  {
1045  if (newitemscore > 0)
1046  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
1047  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
1048  }
1049  }
1050  else
1051  {
1052  if (itemmod > 0)
1053  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
1054  if (itemmod2 > 0)
1055  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1056  }
1057  break;
1058  }
1059  case 3:
1060  {
1061  uint32 itemmodval = pProto->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // equipped item stats if any
1062  uint32 itemmodval2 = pProto2->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // newitem stats
1063  if (itemmod == itemmod2) //same stat type
1064  {
1065  if (pProto == pProto2) // same item
1066  {
1067  if (olditemscore > 0)
1068  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
1069  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1070  }
1071  if (itemmodval < itemmodval2) // which one has the most
1072  {
1073  if (olditemscore > 0)
1074  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
1075  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1076  }
1077  else if (itemmodval > itemmodval2)
1078  {
1079  if (newitemscore > 0)
1080  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
1081  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
1082  }
1083  }
1084  else
1085  {
1086  if (itemmod > 0)
1087  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
1088  if (itemmod2 > 0)
1089  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1090  }
1091  break;
1092  }
1093  default:
1094  break;
1095  }
1096  }
1097  // stats relating to ranged only
1098  if (itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HIT_RANGED_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_RANGED_RATING || itemmod == ITEM_MOD_HASTE_RANGED_RATING ||
1099  itemmod == ITEM_MOD_RANGED_ATTACK_POWER || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HIT_RANGED_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_CRIT_RANGED_RATING ||
1100  itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_HASTE_RANGED_RATING || itemmod2 == ITEM_MOD_RANGED_ATTACK_POWER)
1101  {
1102  switch (isclass) // 1 caster, 2 hybrid, 3 melee
1103  {
1104  case 1:
1105  {
1106  if (itemmod > 0)
1107  {
1108  if (olditemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
1109  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
1110  }
1111  if (itemmod2 > 0)
1112  {
1113  if (newitemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
1114  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
1115  }
1116  break;
1117  }
1118  case 2:
1119  {
1120  if (ishybrid != 2) //not a hunter
1121  {
1122  if (itemmod > 0)
1123  {
1124  if (olditemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
1125  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
1126  }
1127  if (itemmod2 > 0)
1128  {
1129  if (newitemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
1130  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
1131  }
1132  }
1133  else //is a hunter
1134  {
1135  uint32 itemmodval = pProto->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // equipped item stats if any
1136  uint32 itemmodval2 = pProto2->ItemStat[i].ItemStatValue; // newitem stats
1137  if (itemmod == itemmod2) //same stat type
1138  {
1139  if (pProto == pProto2) // same item
1140  {
1141  if (olditemscore > 0)
1142  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
1143  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1144  }
1145  if (itemmodval < itemmodval2) // which one has the most
1146  {
1147  if (olditemscore > 0)
1148  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
1149  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1150  }
1151  else if (itemmodval > itemmodval2)
1152  {
1153  if (newitemscore > 0)
1154  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
1155  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
1156  }
1157  }
1158  else
1159  {
1160  if (itemmod > 0)
1161  olditemscore = (olditemscore + 1);
1162  if (itemmod2 > 0)
1163  newitemscore = (newitemscore + 1);
1164  }
1165  }
1166  break;
1167  }
1168  case 3:
1169  {
1170  if (itemmod > 0)
1171  {
1172  if (olditemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
1173  olditemscore = (olditemscore - 1);
1174  }
1175  if (itemmod2 > 0)
1176  {
1177  if (newitemscore > 0) //we dont want any negative returns
1178  newitemscore = (newitemscore - 1);
1179  }
1180  break;
1181  }
1182  default:
1183  break;
1184  }
1185  }
1186  }
1187  if (olditemscore <= newitemscore)
1188  return true;
1189  else
1190  return false;
1191 }
1192 
1193 void PlayerbotAI::SendQuestNeedList()
1194 {
1195  std::ostringstream out;
1196 
1197  for (BotNeedItem::iterator itr = m_needItemList.begin(); itr != m_needItemList.end(); ++itr)
1198  {
1199  ItemPrototype const* pItemProto = sObjectMgr.GetItemPrototype(itr->first);
1200  if (pItemProto)
1201  {
1202  std::string itemName = pItemProto->Name1;
1203  ItemLocalization(itemName, pItemProto->ItemId);
1204 
1205  out << " " << itr->second << "x|cffffffff|Hitem:" << pItemProto->ItemId
1206  << ":0:0:0:0:0:0:0" << "|h[" << itemName
1207  << "]|h|r";
1208  }
1209  }
1210 
1211  for (BotNeedItem::iterator itr = m_needCreatureOrGOList.begin(); itr != m_needCreatureOrGOList.end(); ++itr)
1212  {
1213  CreatureInfo const* cInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(itr->first);
1214  if (cInfo)
1215  {
1216  std::string creatureName = cInfo->Name;
1217  CreatureLocalization(creatureName, cInfo->Entry);
1218  out << " " << itr->second << "x|cFFFFFF00|Hcreature_entry:" << itr->first << "|h[" << creatureName << "]|h|r";
1219  }
1220 
1221  if (m_bot->HasQuestForGO(itr->first))
1222  {
1223  GameObjectInfo const* gInfo = ObjectMgr::GetGameObjectInfo(itr->first);
1224  if (gInfo)
1225  {
1226  std::string gameobjectName = gInfo->name;
1227  GameObjectLocalization(gameobjectName, gInfo->id);
1228  out << " " << itr->second << "x|cFFFFFF00|Hgameobject_entry:" << itr->first << "|h[" << gameobjectName << "]|h|r";
1229  }
1230  }
1231  }
1232 
1233  TellMaster("Here's a list of all things needed for quests:");
1234  if (!out.str().empty())
1235  TellMaster(out.str().c_str());
1236 }
1237 
1238 bool PlayerbotAI::IsItemUseful(uint32 itemid)
1239 {
1240  const static uint32 item_weapon_skills[MAX_ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON] =
1241  {
1242  SKILL_AXES, SKILL_2H_AXES, SKILL_BOWS, SKILL_GUNS, SKILL_MACES,
1243  SKILL_2H_MACES, SKILL_POLEARMS, SKILL_SWORDS, SKILL_2H_SWORDS, 0,
1244  SKILL_STAVES, 0, 0, SKILL_UNARMED, 0,
1245  SKILL_DAGGERS, SKILL_THROWN, SKILL_ASSASSINATION, SKILL_CROSSBOWS, SKILL_WANDS,
1246  SKILL_FISHING
1247  };
1248 
1249  const static uint32 item_armor_skills[MAX_ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR] =
1250  {
1251  0, SKILL_CLOTH, SKILL_LEATHER, SKILL_MAIL, SKILL_PLATE_MAIL, 0, SKILL_SHIELD, 0, 0, 0, 0
1252  };
1253 
1254  ItemPrototype const* pProto = ObjectMgr::GetItemPrototype(itemid);
1255  if (!pProto || pProto->Quality < ITEM_QUALITY_NORMAL)
1256  return false;
1257 
1258  // do we already have the max allowed of item if more than zero?
1259  if (pProto->MaxCount > 0 && m_bot->HasItemCount(itemid, pProto->MaxCount, true))
1260  return false;
1261 
1262  // quest related items
1263  if (pProto->StartQuest > 0 && HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_QUEST))
1264  return true;
1265 
1266  switch (pProto->Class)
1267  {
1268  case ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON:
1269  if (pProto->SubClass >= MAX_ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON)
1270  return false;
1271  else
1272  return m_bot->HasSkill(item_weapon_skills[pProto->SubClass]);
1273  break;
1274  case ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR:
1275  if (pProto->SubClass >= MAX_ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR)
1276  return false;
1277  else
1278  return (m_bot->HasSkill(item_armor_skills[pProto->SubClass]) && !m_bot->HasSkill(item_armor_skills[pProto->SubClass + 1]));
1279  break;
1280  case ITEM_CLASS_QUEST:
1281  if (!HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_QUEST))
1282  break;
1283  case ITEM_CLASS_KEY:
1284  return true;
1285  case ITEM_CLASS_GEM:
1286  if ((m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_BLACKSMITHING) ||
1287  m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ENGINEERING) ||
1288  m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_JEWELCRAFTING)))
1289  return true;
1290  break;
1291  case ITEM_CLASS_TRADE_GOODS:
1292  if (!HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_PROFESSION))
1293  break;
1294 
1295  switch (pProto->SubClass)
1296  {
1297  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_PARTS:
1298  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_EXPLOSIVES:
1299  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_DEVICES:
1300  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ENGINEERING))
1301  return true;
1302  break;
1303  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_JEWELCRAFTING:
1304  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_JEWELCRAFTING))
1305  return true;
1306  break;
1307  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_CLOTH:
1308  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_TAILORING))
1309  return true;
1310  break;
1311  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_LEATHER:
1312  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_LEATHERWORKING))
1313  return true;
1314  break;
1315  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_METAL_STONE:
1316  if ((m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_BLACKSMITHING) ||
1317  m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ENGINEERING) ||
1318  m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_MINING)))
1319  return true;
1320  break;
1321  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_MEAT:
1322  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_COOKING))
1323  return true;
1324  break;
1325  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_HERB:
1326  if ((m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_HERBALISM) ||
1327  m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ALCHEMY) ||
1328  m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_INSCRIPTION)))
1329  return true;
1330  break;
1331  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_ELEMENTAL:
1332  return true; // pretty much every profession uses these a bit
1333  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_ENCHANTING:
1334  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ENCHANTING))
1335  return true;
1336  break;
1337  default:
1338  break;
1339  }
1340  break;
1341  case ITEM_CLASS_RECIPE:
1342  {
1343  if (!HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_PROFESSION))
1344  break;
1345 
1346  // skip recipes that we have
1347  if (m_bot->HasSpell(pProto->Spells[2].SpellId))
1348  break;
1349 
1350  switch (pProto->SubClass)
1351  {
1352  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_LEATHERWORKING_PATTERN:
1353  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_LEATHERWORKING))
1354  return true;
1355  break;
1356  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_TAILORING_PATTERN:
1357  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_TAILORING))
1358  return true;
1359  break;
1360  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_ENGINEERING_SCHEMATIC:
1361  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ENGINEERING))
1362  return true;
1363  break;
1364  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_BLACKSMITHING:
1365  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_BLACKSMITHING))
1366  return true;
1367  break;
1368  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_COOKING_RECIPE:
1369  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_COOKING))
1370  return true;
1371  break;
1372  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_ALCHEMY_RECIPE:
1373  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ALCHEMY))
1374  return true;
1375  break;
1376  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_FIRST_AID_MANUAL:
1377  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_FIRST_AID))
1378  return true;
1379  break;
1380  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_ENCHANTING_FORMULA:
1381  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ENCHANTING))
1382  return true;
1383  break;
1384  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_FISHING_MANUAL:
1385  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_FISHING))
1386  return true;
1387  break;
1388  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_JEWELCRAFTING_RECIPE:
1389  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_JEWELCRAFTING))
1390  return true;
1391  break;
1392  default:
1393  break;
1394  }
1395  }
1396  default:
1397  break;
1398  }
1399  return false;
1400 }
1401 
1402 void PlayerbotAI::ReloadAI()
1403 {
1404  switch (m_bot->getClass())
1405  {
1406  case CLASS_PRIEST:
1407  if (m_classAI) delete m_classAI;
1408  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_RANGED;
1409  m_classAI = (PlayerbotClassAI*) new PlayerbotPriestAI(*GetMaster(), *m_bot, *this);
1410  break;
1411  case CLASS_MAGE:
1412  if (m_classAI) delete m_classAI;
1413  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_RANGED;
1414  m_classAI = (PlayerbotClassAI*) new PlayerbotMageAI(*GetMaster(), *m_bot, *this);
1415  break;
1416  case CLASS_WARLOCK:
1417  if (m_classAI) delete m_classAI;
1418  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_RANGED;
1419  m_classAI = (PlayerbotClassAI*) new PlayerbotWarlockAI(*GetMaster(), *m_bot, *this);
1420  break;
1421  case CLASS_WARRIOR:
1422  if (m_classAI) delete m_classAI;
1423  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_MELEE;
1424  m_classAI = (PlayerbotClassAI*) new PlayerbotWarriorAI(*GetMaster(), *m_bot, *this);
1425  break;
1426  case CLASS_SHAMAN:
1427  if (m_classAI) delete m_classAI;
1428  if (m_bot->GetSpec() == SHAMAN_SPEC_ENHANCEMENT)
1429  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_MELEE;
1430  else
1431  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_RANGED;
1432  m_classAI = (PlayerbotClassAI*) new PlayerbotShamanAI(*GetMaster(), *m_bot, *this);
1433  break;
1434  case CLASS_PALADIN:
1435  if (m_classAI) delete m_classAI;
1436  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_MELEE;
1437  m_classAI = (PlayerbotClassAI*) new PlayerbotPaladinAI(*GetMaster(), *m_bot, *this);
1438  break;
1439  case CLASS_ROGUE:
1440  if (m_classAI) delete m_classAI;
1441  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_MELEE;
1442  m_classAI = (PlayerbotClassAI*) new PlayerbotRogueAI(*GetMaster(), *m_bot, *this);
1443  break;
1444  case CLASS_DRUID:
1445  if (m_classAI) delete m_classAI;
1446  if (m_bot->GetSpec() == DRUID_SPEC_FERAL)
1447  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_MELEE;
1448  else
1449  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_RANGED;
1450  m_classAI = (PlayerbotClassAI*) new PlayerbotDruidAI(*GetMaster(), *m_bot, *this);
1451  break;
1452  case CLASS_HUNTER:
1453  if (m_classAI) delete m_classAI;
1454  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_RANGED;
1455  m_classAI = (PlayerbotClassAI*) new PlayerbotHunterAI(*GetMaster(), *m_bot, *this);
1456  break;
1457  case CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT:
1458  if (m_classAI) delete m_classAI;
1459  m_combatStyle = COMBAT_MELEE;
1460  m_classAI = (PlayerbotClassAI*) new PlayerbotDeathKnightAI(*GetMaster(), *m_bot, *this);
1461  break;
1462  }
1463 
1464  HERB_GATHERING = initSpell(HERB_GATHERING_1);
1465  MINING = initSpell(MINING_1);
1466  SKINNING = initSpell(SKINNING_1);
1467 }
1468 
1469 void PlayerbotAI::SendOrders(Player& /*player*/)
1470 {
1471  std::ostringstream out;
1472 
1473  if (m_combatOrder == ORDERS_NONE)
1474  out << "Got no combat orders!";
1475  else if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_MAIN_TANK)
1476  out << "I'm a MAIN TANK";
1477  else if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_TANK)
1478  out << "I TANK";
1479  else if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_ASSIST)
1480  out << "I ASSIST " << (m_targetAssist ? m_targetAssist->GetName() : "unknown");
1481  else if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_MAIN_HEAL)
1482  out << "I'm a MAIN HEALER";
1483  else if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_HEAL)
1484  out << "I HEAL";
1485  else if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_NOT_MAIN_HEAL)
1486  out << "I HEAL but will ignore any main tank";
1487  else if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_PASSIVE)
1488  out << "I'm PASSIVE";
1489  if ((m_combatOrder & ORDERS_PRIMARY) && (m_combatOrder & (ORDERS_PROTECT | ORDERS_RESIST | ORDERS_NODISPEL)))
1490  {
1491  out << " and ";
1492  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_PROTECT)
1493  out << "I PROTECT " << (m_targetProtect ? m_targetProtect->GetName() : "unknown");
1494  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_RESIST)
1495  {
1496  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_RESIST_FIRE)
1497  out << "I RESIST FIRE";
1498  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_RESIST_NATURE)
1499  out << "I RESIST NATURE";
1500  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_RESIST_FROST)
1501  out << "I RESIST FROST";
1502  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_RESIST_SHADOW)
1503  out << "I RESIST SHADOW";
1504  }
1505  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_NODISPEL)
1506  out << "I WON'T DISPEL";
1507  }
1508  out << ".";
1509 
1510  if (m_mgr.m_confDebugWhisper)
1511  {
1512  out << " " << (IsInCombat() ? "I'm in COMBAT! " : "Not in combat. ");
1513  out << "Current state is ";
1514  if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_NORMAL)
1515  out << "NORMAL";
1516  else if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_COMBAT)
1517  out << "COMBAT";
1518  else if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_TAME)
1519  out << "TAMING";
1520  else if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_DEAD)
1521  out << "DEAD";
1522  else if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_DEADRELEASED)
1523  out << "RELEASED";
1524  else if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_LOOTING)
1525  out << "LOOTING";
1526  else if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_FLYING)
1527  out << "FLYING";
1528  out << ". Movement order is ";
1529  if (m_movementOrder == MOVEMENT_NONE)
1530  out << "NONE";
1531  else if (m_movementOrder == MOVEMENT_FOLLOW)
1532  out << "FOLLOW " << (m_followTarget ? m_followTarget->GetName() : "unknown");
1533  else if (m_movementOrder == MOVEMENT_STAY)
1534  out << "STAY";
1535  out << ". Got " << m_attackerInfo.size() << " attacker(s) in list.";
1536  out << " Next action in " << m_ignoreAIUpdatesUntilTime - CurrentTime() << "sec.";
1537  }
1538 
1539  TellMaster(out.str().c_str());
1540  if (m_DelayAttack)
1541  TellMaster("My combat delay is '%u'", m_DelayAttack);
1542 }
1543 
1544 // handle outgoing packets the server would send to the client
1545 void PlayerbotAI::HandleBotOutgoingPacket(const WorldPacket& packet)
1546 {
1547  switch (packet.GetOpcode())
1548  {
1549  case SMSG_DUEL_WINNER:
1550  {
1551  m_bot->HandleEmoteCommand(EMOTE_ONESHOT_APPLAUD);
1552  return;
1553  }
1554  case SMSG_DUEL_COMPLETE:
1555  {
1556  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(4);
1557  m_ScenarioType = SCENARIO_PVE;
1558  ReloadAI();
1559  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(true);
1560  return;
1561  }
1562  case SMSG_DUEL_OUTOFBOUNDS:
1563  {
1564  m_bot->HandleEmoteCommand(EMOTE_ONESHOT_CHICKEN);
1565  return;
1566  }
1567  case SMSG_DUEL_REQUESTED:
1568  {
1569  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(0);
1570  WorldPacket p(packet);
1571  ObjectGuid flagGuid;
1572  p >> flagGuid;
1573  ObjectGuid playerGuid;
1574  p >> playerGuid;
1575  Player* const pPlayer = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(playerGuid);
1576  if (canObeyCommandFrom(*pPlayer))
1577  {
1578  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(true);
1579  std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket> packet(new WorldPacket(CMSG_DUEL_ACCEPTED, 8));
1580  *packet << flagGuid;
1581  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::move(packet)); // queue the packet to get around race condition
1582 
1583  // follow target in casting range
1584  float angle = rand_float(0, M_PI_F);
1585  float dist = rand_float(4, 10);
1586 
1587  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(true);
1588  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveFollow(pPlayer, dist, angle);
1589 
1590  m_bot->SetSelectionGuid(ObjectGuid(playerGuid));
1591  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(4);
1592  m_ScenarioType = SCENARIO_PVP_DUEL;
1593  }
1594  return;
1595  }
1596 
1597  case SMSG_PET_TAME_FAILURE:
1598  {
1599  // DEBUG_LOG("SMSG_PET_TAME_FAILURE");
1600  WorldPacket p(packet);
1601  uint8 reason;
1602  p >> reason;
1603 
1604  switch (reason)
1605  {
1606  case PETTAME_INVALIDCREATURE: // = 1,
1607  DEBUG_LOG("Invalid Creature");
1608  break;
1609  case PETTAME_TOOMANY: // = 2,
1610  DEBUG_LOG("Too many Creature");
1611  break;
1612  case PETTAME_CREATUREALREADYOWNED: // = 3,
1613  DEBUG_LOG("Creature already owned");
1614  break;
1615  case PETTAME_NOTTAMEABLE: // = 4,
1616  DEBUG_LOG("Creature not tameable");
1617  break;
1618  case PETTAME_ANOTHERSUMMONACTIVE: // = 5,
1619  DEBUG_LOG("Another summon active");
1620  break;
1621  case PETTAME_UNITSCANTTAME: // = 6,
1622  DEBUG_LOG("Unit cant tame");
1623  break;
1624  case PETTAME_NOPETAVAILABLE: // = 7, // not used in taming
1625  DEBUG_LOG("No pet available");
1626  break;
1627  case PETTAME_INTERNALERROR: // = 8,
1628  DEBUG_LOG("Internal error");
1629  break;
1630  case PETTAME_TOOHIGHLEVEL: // = 9,
1631  DEBUG_LOG("Creature level too high");
1632  break;
1633  case PETTAME_DEAD: // = 10, // not used in taming
1634  DEBUG_LOG("Creature dead");
1635  break;
1636  case PETTAME_NOTDEAD: // = 11, // not used in taming
1637  DEBUG_LOG("Creature not dead");
1638  break;
1639  case PETTAME_CANTCONTROLEXOTIC: // = 12, // 3.x
1640  DEBUG_LOG("Creature exotic");
1641  break;
1642  case PETTAME_UNKNOWNERROR: // = 13
1643  DEBUG_LOG("Unknown error");
1644  break;
1645  }
1646  return;
1647  }
1648 
1649  case SMSG_BUY_FAILED:
1650  {
1651  WorldPacket p(packet); // 8+4+4+1
1652  ObjectGuid vendorguid;
1653  p >> vendorguid;
1654  uint32 itemid;
1655  p >> itemid;
1656  uint8 msg;
1657  p >> msg; // error msg
1658  p.resize(13);
1659 
1660  switch (msg)
1661  {
1662  case BUY_ERR_CANT_FIND_ITEM:
1663  break;
1664  case BUY_ERR_ITEM_ALREADY_SOLD:
1665  break;
1666  case BUY_ERR_NOT_ENOUGHT_MONEY:
1667  {
1668  Announce(CANT_AFFORD);
1669  break;
1670  }
1671  case BUY_ERR_SELLER_DONT_LIKE_YOU:
1672  break;
1673  case BUY_ERR_DISTANCE_TOO_FAR:
1674  break;
1675  case BUY_ERR_ITEM_SOLD_OUT:
1676  break;
1677  case BUY_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE:
1678  {
1679  Announce(INVENTORY_FULL);
1680  break;
1681  }
1682  case BUY_ERR_RANK_REQUIRE:
1683  break;
1684  case BUY_ERR_REPUTATION_REQUIRE:
1685  break;
1686  }
1687  return;
1688  }
1689 
1690  case SMSG_AUCTION_COMMAND_RESULT:
1691  {
1692  uint32 auctionId, Action, ErrorCode;
1693  std::string action[3] = {"Creating", "Cancelling", "Bidding"};
1694  std::ostringstream out;
1695 
1696  WorldPacket p(packet);
1697  p >> auctionId;
1698  p >> Action;
1699  p >> ErrorCode;
1700  p.resize(12);
1701 
1702  switch (ErrorCode)
1703  {
1704  case AUCTION_OK:
1705  {
1706  out << "|cff1eff00|h" << action[Action] << " was successful|h|r";
1707  break;
1708  }
1709  case AUCTION_ERR_DATABASE:
1710  {
1711  out << "|cffff0000|hWhile" << action[Action] << ", an internal error occured|h|r";
1712  break;
1713  }
1714  case AUCTION_ERR_NOT_ENOUGH_MONEY:
1715  {
1716  out << "|cffff0000|hWhile " << action[Action] << ", I didn't have enough money|h|r";
1717  break;
1718  }
1719  case AUCTION_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND:
1720  {
1721  out << "|cffff0000|hItem was not found!|h|r";
1722  break;
1723  }
1724  case AUCTION_ERR_BID_OWN:
1725  {
1726  out << "|cffff0000|hI cannot bid on my own auctions!|h|r";
1727  break;
1728  }
1729  }
1730  TellMaster(out.str().c_str());
1731  return;
1732  }
1733 
1734  case SMSG_INVENTORY_CHANGE_FAILURE:
1735  {
1736  WorldPacket p(packet);
1737  uint8 err;
1738  p >> err;
1739 
1740  if (err != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1741  {
1742  switch (err)
1743  {
1744  case EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS:
1745  {
1746  TellMaster("I can't carry anymore of those.");
1747  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
1748  return;
1749  }
1750  case EQUIP_ERR_MISSING_REAGENT:
1751  TellMaster("I'm missing some reagents for that.");
1752  return;
1753  case EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_LOCKED:
1754  TellMaster("That item is locked.");
1755  return;
1756  case EQUIP_ERR_ALREADY_LOOTED:
1757  TellMaster("That is already looted.");
1758  return;
1759  case EQUIP_ERR_INVENTORY_FULL:
1760  {
1761  if (DropGarbage(false))
1762  return;
1763 
1764  if (m_lootCurrent.IsGameObject())
1765  if (GameObject* go = m_bot->GetMap()->GetGameObject(m_lootCurrent))
1766  m_collectObjects.remove(go->GetEntry());
1767 
1768  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
1769 
1770  if (m_inventory_full)
1771  return;
1772 
1773  TellMaster("My inventory is full.");
1774  m_inventory_full = true;
1775  return;
1776  }
1777  case EQUIP_ERR_NOT_IN_COMBAT:
1778  TellMaster("I can't use that in combat.");
1779  return;
1780  case EQUIP_ERR_LOOT_CANT_LOOT_THAT_NOW:
1781  TellMaster("I can't get that now.");
1782  return;
1783  case EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_UNIQUE_EQUIPABLE:
1784  TellMaster("I can only have one of those equipped.");
1785  return;
1786  case EQUIP_ERR_BANK_FULL:
1787  TellMaster("My bank is full.");
1788  return;
1789  case EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND:
1790  TellMaster("I can't find the item.");
1791  return;
1792  case EQUIP_ERR_TOO_FAR_AWAY_FROM_BANK:
1793  TellMaster("I'm too far from the bank.");
1794  return;
1795  case EQUIP_ERR_NONE:
1796  TellMaster("I can't use it on that");
1797  return;
1798  default:
1799  TellMaster("I can't use that.");
1800  DEBUG_LOG("[PlayerbotAI]: HandleBotOutgoingPacket - SMSG_INVENTORY_CHANGE_FAILURE: %u", err);
1801  return;
1802  }
1803  }
1804  }
1805 
1806  case SMSG_CAST_RESULT:
1807  {
1808  WorldPacket p(packet);
1809  uint8 castCount;
1810  uint32 spellId;
1811  uint8 result;
1812  std::ostringstream out;
1813 
1814  p >> castCount >> spellId >> result;
1815 
1816  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
1817  if (!spellInfo)
1818  return;
1819 
1820  if (result != SPELL_CAST_OK)
1821  {
1822  switch (result)
1823  {
1824  case SPELL_FAILED_INTERRUPTED: // 40
1825  {
1826  DEBUG_LOG("spell %s interrupted (%u)", spellInfo->SpellName[0], result);
1827  return;
1828  }
1829  case SPELL_FAILED_UNIT_NOT_INFRONT: // 134
1830  if (m_targetCombat)
1831  m_bot->SetInFront(m_targetCombat);
1832  case SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS: // 12
1833  {
1834  // DEBUG_LOG("[%s]bad target / not in front(%u) for spellId (%u) & m_CurrentlyCastingSpellId (%u)",m_bot->GetName(),result,spellId,m_CurrentlyCastingSpellId);
1835  Spell* const pSpell = GetCurrentSpell();
1836  if (pSpell)
1837  pSpell->cancel();
1838  return;
1839  }
1840  case SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_SPELL_FOCUS: // 102
1841  {
1842  switch (spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus) // SpellFocusObject.dbc id
1843  {
1844  case 1: // need an anvil
1845  out << "|cffff0000I require an anvil.";
1846  break;
1847  case 2: // need a loom
1848  out << "|cffff0000I require a loom.";
1849  break;
1850  case 3: // need forge
1851  out << "|cffff0000I require a forge.";
1852  break;
1853  case 4: // need cooking fire
1854  out << "|cffff0000I require a cooking fire.";
1855  break;
1856  default:
1857  out << "|cffff0000I Require Spell Focus on " << spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus;
1858  }
1859  break;
1860  }
1861  case SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED: // 14
1862  {
1863  out << "|cffff0000Item cannot be disenchanted.";
1864  break;
1865  }
1866  case SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_MILLED: // 16
1867  {
1868  out << "|cffff0000I cannot mill that.";
1869  break;
1870  }
1871  case SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_PROSPECTED: // 17
1872  {
1873  out << "|cffff0000There are no gems in this.";
1874  break;
1875  }
1876  case SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS: // 29
1877  {
1878  out << "|cffff0000That item is not a valid target.";
1879  break;
1880  }
1881  case SPELL_FAILED_NEED_MORE_ITEMS: // 55
1882  {
1883  ItemPrototype const* pProto = ObjectMgr::GetItemPrototype(m_itemTarget);
1884  if (!pProto)
1885  return;
1886 
1887  out << "|cffff0000Requires 5 " << pProto->Name1 << ".";
1888  m_itemTarget = 0;
1889  break;
1890  }
1891  case SPELL_FAILED_REAGENTS:
1892  {
1893  out << "|cffff0000I don't have the reagents";
1894  break;
1895  }
1896  default:
1897  DEBUG_LOG("[%s] SMSG_CAST_FAIL: %s err (%u)", m_bot->GetName(), spellInfo->SpellName[0], result);
1898  return;
1899  }
1900  }
1901  TellMaster(out.str().c_str());
1902  return;
1903  }
1904 
1905  case SMSG_SPELL_FAILURE:
1906  {
1907  WorldPacket p(packet);
1908  uint8 castCount;
1909  uint32 spellId;
1910  ObjectGuid casterGuid;
1911 
1912  p >> casterGuid.ReadAsPacked();

1914  return;

1918  {
1919  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(0);
1920  m_CurrentlyCastingSpellId = 0;
1921  }
1922  return;
1923  }

1932  return;
1933  m_bot->m_movementInfo.AddMovementFlag(MOVEFLAG_FLYING);
1934  //m_bot->SetSpeed(MOVE_RUN, GetMaster()->GetSpeed(MOVE_FLIGHT) +0.1f, true);

1952  // Handle chat messages here
1953  case SMSG_MESSAGECHAT:
1954  {
1955  WorldPacket p(packet);
1956  uint8 msgtype;
1957  uint32 language;
1958 
1959  p >> msgtype; // 1 type
1960  p >> language; // 4 language
1961 
1962  if (language == LANG_ADDON)
1963  return;
1964 
1965  switch (msgtype)
1966  {
1967  case CHAT_MSG_RAID:
1968  case CHAT_MSG_RAID_LEADER:
1969  case CHAT_MSG_PARTY:
1970  case CHAT_MSG_PARTY_LEADER:
1971  case CHAT_MSG_WHISPER:
1972  {
1973  ObjectGuid senderGuid;
1974  std::string channelName;
1975  uint32 length;
1976  std::string text;
1977  uint8 chattag;
1978 
1979  p >> senderGuid; // 8 player from guid
1980  p.read_skip<uint32>(); // 4 chat msg group
1981  p.read_skip<uint64>(); // 8 player from guid
1982  p >> length; // 4 length of text
1983  p >> text; // string message
1984  p >> chattag; // 1 AFK/DND/WHISPER_INFORM
1985 
1986  Player* sender = sObjectMgr.GetPlayer(senderGuid);
1987  if (!sender) // couldn't find player that sent message
1988  return;
1989 
1990  // do not listen to other bots
1991  if (sender != m_bot && sender->GetPlayerbotAI())
1992  return;
1993  HandleCommand(text, *sender);
1994  return;
1995  }
1996  default:
1997  return;
1998  }
1999 
2000  return;
2001  }
2002 
2003  // If the leader role was given to the bot automatically give it to the master
2004  // if the master is in the group, otherwise leave group
2005  case SMSG_GROUP_SET_LEADER:
2006  {

2008  std::string name;
2009  p >> name;
2010  if (m_bot->GetGroup() && name == m_bot->GetName())
2011  {
2012  if (m_bot->GetGroup()->IsMember(GetMaster()->GetObjectGuid()))
2013  {
2014  p.resize(8);
2015  p << GetMaster()->GetObjectGuid();
2016  m_bot->GetSession()->HandleGroupSetLeaderOpcode(p);
2017  }
2018  else
2019  {
2020  p.clear(); // not really needed
2021  m_bot->GetSession()->HandleGroupDisbandOpcode(p); // packet not used updated code
2022  }
2023  }
2024  return;
2025  }

2028  case SMSG_PARTY_COMMAND_RESULT:

2040  m_bot->GetSession()->HandleGroupDisbandOpcode(p); // packet not used updated code
2041  return;

2044  // Handle Group invites (auto accept if master is in group, otherwise decline & send message
2045  case SMSG_GROUP_INVITE:

2061  buf += GetMaster()->GetName();

2080  return;

2083  return;

2085  guild->LogGuildEvent(GUILD_EVENT_LOG_JOIN_GUILD, m_bot->GetObjectGuid());
2086

2091  // also sends list of tradable items bot can trade if bot is allowed to obey commands from

2099  p >> status;
2100  p.resize(4);

2102  //4 == TRADE_STATUS_TRADE_ACCEPT

2104  {
2105  m_bot->GetSession()->HandleAcceptTradeOpcode(p); // packet not used
2106  SetQuestNeedItems();
2107  AutoUpgradeEquipment();
2108  }
2109 
2110  //1 == TRADE_STATUS_BEGIN_TRADE
2111  else if (status == 1)
2112  {
2113  m_bot->GetSession()->HandleBeginTradeOpcode(p); // packet not used
2114 
2115  if (!canObeyCommandFrom(*(m_bot->GetTrader())))
2116  {
2117  // TODO: Really? What if I give a bot all my junk so it's inventory is full when a nice green/blue/purple comes along?
2118  SendWhisper("I'm not allowed to trade you any of my items, but you are free to give me money or items.", *(m_bot->GetTrader()));
2119  return;
2120  }
2121 
2122  // list out items
2123  std::ostringstream out;
2124  std::ostringstream outT;
2125  std::ostringstream outNT;
2126  uint8 countTotalTradeable = 0;
2127  uint8 countTradeable = 0;
2128  uint8 countNonTradeable = 0;
2129 
2130  outT << "Tradeable:";
2131  outNT << "Non-tradeable:";
2132  // list out items in main backpack
2133  for (uint8 slot = INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START; slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; slot++)
2134  {

2136  if (pItem)
2137  {
2138  if (pItem->CanBeTraded())
2139  {
2140  countTradeable++;
2141  MakeItemLink(pItem, outT, true);
2142  }
2143  else
2144  {
2145  countNonTradeable++;
2146  MakeItemLink(pItem, outNT, true);
2147  }
2148  }
2149  }
2150 
2151  countTotalTradeable = countTradeable;
2152  out << "Backpack (" << countTradeable + countNonTradeable << "/16) ";
2153  if (countTradeable > 0)
2154  out << outT.str();
2155  if (countNonTradeable > 0)
2156  out << "\r" << outNT.str();
2157  SendWhisper(out.str().c_str(), *(m_bot->GetTrader()));
2158 
2159  // list out items in other removable backpacks
2160  for (uint8 bag = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; bag < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++bag)
2161  {
2162  const Bag* const pBag = (Bag*) m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, bag);
2163  if (pBag)
2164  {
2165  countTradeable = 0;
2166  countNonTradeable = 0;
2167  std::ostringstream outbagT;
2168  std::ostringstream outbagNT;
2169  outbagT << "Tradeable:";
2170  outbagNT << "Non-tradeable:";
2171 
2172  for (uint8 slot = 0; slot < pBag->GetBagSize(); ++slot)
2173  {
2174  const Item* const pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(bag, slot);
2175  if (pItem)
2176  {
2177  if (pItem->CanBeTraded())
2178  {
2179  countTradeable++;
2180  MakeItemLink(pItem, outbagT, true);
2181  }
2182  else
2183  {
2184  countNonTradeable++;
2185  MakeItemLink(pItem, outbagNT, true);
2186  }
2187  }
2188  }
2189 
2190  countTotalTradeable += countTradeable;
2191  std::ostringstream outbag;

2194  ItemLocalization(bagName, pBagProto->ItemId);
2195  outbag << bagName << " (";

2197  outbag << ") ";
2198  if (countTradeable > 0)
2199  outbag << outbagT.str();
2200  if (countNonTradeable > 0)
2201  outbag << "\r" << outbagNT.str();
2202  SendWhisper(outbag.str().c_str(), *(m_bot->GetTrader()));
2203  }
2204  }
2205  if (countTotalTradeable == 0)
2206  SendWhisper("I have no items to give you.", *(m_bot->GetTrader()));
2207 
2208  // calculate how much money bot has
2209  // send bot the message
2210  uint32 copper = m_bot->GetMoney();
2211  out.str("");
2212  out << "I have |cff00ff00" << Cash(copper) << "|r";
2213  SendWhisper(out.str().c_str(), *(m_bot->GetTrader()));
2214  }

2216  }

2298  case SMSG_LOOT_RESPONSE:
2299  {
2300  WorldPacket p(packet); // (8+1+4+1+1+4+4+4+4+4+1)
2301  ObjectGuid guid;
2302  uint8 loot_type;
2303 
2304  p >> guid; // 8 corpse guid
2305  p >> loot_type; // 1 loot type
2306

2318  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket>(packet));
2319  }

2321  for (uint8 i = 0; i < items; ++i)
2322  {
2323  uint32 itemid;
2324  uint32 itemcount;
2325  uint8 lootslot_type;
2326  uint8 itemindex;
2327

2329  p >> itemid; // 4 itemid
2330  p >> itemcount; // 4 item stack count

2332  p.read_skip<uint32>(); // 4 randomSuffix

2335

2346  (loot_type == LOOT_CORPSE && (IsInQuestItemList(itemid) || IsItemUseful(itemid))))

2359

2363  }

2367  TellMaster("Skipping loot item %s", pProto->Name1);
2368  }
2369  }
2370  }

2377  WorldPacket* const packet = new WorldPacket(CMSG_LOOT_RELEASE, 8);
2378  *packet << guid;
2379  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket>(packet));
2380

2382  }
2383 
2384  case SMSG_LOOT_RELEASE_RESPONSE:
2385  {
2386  WorldPacket p(packet);
2387  ObjectGuid guid;
2388 
2389  p >> guid;
2390 
2391  if (guid == m_lootPrev)
2392  {
2393  Creature* c = m_bot->GetMap()->GetCreature(m_lootPrev);
2394 
2395  if (c && c->GetCreatureInfo()->SkinningLootId && c->GetLootStatus() != CREATURE_LOOT_STATUS_LOOTED)
2396  {

2398  // check if it is a leather skin and if it is to be collected (could be ore or herb)
2399  if (m_bot->HasSkill(reqSkill) && ((reqSkill != SKILL_SKINNING) ||
2400  (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_SKIN) && reqSkill == SKILL_SKINNING)))
2401  {
2402  // calculate skill requirement
2403  uint32 skillValue = m_bot->GetSkillValue(reqSkill);
2404  uint32 targetLevel = c->GetLevel();
2405  uint32 reqSkillValue = targetLevel < 10 ? 0 : targetLevel < 20 ? (targetLevel - 10) * 10 : targetLevel * 5;
2406  if (skillValue >= reqSkillValue)
2407  {
2408  m_lootCurrent = m_lootPrev;
2409  if (m_debugWhisper)
2410  TellMaster("I will try to skin next loot attempt.");
2411 
2412  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(1);
2413  return; // so that the DoLoot function is called again to get skin
2414  }
2415  else
2416  TellMaster("My skill is %u but it requires %u", skillValue, reqSkillValue);
2417  }
2418  }
2419

2421  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(false);
2422  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveIdle();
2423  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(0);
2424  }
2425 
2426  return;
2427  }
2428 
2429  case SMSG_LOOT_ROLL_WON:
2430  {
2431  WorldPacket p(packet); // (8+4+4+4+4+8+1+1)
2432  ObjectGuid p_guid, co_guid;
2433  uint32 itemid;
2434 
2435  p >> co_guid; // creature or gameobject guid what we're looting
2436  p.read_skip<uint32>(); // item slot in loot
2437  p >> itemid; // the itemEntryId for the item that shall be rolled fo
2438  p.read_skip<uint32>(); // randomSuffix

2440  p >> p_guid; // guid of the player who won

2443 
2444  Loot* loot = sLootMgr.GetLoot(m_bot, co_guid);
2445 
2446  if (!loot)
2447  return;
2448 
2449  // Clean up: remove target guid from (ignore list)
2450  for (std::list<ObjectGuid>::iterator itr = m_being_rolled_on.begin(); itr != m_being_rolled_on.end();)
2451  if (co_guid == *itr)
2452  {
2453  // DEBUG_LOG("Rolled item won, removing (%s)",co_guid.GetString().c_str());
2454  itr = m_being_rolled_on.erase(itr);
2455  }
2456  else
2457  ++itr;
2458 
2459  // allow creature corpses to be skinned after roll
2460  loot->Release(m_bot);
2461 
2462  if (m_bot->GetObjectGuid() != p_guid)
2463  return;
2464 
2465  SetState(BOTSTATE_DELAYED);
2466 
2467  /* ItemPrototype const *pProto = ObjectMgr::GetItemPrototype(itemid);
2468  if(pProto)
2469  {
2470  std::ostringstream out;
2471  out << "|cff009900" << "I won: |r";
2472  MakeItemLink(pProto,out);
2473  if (FindItem(itemid,true))
2474  out << "and have the item";
2475  TellMaster(out.str().c_str());
2476  }*/
2477  return;
2478  }
2479 
2480  case SMSG_PARTYKILLLOG:
2481  {
2482  // reset AI delay so bots immediately respond to next combat target & or looting/skinning
2483  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(0);
2484  return;
2485  }
2486 
2487  case SMSG_ITEM_PUSH_RESULT:
2488  {
2489  WorldPacket p(packet); // (8+4+4+4+1+4+4+4+4+4+4)
2490  ObjectGuid guid;
2491 
2492  p >> guid; // 8 player guid
2493  if (m_bot->GetObjectGuid() != guid)
2494  return;
2495 
2496  uint8 bagslot;
2497  uint32 itemslot, itemid, count, totalcount, received, created;
2498 
2499  p >> received; // 4 0=looted, 1=from npc
2500  p >> created; // 4 0=received, 1=created
2501  p.read_skip<uint32>(); // 4 IsShowChatMessage
2502  p >> bagslot; // 1 bagslot
2503  p >> itemslot; // 4 item slot, but when added to stack: 0xFFFFFFFF
2504  p >> itemid; // 4 item entry id
2505  p.read_skip<uint32>(); // 4 SuffixFactor
2506  p.read_skip<uint32>(); // 4 random item property id
2507  p >> count; // 4 count of items
2508  p >> totalcount; // 4 count of items in inventory
2509 
2510  ItemPrototype const* pProto = ObjectMgr::GetItemPrototype(itemid);
2511  if (pProto)
2512  {
2513  std::ostringstream out;
2514  if (received == 1)
2515  {
2516  if (created == 1)
2517  out << "|cff009900" << "I created: |r";
2518  else
2519  out << "|cff009900" << "I received: |r";
2520  MakeItemLink(pProto, out);
2521  TellMaster(out.str().c_str());
2522  SetState(BOTSTATE_DELAYED);
2523  }
2524  }
2525 
2526  if (IsInQuestItemList(itemid))
2527  {
2528  m_needItemList[itemid] = (m_needItemList[itemid] - count);
2529  if (m_needItemList[itemid] <= 0)
2530  m_needItemList.erase(itemid);
2531  }
2532 
2533  return;
2534  }
2535 
2536  case MSG_MOVE_TELEPORT_ACK:
2537  {
2538  WorldPacket rp(packet);
2539  ObjectGuid guid;
2540  rp >> guid.ReadAsPacked();
2541 
2542  if (guid != m_bot->GetObjectGuid())
2543  return;
2544 
2545  uint32 counter;
2546  rp >> counter;
2547  // movement location to teleport to
2548  MovementInfo mi;
2549  rp >> mi;
2550 
2551  if (m_debugWhisper)
2552  TellMaster("Preparing to teleport");
2553 
2554  if (m_bot->IsBeingTeleportedNear())
2555  {
2556  // simulate same packets that are sent for client
2557  WorldPacket* const p = new WorldPacket(MSG_MOVE_TELEPORT_ACK, 8 + 4 + 4);
2558  p->appendPackGUID(m_bot->GetObjectGuid());
2559  *p << counter;
2560  *p << (uint32) time(0); // time - not currently used
2561  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket>(p));
2562 
2563  // send movement info using received movement packet, pops in location
2564  WorldPacket* const p2 = new WorldPacket(MSG_MOVE_HEARTBEAT, 64);
2565  p2->appendPackGUID(m_bot->GetObjectGuid());
2566  *p2 << mi;
2567  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket>(p2));
2568 
2569  WorldPacket* const p3 = new WorldPacket(MSG_MOVE_FALL_LAND, 64);
2570  p3->appendPackGUID(m_bot->GetObjectGuid());
2571  *p3 << mi;
2572  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket>(p3));
2573 
2574  // resume normal state if was loading
2575  if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_LOADING)
2576  SetState(BOTSTATE_NORMAL);
2577  }
2578  return;
2579  }
2580  case SMSG_TRANSFER_PENDING:
2581  {
2582  if (m_debugWhisper)
2583  TellMaster("World transfer is pending");
2584  SetState(BOTSTATE_LOADING);
2585  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(1);
2586  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(true);
2587  return;
2588  }
2589  case SMSG_NEW_WORLD:
2590  {
2591  if (m_debugWhisper)
2592  TellMaster("Preparing to teleport far");
2593 
2594  if (m_bot->IsBeingTeleportedFar())
2595  {
2596  // simulate client canceling trade before worldport
2597  WorldPacket* const pt1 = new WorldPacket(CMSG_CANCEL_TRADE);
2598  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket>(pt1));
2599 
2600  WorldPacket* const p = new WorldPacket(MSG_MOVE_WORLDPORT_ACK);
2601  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket>(p));
2602  SetState(BOTSTATE_NORMAL);
2603  }
2604  return;
2605  }
2606 
2607  /* uncomment this and your bots will tell you all their outgoing packet opcode names
2608  case SMSG_MONSTER_MOVE:
2609  case SMSG_UPDATE_WORLD_STATE:
2610  case SMSG_COMPRESSED_UPDATE_OBJECT:
2611  case MSG_MOVE_SET_FACING:
2612  case MSG_MOVE_STOP:
2613  case MSG_MOVE_HEARTBEAT:
2614  case MSG_MOVE_STOP_STRAFE:
2615  case MSG_MOVE_START_STRAFE_LEFT:
2616  case SMSG_UPDATE_OBJECT:
2617  case MSG_MOVE_START_FORWARD:
2618  case MSG_MOVE_START_STRAFE_RIGHT:
2619  case SMSG_DESTROY_OBJECT:
2620  case MSG_MOVE_START_BACKWARD:
2621  case SMSG_AURA_UPDATE_ALL:
2622  case MSG_MOVE_FALL_LAND:
2623  case MSG_MOVE_JUMP:
2624  return;*/
2625 
2626  default:
2627  {
2628  /*const char* oc = LookupOpcodeName(packet.GetOpcode());
2629 
2630  std::ostringstream out;
2631  out << "botout: " << oc;
2632  sLog.outError(out.str().c_str());
2633 
2634  TellMaster(oc);*/
2635  }
2636  }
2637 }

2689 bool PlayerbotAI::HasAura(uint32 spellId, const Unit& player) const
2690 {
2691  if (spellId <= 0)
2692  return false;
2693 
2694  for (Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap::const_iterator iter = player.GetSpellAuraHolderMap().begin(); iter != player.GetSpellAuraHolderMap().end(); ++iter)
2695  {
2696  if (iter->second->GetId() == spellId)
2697  return true;
2698  }
2699  return false;
2700 }

2713 // looks through all items / spells that bot could have to get a mount
2714 Item* PlayerbotAI::FindMount(uint32 matchingRidingSkill) const
2715 {
2716  // list out items in main backpack
2717 
2718  Item* partialMatch = nullptr;
2719 
2720  for (uint8 slot = INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START; slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; slot++)
2721  {
2722  Item* const pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slot);
2723  if (pItem)
2724  {
2725  const ItemPrototype* const pItemProto = pItem->GetProto();
2726  if (!pItemProto || m_bot->CanUseItem(pItemProto) != EQUIP_ERR_OK || pItemProto->RequiredSkill != SKILL_RIDING)
2727  continue;
2728 
2729  // Ignore items that can not be used in the current situation (have requirements)
2730  uint32 spellId = 0;
2731  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS; ++i)
2732  {
2733  if (pItemProto->Spells[i].SpellId > 0)
2734  {
2735  spellId = pItemProto->Spells[i].SpellId;
2736  break;
2737  }
2738  }
2739  const SpellEntry* const spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
2740  if (spellInfo)
2741  {
2742  if (Spell(m_bot, spellInfo, false).CheckCast(false) != SPELL_CAST_OK)
2743  continue;
2744  }
2745 
2746  if (pItemProto->RequiredSkillRank == matchingRidingSkill)
2747  return pItem;
2748 
2749  else if (!partialMatch || (partialMatch && partialMatch->GetProto()->RequiredSkillRank < pItemProto->RequiredSkillRank))
2750  partialMatch = pItem;
2751  }
2752  }
2753 
2754  // list out items in other removable backpacks
2755  for (uint8 bag = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; bag < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++bag)
2756  {
2757  const Bag* const pBag = (Bag*) m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, bag);
2758  if (pBag)
2759  for (uint8 slot = 0; slot < pBag->GetBagSize(); ++slot)
2760  {
2761  Item* const pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(bag, slot);
2762  if (pItem)
2763  {
2764  const ItemPrototype* const pItemProto = pItem->GetProto();
2765  if (!pItemProto || m_bot->CanUseItem(pItemProto) != EQUIP_ERR_OK || pItemProto->RequiredSkill != SKILL_RIDING)
2766  continue;
2767 
2768  // Ignore items that can not be used in the current situation (have requirements)
2769  uint32 spellId = 0;
2770  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS; ++i)
2771  {
2772  if (pItemProto->Spells[i].SpellId > 0)
2773  {
2774  spellId = pItemProto->Spells[i].SpellId;
2775  break;
2776  }
2777  }
2778  const SpellEntry* const spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
2779  if (spellInfo)
2780  {
2781  if (Spell(m_bot, spellInfo, false).CheckCast(false) != SPELL_CAST_OK)
2782  continue;
2783  }
2784 
2785  if (pItemProto->RequiredSkillRank == matchingRidingSkill)
2786  return pItem;
2787 
2788  else if (!partialMatch || (partialMatch && partialMatch->GetProto()->RequiredSkillRank < pItemProto->RequiredSkillRank))
2789  partialMatch = pItem;
2790  }
2791  }
2792  }
2793  return partialMatch;
2794 }

3032 Item* PlayerbotAI::FindManaRegenItem() const
3033 {
3034  Item* manaRegen;
3035  // If bot has enough health, try to use a Demonic or Dark Rune
3036  // to avoid triggering the health potion cooldown with a mana potion
3037  if (m_bot->GetHealth() > 1500)
3038  {
3039  // First try a Demonic Rune as they are BoP
3040  manaRegen = FindConsumable(DEMONIC_RUNE);
3041  if (manaRegen)
3042  return manaRegen;
3043  else
3044  {
3045  manaRegen = FindConsumable(DARK_RUNE);
3046  if (manaRegen)
3047  return manaRegen;
3048  }
3049  }
3050  // Else use mana potion (and knowingly trigger the health potion cooldown)
3051  for (uint8 i = 0; i < countof(uPriorizedManaPotionIds); ++i)
3052  {
3053  manaRegen = FindConsumable(uPriorizedManaPotionIds[i]);
3054  if (manaRegen)
3055  return manaRegen;
3056  }
3057 
3058  return nullptr;
3059 }

3061 bool PlayerbotAI::FindAmmo() const
3062 {
3063  for (int i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++i)
3064  {
3065  Item* pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
3066  if (pItem)
3067  {
3068  const ItemPrototype* const pItemProto = pItem->GetProto();
3069 
3070  if (pItemProto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_PROJECTILE && m_bot->CheckAmmoCompatibility(pItemProto))
3071  {
3072  m_bot->SetAmmo(pItem->GetEntry());
3073  return true;
3074  }
3075  }
3076  }
3077  for (int i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
3078  {
3079  if (Bag* pBag = (Bag*)m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
3080  {
3081  for (uint32 j = 0; j < pBag->GetBagSize(); ++j)
3082  {
3083  Item* pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(i, j);
3084  if (pItem)
3085  {
3086  const ItemPrototype* const pItemProto = pItem->GetProto();
3087 
3088  if (pItemProto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_PROJECTILE && m_bot->CheckAmmoCompatibility(pItemProto))
3089  {
3090  m_bot->SetAmmo(pItem->GetEntry());
3091  return true;
3092  }
3093  }
3094  }
3095  }
3096  }
3097  return false;
3098 }

3112 void PlayerbotAI::Attack(Unit* forcedTarget)
3113 {
3114  // set combat state, and clear looting, etc...
3115  if (m_botState != BOTSTATE_COMBAT)
3116  {
3117  SetState(BOTSTATE_COMBAT);
3118  // m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid(); This was clearing loot target, causing bots to leave corpses unlooted if interupted by combat. Needs testing.
3119  // using this caused bot to remove current loot target, and add this new threat to the loot list. Now it remembers the loot target and adds a new one.
3120  // Bot will still clear the target if the master gets too far away from it.
3121  m_targetCombat = nullptr;
3122  m_DelayAttackInit = CurrentTime(); // Combat started, new start time to check CombatDelay for.
3123  }
3124 
3125  GetCombatTarget(forcedTarget);
3126 
3127  if (!m_targetCombat)
3128  return;
3129 
3130  m_bot->Attack(m_targetCombat, true);
3131 
3132  // add thingToAttack to loot list to loot after combat
3133  if (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_COMBAT))
3134  m_lootTargets.push_back(m_targetCombat->GetObjectGuid());
3135 }
