3137 // intelligently sets a reasonable combat order for this bot
3138 // based on its class / level / etc
3139 // Function will try to avoid returning crowd controlled (neutralised) unit
3140 // unless told so by using forcedTarget parameter
3141 void PlayerbotAI::GetCombatTarget(Unit* forcedTarget)
3142 {
3143  // update attacker info now
3144  UpdateAttackerInfo();
3145 
3146  Unit* candidateTarget;
3147 
3148  // check for attackers on protected unit, and make it a forcedTarget if any
3149  if (!forcedTarget && (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_PROTECT) && m_targetProtect)
3150  {
3151  candidateTarget = FindAttacker((ATTACKERINFOTYPE)(AIT_VICTIMNOTSELF | AIT_HIGHESTTHREAT), m_targetProtect);
3152  if (candidateTarget && candidateTarget != m_targetCombat && !IsNeutralized(candidateTarget))
3153  {
3154  forcedTarget = candidateTarget;
3155  m_targetType = TARGET_THREATEN;
3156  if (m_mgr.m_confDebugWhisper)
3157  TellMaster("Changing target to %s to protect %s", forcedTarget->GetName(), m_targetProtect->GetName());
3158  }
3159  }
3160 
3161  // are we forced on a target?
3162  if (forcedTarget)
3163  {
3164  // forced to change target to current target == null operation
3165  if (forcedTarget && forcedTarget == m_targetCombat)
3166  return;
3167 
3168  if (m_mgr.m_confDebugWhisper)
3169  TellMaster("Changing target to %s by force!", forcedTarget->GetName());
3170  m_targetCombat = forcedTarget;
3171  m_ignoreNeutralizeEffect = true; // Bypass IsNeutralized() checks on next updates
3172  m_targetChanged = true;
3173  m_targetType = (m_combatOrder & (ORDERS_TANK | ORDERS_MAIN_TANK) ? TARGET_THREATEN : TARGET_NORMAL);
3174  }
3175 
3176  // we already have a target and we are not forced to change it
3177  if (m_targetCombat)
3178  {
3179  // We have a target but it is neutralised and we are not forced to attack it: clear it for now
3180  if ((IsNeutralized(m_targetCombat) && !m_ignoreNeutralizeEffect))
3181  {
3182  m_targetCombat = nullptr;
3183  m_targetType = TARGET_NORMAL;
3184  m_targetChanged = true;
3185  return;
3186  }
3187  else
3188  {
3189  if (!IsNeutralized(m_targetCombat) && m_ignoreNeutralizeEffect)
3190  m_ignoreNeutralizeEffect = false; // target is no longer neutralised, clear ignore order
3191  return; // keep on attacking target
3192  }
3193  }
3194 
3195  // No target for now, try to get one
3196  // do we have to assist someone?
3197  if (!m_targetCombat && (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_ASSIST) && m_targetAssist)
3198  {
3199  candidateTarget = FindAttacker((ATTACKERINFOTYPE)(AIT_VICTIMNOTSELF | AIT_LOWESTTHREAT), m_targetAssist);
3200  if (candidateTarget && !IsNeutralized(candidateTarget))
3201  {
3202  m_targetCombat = candidateTarget;
3203  if (m_mgr.m_confDebugWhisper)
3204  TellMaster("Attacking %s to assist %s", m_targetCombat->GetName(), m_targetAssist->GetName());
3205  m_targetType = (m_combatOrder & (ORDERS_TANK | ORDERS_MAIN_TANK) ? TARGET_THREATEN : TARGET_NORMAL);
3206  m_targetChanged = true;
3207  }
3208  }
3209  // are there any other attackers?
3210  if (!m_targetCombat)
3211  {
3212  candidateTarget = FindAttacker();
3213  if (candidateTarget && !IsNeutralized(candidateTarget))
3214  {
3215  m_targetCombat = candidateTarget;
3216  m_targetType = (m_combatOrder & (ORDERS_TANK | ORDERS_MAIN_TANK) ? TARGET_THREATEN : TARGET_NORMAL);
3217  m_targetChanged = true;
3218  }
3219  }
3220  // no attacker found anyway
3221  if (!m_targetCombat)
3222  {
3223  m_targetType = TARGET_NORMAL;
3224  m_targetChanged = false;
3225  return;
3226  }
3227 
3228  // if thing to attack is in a duel, then ignore and don't call updateAI for 6 seconds
3229  // this method never gets called when the bot is in a duel and this code
3230  // prevents bot from helping
3231  if (m_targetCombat->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && dynamic_cast<Player*>(m_targetCombat)->duel)
3232  {
3233  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(6);
3234  return;
3235  }
3236 
3237  m_bot->SetSelectionGuid((m_targetCombat->GetObjectGuid()));
3238  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(1);
3239 
3240  if (m_bot->getStandState() != UNIT_STAND_STATE_STAND)
3241  m_bot->SetStandState(UNIT_STAND_STATE_STAND);
3242 }

3258 void PlayerbotAI::DoNextCombatManeuver()
3259 {
3260  if (!GetClassAI())
3261  return; // error, error...
3262 
3263  if (m_combatOrder == ORDERS_PASSIVE)
3264  return;
3265 
3266  // check for new targets
3267  if (m_ScenarioType == SCENARIO_PVP_DUEL)
3268  GetDuelTarget(GetMaster()); // TODO: Woah... wait... what? So not right.
3269  else
3270  Attack();
3271 
3272  // clear orders if current target for attacks doesn't make sense anymore
3273  if (!m_targetCombat || m_targetCombat->IsDead() || !m_targetCombat->IsInWorld() || !m_bot->CanAttack(m_targetCombat) || !m_bot->IsInMap(m_targetCombat))
3274  {
3275  m_bot->AttackStop();
3276  m_bot->SetSelectionGuid(ObjectGuid());
3277  MovementReset();
3278  m_bot->InterruptNonMeleeSpells(true);
3279  m_targetCombat = nullptr;
3280  m_targetChanged = false;
3281  m_targetType = TARGET_NORMAL;
3282  SetQuestNeedCreatures();
3283  if (GetCombatOrder() & ORDERS_TEMP)
3284  {
3285  if (GetCombatOrder() & ORDERS_TEMP_WAIT_TANKAGGRO)
3286  TellMaster("I was still waiting for the tank to gain aggro, but that doesn't make sense anymore...");
3287  if (GetCombatOrder() & ORDERS_TEMP_WAIT_OOC)
3288  TellMaster("I was still waiting OOC but that was way off...");
3289  ClearCombatOrder(ORDERS_TEMP);
3290  }
3291  return;
3292  }
3293 
3294  // new target -> DoFirstCombatManeuver
3295  if (m_targetChanged)
3296  {
3297  switch (GetClassAI()->DoFirstCombatManeuver(m_targetCombat))
3298  {
3299  case RETURN_CONTINUE: // true needed for rogue stealth attack
3300  break;
3301 
3302  case RETURN_NO_ACTION_ERROR:
3303  TellMaster("FirstCombatManeuver: No action performed due to error. Heading onto NextCombatManeuver.");
3304  case RETURN_FINISHED_FIRST_MOVES: // false default
3305  case RETURN_NO_ACTION_UNKNOWN:
3306  case RETURN_NO_ACTION_OK:
3307  default: // assume no action -> no return
3308  m_targetChanged = false;
3309  }
3310  }
3311 
3312  // do normal combat movement
3313  DoCombatMovement();
3314 
3315  if (!m_targetChanged)
3316  {
3317  // if m_targetChanged = false
3318  switch (GetClassAI()->DoNextCombatManeuver(m_targetCombat))
3319  {
3320  case RETURN_NO_ACTION_UNKNOWN:
3321  case RETURN_NO_ACTION_OK:
3322  case RETURN_CONTINUE:
3323  case RETURN_NO_ACTION_ERROR:
3324  default:
3325  return;
3326  }
3327  }
3328 }

3330 void PlayerbotAI::DoCombatMovement()
3331 {
3332  if (!m_targetCombat) return;
3333 
3334  bool meleeReach = m_bot->CanReachWithMeleeAttack(m_targetCombat);
3335 
3336  if (m_combatStyle == COMBAT_MELEE
3337  && !m_bot->hasUnitState(UNIT_STAT_CHASE)
3338  && ((m_movementOrder == MOVEMENT_STAY && meleeReach) || m_movementOrder != MOVEMENT_STAY)
3339  && GetClassAI()->GetWaitUntil() == 0) // Not waiting
3340  {
3341  // melee combat - chase target if in range or if we are not forced to stay
3342  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(false);
3343  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveChase(m_targetCombat);
3344  }
3345  else if (m_combatStyle == COMBAT_RANGED
3346  && m_movementOrder != MOVEMENT_STAY
3347  && GetClassAI()->GetWaitUntil() == 0) // Not waiting
3348  {
3349  // ranged combat - just move within spell range if bot does not have heal orders
3350  if (!CanReachWithSpellAttack(m_targetCombat) && !IsHealer())
3351  {
3352  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(false);
3353  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveChase(m_targetCombat);
3354  }
3355  else
3356  MovementClear();
3357  }
3358 }

3360 /*
3361  * IsGroupReady()
3362  *
3363  * return false if any member of the group is in combat or (error handling only) occupied in some way
3364  * return true otherwise
3365  */
3366 bool PlayerbotAI::IsGroupReady()
3367 {
3368  if (!m_bot) return true;
3369  if (!m_bot->IsAlive() || m_bot->IsInDuel()) return false; // Let's just say you're otherwise occupied
3370  if (m_bot->IsInCombat()) return false;
3371 
3372  if (m_bot->GetGroup())
3373  {
3374  Group::MemberSlotList const& groupSlot = m_bot->GetGroup()->GetMemberSlots();
3375  for (Group::member_citerator itr = groupSlot.begin(); itr != groupSlot.end(); itr++)
3376  {
3377  Player* groupMember = sObjectMgr.GetPlayer(itr->guid);
3378  if (groupMember && groupMember->IsAlive())
3379  {
3380  if (groupMember->IsInDuel() || groupMember->IsInCombat()) // all occupied in some way
3381  return false;
3382  }
3383  }
3384  }
3385 
3386  return true;
3387 }

3398  {
3399  Player* groupMember = sObjectMgr.GetPlayer(itr->guid);
3400  if (!groupMember || !groupMember->GetPlayerbotAI())
3401  continue;
3402  if (groupMember->GetPlayerbotAI()->IsMainTank())
3403  return groupMember;
3404  }
3405  // Second loop: we look for any tank (bots with JOB_TANK or human players with the right class/spec combination)
3406  for (Group::member_citerator itr = groupSlot.begin(); itr != groupSlot.end(); itr++)
3407  {
3408  Player* groupMember = sObjectMgr.GetPlayer(itr->guid);
3409  if (groupMember)
3410  {
3411  if (!groupMember->GetPlayerbotAI() && m_bot->GetPlayerbotAI()->GetClassAI()->GetTargetJob(groupMember) & JOB_TANK)
3412  return groupMember;
3413  else if (groupMember->GetPlayerbotAI() && groupMember->GetPlayerbotAI()->IsTank())
3414  return groupMember;
3415  }
3416  }
3417  }
3418 
3419  return nullptr;
3420 }

3623 // Wrapper for the UpdateAI cast subfunction
3624 // Each bot class neutralize function will return a spellId
3625 // depending on the creatureType of the target
3626 bool PlayerbotAI::CastNeutralize()
3627 {
3628  if (!m_bot) return false;
3629  if (!GetClassAI()) return false;
3630  if (!m_targetGuidCommand) return false;
3631 
3632  Unit* target = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_bot, m_targetGuidCommand);
3633  if (!target) return false;
3634 
3635  uint8 creatureType = 0;
3636  if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
3637  {
3638  // Define the target's creature type, so the bot AI will now if
3639  // it can neutralize it
3640  auto* creature = (Creature*) target;
3641  creatureType = creature->GetCreatureInfo()->CreatureType;
3642  }
3643  else // Target is a player
3644  {
3645  // Shapeshifted druids are considered as beasts
3646  if (target->getClass() == CLASS_DRUID && target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT))
3647  creatureType = CREATURE_TYPE_BEAST;
3648  // Else, players are humanoids
3649  else
3650  creatureType = CREATURE_TYPE_HUMANOID;
3651  }
3652 
3653  m_spellIdCommand = ((PlayerbotClassAI*)GetClassAI())->Neutralize(creatureType);
3654 
3655  // A spellId was found
3656  return m_spellIdCommand != 0;
3657 }

3659 void PlayerbotAI::SetQuestNeedCreatures()
3660 {
3661  // reset values first
3662  m_needCreatureOrGOList.clear();
3663 
3664  // run through accepted quests, get quest info and data
3665  for (int qs = 0; qs < MAX_QUEST_LOG_SIZE; ++qs)
3666  {
3667  uint32 questid = m_bot->GetQuestSlotQuestId(qs);
3668  if (questid == 0)
3669  continue;
3670 
3671  QuestStatusData& qData = m_bot->getQuestStatusMap()[questid];
3672  // only check quest if it is incomplete
3673  if (qData.m_status != QUEST_STATUS_INCOMPLETE)
3674  continue;
3675 
3676  Quest const* qInfo = sObjectMgr.GetQuestTemplate(questid);
3677  if (!qInfo)
3678  continue;
3679 
3680  // All creature/GO slain/casted (not required, but otherwise it will display "Creature slain 0/10")
3681  for (int i = 0; i < QUEST_OBJECTIVES_COUNT; i++)
3682  {
3683  if (!qInfo->ReqCreatureOrGOCount[i] || (qInfo->ReqCreatureOrGOCount[i] - qData.m_creatureOrGOcount[i]) <= 0)
3684  continue;
3685  m_needCreatureOrGOList[qInfo->ReqCreatureOrGOId[i]] = (qInfo->ReqCreatureOrGOCount[i] - qData.m_creatureOrGOcount[i]);
3686  }
3687  }
3688 }
3689 
3690 void PlayerbotAI::SetQuestNeedItems()
3691 {
3692  // reset values first
3693  m_needItemList.clear();
3694 
3695  // run through accepted quests, get quest info and data
3696  for (int qs = 0; qs < MAX_QUEST_LOG_SIZE; ++qs)
3697  {
3698  uint32 questid = m_bot->GetQuestSlotQuestId(qs);
3699  if (questid == 0)
3700  continue;
3701 
3702  QuestStatusData& qData = m_bot->getQuestStatusMap()[questid];
3703  // only check quest if it is incomplete
3704  if (qData.m_status != QUEST_STATUS_INCOMPLETE)
3705  continue;
3706 
3707  Quest const* qInfo = sObjectMgr.GetQuestTemplate(questid);
3708  if (!qInfo)
3709  continue;
3710 
3711  // check for items we not have enough of
3712  for (int i = 0; i < QUEST_ITEM_OBJECTIVES_COUNT; i++)
3713  {
3714  if (!qInfo->ReqItemCount[i] || (qInfo->ReqItemCount[i] - qData.m_itemcount[i]) <= 0)
3715  continue;
3716  m_needItemList[qInfo->ReqItemId[i]] = (qInfo->ReqItemCount[i] - qData.m_itemcount[i]);
3717 
3718  // collect flags not set to gather quest objects skip remaining section
3719  if (!HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_NEAROBJECT) && !HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_QUEST))
3720  continue;
3721 
3722  // TODO: find faster way to handle this look up instead of using SQL lookup for each item
3723  QueryResult* result;
3724  // determine if GOs are needed
3725  result = WorldDatabase.PQuery("SELECT entry FROM gameobject_template WHERE questitem1='%u' "
3726  "OR questitem2='%u' OR questitem3='%u' OR questitem4='%u' OR questitem5='%u' OR questitem6='%u'",
3727  qInfo->ReqItemId[i], qInfo->ReqItemId[i], qInfo->ReqItemId[i], qInfo->ReqItemId[i],
3728  qInfo->ReqItemId[i], qInfo->ReqItemId[i]);
3729 
3730  if (result)
3731  {
3732  do
3733  {
3734  Field* fields = result->Fetch();
3735  uint32 entry = fields[0].GetUInt32();
3736 
3737  GameObjectInfo const* gInfo = ObjectMgr::GetGameObjectInfo(entry);
3738  if (!gInfo)
3739  continue;
3740 
3741  // add this GO to our collection list if is chest/ore/herb
3742  if (gInfo->type == GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_CHEST)
3743  {
3744  m_collectObjects.push_back(entry);
3745  m_collectObjects.sort();
3746  m_collectObjects.unique();
3747  }
3748  }
3749  while (result->NextRow());
3750 
3751  delete result;
3752  }
3753  }
3754  }
3755 }

3763 uint32 PlayerbotAI::GetFreeBagSpace() const
3764 {
3765  uint32 totalused = 0;
3766  // list out items in main backpack
3767  for (uint8 slot = INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START; slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; slot++)
3768  {
3769  const Item* const pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slot);
3770  if (pItem)
3771  totalused++;
3772  }
3773  uint32 totalfree = 16 - totalused;
3774  // list out items in other removable backpacks
3775  for (uint8 bag = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; bag < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++bag)
3776  {
3777  const Bag* const pBag = (Bag*) m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, bag);
3778  if (pBag)
3779  {
3780  ItemPrototype const* pBagProto = pBag->GetProto();
3781  if (pBagProto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_CONTAINER && pBagProto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_CONTAINER)
3782  totalfree = totalfree + pBag->GetFreeSlots();
3783  }
3784  }
3785  return totalfree;
3786 }

3802 void PlayerbotAI::DoLoot()
3803 {
3804  // clear BOTSTATE_LOOTING if no more loot targets
3805  if (m_lootCurrent.IsEmpty() && m_lootTargets.empty())
3806  {
3807  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]: DoLoot - %s is going back to idle", m_bot->GetName());
3808  SetState(BOTSTATE_NORMAL);
3809  m_bot->RemoveFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_LOOTING);
3810  m_inventory_full = false;
3811  AutoUpgradeEquipment();
3812  return;
3813  }
3814 
3815  // set first in list to current
3816  if (m_lootCurrent.IsEmpty())
3817  {
3818  m_lootCurrent = m_lootTargets.front();
3819  m_lootTargets.pop_front();
3820  }
3821 
3822  WorldObject* wo = m_bot->GetMap()->GetWorldObject(m_lootCurrent);
3823 
3824  // clear invalid object or object that is too far from master
3825  if (!wo || GetMaster()->GetDistance(wo) > float(m_mgr.m_confCollectDistanceMax))
3826  {
3827  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
3828  if (m_debugWhisper)
3829  TellMaster("Object is too far away.");
3830  return;
3831  }
3832 
3833  Creature* c = nullptr;
3834  GameObject* go = nullptr;
3835  if (m_lootCurrent.IsAnyTypeCreature())
3836  c = static_cast<Creature*>(wo);
3837  else if (m_lootCurrent.IsGameObject())
3838  go = static_cast<GameObject*>(wo);
3839 
3840  // clear creature or object that is not spawned or if not creature or object
3841  if ((c && c->IsDespawned()) || (go && !go->IsSpawned()) || (!c && !go))
3842  {
3843  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
3844  if (m_debugWhisper)
3845  TellMaster("Object is not spawned.");
3846  return;
3847  }
3848 
3849  uint32 skillId = 0;
3850 
3851  if (c)
3852  {
3853  if (c->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE))
3854  skillId = c->GetCreatureInfo()->GetRequiredLootSkill();
3855 
3856  // not a lootable creature, clear it
3857  if ((!c->HasFlag(UNIT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS, UNIT_DYNFLAG_LOOTABLE) &&
3858  !c->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE)) ||
3859  (c->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE) && !m_bot->HasSkill(skillId)))
3860  {
3861  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
3862  // clear movement target, take next target on next update
3863  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(false);
3864  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveIdle();
3865  return;
3866  }
3867  else if (c->m_loot && !c->m_loot->CanLoot(m_bot) && !c->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE))
3868  {
3869  if (m_debugWhisper)
3870  TellMaster("%s is not lootable by me.", wo->GetName());
3871  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
3872  // clear movement target, take next target on next update
3873  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(false);
3874  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveIdle();
3875  return;
3876  }
3877  }
3878 
3879  // if target contains item being rolled on, do not loot again.
3880  for (std::list<ObjectGuid>::iterator itr = m_being_rolled_on.begin(); itr != m_being_rolled_on.end(); ++itr)
3881  if (m_lootCurrent == *itr)
3882  {
3883  // DEBUG_LOG("An item is currently being rolled on, ignoring (%s)!",m_lootCurrent.GetString().c_str());
3884  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
3885  return;
3886  }
3887 
3888  if (m_bot->GetDistance(wo) > CONTACT_DISTANCE + wo->GetObjectBoundingRadius())
3889  {
3890  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MovePoint(wo->GetMapId(), wo->GetPositionX(), wo->GetPositionY(), wo->GetPositionZ(), FORCED_MOVEMENT_RUN);
3891  // give time to move to point before trying again
3892  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(1);
3893  if (m_debugWhisper)
3894  TellMaster("Moving to loot %s", go ? go->GetName() : wo->GetName());
3895  }
3896 
3897  if (m_bot->GetDistance(wo) < INTERACTION_DISTANCE)
3898  {
3899  uint32 reqSkillValue = 0;
3900  uint32 SkillValue = 0;
3901  bool keyFailed = false;
3902  bool skillFailed = false;
3903  bool forceFailed = false;
3904 
3905  if (m_debugWhisper)
3906  TellMaster("Beginning to loot %s", go ? go->GetName() : wo->GetName());
3907 
3908  if (c) // creature
3909  {
3910  if (c->HasFlag(UNIT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS, UNIT_DYNFLAG_LOOTABLE) && !c->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE))
3911  {
3912  // loot the creature
3913  std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket> packet(new WorldPacket(CMSG_LOOT, 8));
3914  *packet << m_lootCurrent;
3915  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::move(packet));
3916  return; // no further processing is needed
3917  // m_lootCurrent is reset in SMSG_LOOT_RESPONSE/SMSG_LOOT_RELEASE_RESPONSE
3918  }
3919  else if (c->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE))
3920  // not all creature skins are leather, some are ore or herb
3921  if (m_bot->HasSkill(skillId) && ((skillId != SKILL_SKINNING) ||
3922  (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_SKIN) && skillId == SKILL_SKINNING)))
3923  {
3924  // calculate skinning skill requirement
3925  uint32 targetLevel = c->GetLevel();
3926  reqSkillValue = targetLevel < 10 ? 0 : targetLevel < 20 ? (targetLevel - 10) * 10 : targetLevel * 5;
3927  }
3928 
3929  // creatures cannot be unlocked or forced open
3930  keyFailed = true;
3931  forceFailed = true;
3932  }
3933 
3934  if (go) // object
3935  {
3936  // add this GO to our collection list if active and is chest/ore/herb
3937  if (go && HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_NEAROBJECT) && go->GetGoType() == GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_CHEST)
3938  {
3939  m_collectObjects.push_back(go->GetEntry());
3940  m_collectObjects.sort();
3941  m_collectObjects.unique();
3942  }
3943 
3944  uint32 reqItem = 0;
3945 
3946  // check skill or lock on object
3947  uint32 lockId = go->GetGOInfo()->GetLockId();
3948  LockEntry const* lockInfo = sLockStore.LookupEntry(lockId);
3949  if (lockInfo)
3950  for (int i = 0; i < 8; ++i)
3951  {
3952  if (lockInfo->Type[i] == LOCK_KEY_ITEM)
3953  {
3954  if (lockInfo->Index[i] > 0)
3955  {
3956  reqItem = lockInfo->Index[i];
3957  if (m_bot->HasItemCount(reqItem, 1))
3958  break;
3959  continue;
3960  }
3961  }
3962  else if (lockInfo->Type[i] == LOCK_KEY_SKILL)
3963  {
3964  switch (LockType(lockInfo->Index[i]))
3965  {
3966  case LOCKTYPE_OPEN:
3967  if (CastSpell(3365) == SPELL_CAST_OK) // Opening
3968  return;
3969  break;
3970  case LOCKTYPE_CLOSE:
3971  if (CastSpell(6233) == SPELL_CAST_OK) // Closing
3972  return;
3973  break;
3974  case LOCKTYPE_QUICK_OPEN:
3975  if (CastSpell(6247) == SPELL_CAST_OK) // Opening
3976  return;
3977  break;
3978  case LOCKTYPE_QUICK_CLOSE:
3979  if (CastSpell(6247) == SPELL_CAST_OK) // Closing
3980  return;
3981  break;
3982  case LOCKTYPE_OPEN_TINKERING:
3983  if (CastSpell(6477) == SPELL_CAST_OK) // Opening
3984  return;
3985  break;
3986  case LOCKTYPE_OPEN_KNEELING:
3987  if (CastSpell(6478) == SPELL_CAST_OK) // Opening; listed with 17667 and 22810
3988  return;
3989  break;
3990  case LOCKTYPE_OPEN_ATTACKING:
3991  if (CastSpell(8386) == SPELL_CAST_OK) // Attacking
3992  return;
3993  break;
3994  case LOCKTYPE_SLOW_OPEN:
3995  if (CastSpell(21651) == SPELL_CAST_OK) // Opening; also had 26868
3996  return;
3997  break;
3998  case LOCKTYPE_SLOW_CLOSE:
3999  if (CastSpell(21652) == SPELL_CAST_OK) // Closing
4000  return;
4001  break;
4002  case LOCKTYPE_OPEN_FROM_VEHICLE:
4003  if (CastSpell(61437) == SPELL_CAST_OK) // Opening
4004  return;
4005  break;
4006  default:
4007  if (SkillByLockType(LockType(lockInfo->Index[i])) > 0)
4008  {
4009  skillId = SkillByLockType(LockType(lockInfo->Index[i]));
4010  reqSkillValue = lockInfo->Skill[i];
4011  }
4012  }
4013  }
4014  }
4015 
4016  // use key on object if available
4017  if (reqItem > 0 && m_bot->HasItemCount(reqItem, 1))
4018  {
4019  UseItem(m_bot->GetItemByEntry(reqItem), TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT, m_lootCurrent);
4020  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
4021  return;
4022  }
4023  else
4024  keyFailed = true;
4025  }
4026 
4027  // determine bot's skill value for object's required skill
4028  if (skillId != SKILL_NONE)
4029  SkillValue = uint32(m_bot->GetSkillValue(skillId));
4030 
4031  // bot has the specific skill or object requires no skill at all
4032  if ((m_bot->HasSkill(skillId) && skillId != SKILL_NONE) || (skillId == SKILL_NONE && go))
4033  {
4034  if (SkillValue < reqSkillValue)
4035  {
4036  TellMaster("My skill is not high enough. It requires %u, but mine is %u.",
4037  reqSkillValue, SkillValue);
4038  skillFailed = true;
4039  }
4040  switch (skillId)
4041  {
4042  case SKILL_MINING:
4043  if (HasTool(TC_MINING_PICK) && CastSpell(MINING) == SPELL_CAST_OK)
4044  return;
4045  else
4046  skillFailed = true;
4047  break;
4048  case SKILL_HERBALISM:
4049  if (CastSpell(HERB_GATHERING) == SPELL_CAST_OK)
4050  return;
4051  else
4052  skillFailed = true;
4053  break;
4054  case SKILL_SKINNING:
4055  if (c && HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_SKIN) &&
4056  HasTool(TC_SKINNING_KNIFE) && CastSpell(SKINNING, *c) == SPELL_CAST_OK)
4057  return;
4058  else
4059  skillFailed = true;
4060  break;
4061  case SKILL_LOCKPICKING:
4062  if (CastSpell(PICK_LOCK_1) == SPELL_CAST_OK)
4063  return;
4064  else
4065  skillFailed = true;
4066  break;
4067  case SKILL_NONE:
4068  if (CastSpell(3365) == SPELL_CAST_OK) //Spell 3365 = Opening?
4069  return;
4070  else
4071  skillFailed = true;
4072  break;
4073  default:
4074  TellMaster("I'm not sure how to get that.");
4075  skillFailed = true;
4076  DEBUG_LOG("[PlayerbotAI]:DoLoot Skill %u is not implemented", skillId);
4077  break;
4078  }
4079  }
4080  else
4081  {
4082  TellMaster("I do not have the required skill.");
4083  skillFailed = true;
4084  }
4085 
4086  if (go) // only go's can be forced
4087  {
4088  // if pickable, check if a forcible item is available for the bot
4089  if (skillId == SKILL_LOCKPICKING && (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_BLACKSMITHING) ||
4090  m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ENGINEERING)))
4091  {
4092  // check for skeleton keys appropriate for lock value
4093  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_BLACKSMITHING))
4094  {
4095  Item* kItem = FindKeyForLockValue(reqSkillValue);
4096  if (kItem)
4097  {
4098  TellMaster("I have a skeleton key that can open it!");
4099  UseItem(kItem, TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT, m_lootCurrent);
4100  return;
4101  }
4102  else
4103  {
4104  TellMaster("I have no skeleton keys that can open that lock.");
4105  forceFailed = true;
4106  }
4107  }
4108 
4109  // check for a charge that can blast it open
4110  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ENGINEERING))
4111  {
4112  Item* bItem = FindBombForLockValue(reqSkillValue);
4113  if (bItem)
4114  {
4115  TellMaster("I can blast it open!");
4116  UseItem(bItem, TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT, m_lootCurrent);
4117  return;
4118  }
4119  else
4120  {
4121  TellMaster("I have nothing to blast it open with.");
4122  forceFailed = true;
4123  }
4124  }
4125  }
4126  else
4127  forceFailed = true;
4128  }
4129 
4130  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]%s: keyFailed [%s]", m_bot->GetName(), keyFailed ? "true" : "false");
4131  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]%s: skillFailed [%s]", m_bot->GetName(), skillFailed ? "true" : "false");
4132  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]%s: forceFailed [%s]", m_bot->GetName(), forceFailed ? "true" : "false");
4133 
4134  // if all attempts failed in some way then clear because it won't get SMSG_LOOT_RESPONSE
4135  if (keyFailed && skillFailed && forceFailed)
4136  {
4137  DEBUG_LOG("[PlayerbotAI]: DoLoot attempts failed on [%s]",
4138  go ? go->GetGOInfo()->name : c->GetCreatureInfo()->Name);
4139  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
4140 
4141  // remove this GO from our list using the same settings that it was added with earlier
4142  if (go && HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_NEAROBJECT) && go->GetGoType() == GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_CHEST)
4143  m_collectObjects.remove(go->GetEntry());
4144  }
4145  // clear movement target, take next target on next update
4146  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(false);
4147  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveIdle();
4148  }
4149 }
4150 
4151 void PlayerbotAI::AcceptQuest(Quest const* qInfo, Player* pGiver)
4152 {
4153  if (!qInfo || !pGiver)
4154  return;
4155 
4156  uint32 quest = qInfo->GetQuestId();
4157 
4158  if (!pGiver->CanShareQuest(qInfo->GetQuestId()))
4159  {
4160  // giver can't share quest
4161  m_bot->ClearDividerGuid();
4162  return;
4163  }
4164 
4165  if (!m_bot->CanTakeQuest(qInfo, false))
4166  {
4167  // can't take quest
4168  m_bot->ClearDividerGuid();
4169  return;
4170  }
4171 
4172  if (m_bot->GetDividerGuid())
4173  {
4174  // send msg to quest giving player
4175  pGiver->SendPushToPartyResponse(m_bot, QUEST_PARTY_MSG_ACCEPT_QUEST);
4176  m_bot->ClearDividerGuid();
4177  }
4178 
4179  if (m_bot->CanAddQuest(qInfo, false))
4180  {
4181  m_bot->AddQuest(qInfo, pGiver);
4182 
4183  if (m_bot->CanCompleteQuest(quest))
4184  m_bot->CompleteQuest(quest);
4185 
4186  // build needed items if quest contains any
4187  for (int i = 0; i < QUEST_ITEM_OBJECTIVES_COUNT; i++)
4188  if (qInfo->ReqItemCount[i] > 0)
4189  {
4190  SetQuestNeedItems();
4191  break;
4192  }
4193 
4194  // build needed creatures if quest contains any
4195  for (int i = 0; i < QUEST_OBJECTIVES_COUNT; i++)
4196  if (qInfo->ReqCreatureOrGOCount[i] > 0)
4197  {
4198  SetQuestNeedCreatures();
4199  break;
4200  }
4201 
4202  // Runsttren: did not add typeid switch from WorldSession::HandleQuestgiverAcceptQuestOpcode!
4203  // I think it's not needed, cause typeid should be TYPEID_PLAYER - and this one is not handled
4204  // there and there is no default case also.
4205 
4206  if (qInfo->GetSrcSpell() > 0)
4207  m_bot->CastSpell(m_bot, qInfo->GetSrcSpell(), TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
4208  }
4209 }
4210 
4211 void PlayerbotAI::TurnInQuests(WorldObject* questgiver)
4212 {
4213  ObjectGuid giverGUID = questgiver->GetObjectGuid();
4214 
4215  if (!m_bot->IsInMap(questgiver))
4216  TellMaster("hey you are turning in quests without me!");
4217  else
4218  {
4219  m_bot->SetSelectionGuid(giverGUID);
4220 
4221  // auto complete every completed quest this NPC has
4222  m_bot->PrepareQuestMenu(giverGUID);
4223  QuestMenu& questMenu = m_bot->GetPlayerMenu()->GetQuestMenu();
4224  for (uint32 iI = 0; iI < questMenu.MenuItemCount(); ++iI)
4225  {
4226  QuestMenuItem const& qItem = questMenu.GetItem(iI);
4227  uint32 questID = qItem.m_qId;
4228  Quest const* pQuest = sObjectMgr.GetQuestTemplate(questID);
4229 
4230  std::ostringstream out;
4231 
4232  QuestStatus status = m_bot->GetQuestStatus(questID);
4233 
4234  // if quest is complete, turn it in
4235  if (status == QUEST_STATUS_COMPLETE)
4236  {
4237  // if bot hasn't already turned quest in
4238  if (!m_bot->GetQuestRewardStatus(questID))
4239  {
4240  // auto reward quest if no choice in reward
4241  if (pQuest->GetRewChoiceItemsCount() == 0)
4242  {
4243  if (m_bot->CanRewardQuest(pQuest, false))
4244  {
4245  m_bot->RewardQuest(pQuest, 0, questgiver, false);
4246  out << "Quest complete: ";
4247  }
4248  else
4249  out << "|cffff0000Unable to turn quest in:|r ";
4250  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, out);
4251  }
4252  // auto reward quest if one item as reward
4253  else if (pQuest->GetRewChoiceItemsCount() == 1)
4254  {
4255  int rewardIdx = 0;
4256  ItemPrototype const* pRewardItem = sObjectMgr.GetItemPrototype(pQuest->RewChoiceItemId[rewardIdx]);
4257  if (m_bot->CanRewardQuest(pQuest, rewardIdx, false))
4258  {
4259  m_bot->RewardQuest(pQuest, rewardIdx, questgiver, true);
4260  out << "Quest complete: ";
4261  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, out);
4262  }
4263  else
4264  out << "|cffff0000Unable to turn quest in:|r ";
4265  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, out);
4266  out << " reward: ";
4267  MakeItemLink(pRewardItem, out);
4268  }
4269  // else multiple rewards - let master pick
4270  else
4271  {
4272  out << "What reward should I take for ";
4273  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, out);
4274  for (uint8 i = 0; i < pQuest->GetRewChoiceItemsCount(); ++i)
4275  {
4276  ItemPrototype const* const pRewardItem = sObjectMgr.GetItemPrototype(pQuest->RewChoiceItemId[i]);
4277  MakeItemLink(pRewardItem, out);
4278  }
4279  }
4280  }
4281  }
4282  else if (status == QUEST_STATUS_INCOMPLETE)
4283  {
4284  out << "|cffff0000Quest incomplete:|r ";
4285  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, out);
4286  }
4287  else if (status == QUEST_STATUS_AVAILABLE)
4288  {
4289  out << "|cff00ff00Quest available:|r ";
4290  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, out);
4291  }
4292 
4293  if (!out.str().empty())
4294  TellMaster(out.str());
4295  }
4296  AutoUpgradeEquipment();
4297  }
4298 }

4300 bool PlayerbotAI::IsInCombat()
4301 {
4302  Pet* pet;
4303  bool inCombat = false;
4304  inCombat |= m_bot->IsInCombat();
4305  pet = m_bot->GetPet();
4306  if (pet)
4307  inCombat |= pet->IsInCombat();
4308  inCombat |= GetMaster()->IsInCombat();
4309  if (m_bot->GetGroup())
4310  {
4311  GroupReference* ref = m_bot->GetGroup()->GetFirstMember();
4312  while (ref)
4313  {
4314  inCombat |= ref->getSource()->IsInCombat();
4315  pet = ref->getSource()->GetPet();
4316  if (pet)
4317  inCombat |= pet->IsInCombat();
4318  ref = ref->next();
4319  }
4320  }
4321  return inCombat;
4322 }

4332 bool PlayerbotAI::IsRegenerating()
4333 {
4334  // We check spell category to know if bot is drinking (spell category 59, at least for conjured water)
4335  // or eating (spell category 11, at least for conjured food or season/battle ground items triggering both food and drink auras)
4336  // or we check is spell is castable while sitting and provide health/power regen like food/drink spells do
4337  Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap& auras = m_bot->GetSpellAuraHolderMap();
4338  for (auto & aura : auras)
4339  {
4340  SpellEntry const* spell = aura.second->GetSpellProto();
4341  // Exclude permanent regenerating aura (DurationIndex 21 : unlimited)
4342  if (!spell || spell->DurationIndex == 21)
4343  continue;
4344  // Generic drinking / eating
4345  if (spell->Category == 59 || spell->Category == 11)
4346  return true;
4347  // Specific drinking / eating after patch 2.0.1, especially conjured goods
4348  if(spell->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_ALLOW_WHILE_SITTING))
4349  {
4350  for (uint32 i = EFFECT_INDEX_0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
4351  {
4352  if (spell->Effect[i] == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA && (spell->EffectApplyAuraName[i] == SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN || spell->EffectApplyAuraName[i] == SPELL_AURA_MOD_REGEN))
4353  return true;
4354  }
4355  }
4356  }
4357  if (m_bot->getStandState() != UNIT_STAND_STATE_STAND)
4358  m_bot->SetStandState(UNIT_STAND_STATE_STAND);
4359  return false;
4360 }

4362 void PlayerbotAI::UpdateAttackersForTarget(Unit* victim)
4363 {
4364  HostileReference* ref = victim->getHostileRefManager().getFirst();
4365  while (ref)

4369  m_attackerInfo[guid].attacker = target->getOwner();
4370  m_attackerInfo[guid].victim = target->getOwner()->GetVictim();
4371  m_attackerInfo[guid].threat = target->getThreat(victim);
4372  m_attackerInfo[guid].count = 1;
4373  //m_attackerInfo[guid].source = 1; // source is not used so far.
4374  ref = ref->next();
4375  }
4376 }

4378 void PlayerbotAI::UpdateAttackerInfo()
4379 {
4380  // clear old list
4381  m_attackerInfo.clear();
4382 
4383  // check own attackers
4384  UpdateAttackersForTarget(m_bot);
4385  Pet* pet = m_bot->GetPet();
4386  if (pet)
4387  UpdateAttackersForTarget(pet);
4388 
4389  // check master's attackers
4390  UpdateAttackersForTarget(GetMaster());
4391  pet = GetMaster()->GetPet();
4392  if (pet)
4393  UpdateAttackersForTarget(pet);
4394 
4395  // check all group members now
4396  if (m_bot->GetGroup())
4397  {
4398  GroupReference* gref = m_bot->GetGroup()->GetFirstMember();
4399  while (gref)
4400  {
4401  if (gref->getSource() == m_bot || gref->getSource() == GetMaster())
4402  {
4403  gref = gref->next();
4404  continue;
4405  }
4406 
4407  UpdateAttackersForTarget(gref->getSource());
4408  pet = gref->getSource()->GetPet();
4409  if (pet)
4410  UpdateAttackersForTarget(pet);
4411 
4412  gref = gref->next();
4413  }
4414  }
4415 
4416  // get highest threat not caused by bot for every entry in AttackerInfoList...
4417  for (AttackerInfoList::iterator itr = m_attackerInfo.begin(); itr != m_attackerInfo.end(); ++itr)
4418  {
4419  if (!itr->second.attacker)
4420  continue;
4421  Unit* a = itr->second.attacker;
4422  float t = 0.00;
4423  std::list<HostileReference*>::const_iterator i = a->getThreatManager().getThreatList().begin();
4424  for (; i != a->getThreatManager().getThreatList().end(); ++i)
4425  {
4426  if ((*i)->getThreat() > t && (*i)->getTarget() != m_bot)
4427  t = (*i)->getThreat();
4428  }
4429  m_attackerInfo[itr->first].threat2 = t;
4430  }
4431 
4432  // DEBUG: output attacker info
4433  //sLog.outBasic( "[PlayerbotAI]: %s m_attackerInfo = {", m_bot->GetName() );
4434  //for( AttackerInfoList::iterator i=m_attackerInfo.begin(); i!=m_attackerInfo.end(); ++i )
4435  // sLog.outBasic( "[PlayerbotAI]: [%016I64X] { %08X, %08X, %.2f, %.2f, %d, %d }",
4436  // i->first,
4437  // (i->second.attacker?i->second.attacker->GetGUIDLow():0),
4438  // (i->second.victim?i->second.victim->GetGUIDLow():0),
4439  // i->second.threat,
4440  // i->second.threat2,
4441  // i->second.count,
4442  // i->second.source );
4443  //sLog.outBasic( "[PlayerbotAI]: };" );
4444 }

4446 uint32 PlayerbotAI::EstRepairAll()
4447 {
4448  uint32 TotalCost = 0;
4449  // equipped, backpack, bags itself
4450  for (int i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++i)
4451  TotalCost += EstRepair(((INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 << 8) | i));
4452 
4453  // bank, buyback and keys not repaired
4454 
4455  // items in inventory bags
4456  for (int j = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; j < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++j)
4457  for (int i = 0; i < MAX_BAG_SIZE; ++i)
4458  TotalCost += EstRepair(((j << 8) | i));
4459  return TotalCost;
4460 }
4461 
4462 uint32 PlayerbotAI::EstRepair(uint16 pos)
4463 {
4464  Item* item = m_bot->GetItemByPos(pos);
4465 
4466  uint32 TotalCost = 0;
4467  if (!item)
4468  return TotalCost;
4469 
4470  uint32 maxDurability = item->GetUInt32Value(ITEM_FIELD_MAXDURABILITY);
4471  if (!maxDurability)
4472  return TotalCost;
4473 
4474  uint32 curDurability = item->GetUInt32Value(ITEM_FIELD_DURABILITY);
4475 
4476  uint32 LostDurability = maxDurability - curDurability;
4477  if (LostDurability > 0)
4478  {
4479  ItemPrototype const* ditemProto = item->GetProto();
4480 
4481  DurabilityCostsEntry const* dcost = sDurabilityCostsStore.LookupEntry(ditemProto->ItemLevel);
4482  if (!dcost)
4483  {
4484  sLog.outError("RepairDurability: Wrong item lvl %u", ditemProto->ItemLevel);
4485  return TotalCost;
4486  }
4487 
4488  uint32 dQualitymodEntryId = (ditemProto->Quality + 1) * 2;
4489  DurabilityQualityEntry const* dQualitymodEntry = sDurabilityQualityStore.LookupEntry(dQualitymodEntryId);
4490  if (!dQualitymodEntry)
4491  {
4492  sLog.outError("RepairDurability: Wrong dQualityModEntry %u", dQualitymodEntryId);
4493  return TotalCost;
4494  }
4495 
4496  uint32 dmultiplier = dcost->multiplier[ItemSubClassToDurabilityMultiplierId(ditemProto->Class, ditemProto->SubClass)];
4497  uint32 costs = uint32(LostDurability * dmultiplier * double(dQualitymodEntry->quality_mod));
4498 
4499  if (costs == 0) //fix for ITEM_QUALITY_ARTIFACT
4500  costs = 1;
4501 
4502  TotalCost = costs;
4503  }
4504  return TotalCost;
4505 }
4506 
4507 Unit* PlayerbotAI::FindAttacker(ATTACKERINFOTYPE ait, Unit* victim)
4508 {
4509  // list empty? why are we here?
4510  if (m_attackerInfo.empty())
4511  return nullptr;
4512 
4513  // not searching something specific - return first in list
4514  if (!ait)
4515  return (m_attackerInfo.begin())->second.attacker;
4516 
4517  float t = ((ait & AIT_HIGHESTTHREAT) ? 0.00 : 9999.00);
4518  Unit* a = nullptr;
4519  AttackerInfoList::iterator itr = m_attackerInfo.begin();
4520  for (; itr != m_attackerInfo.end(); ++itr)
4521  {
4522  if ((ait & AIT_VICTIMSELF) && !(ait & AIT_VICTIMNOTSELF) && itr->second.victim != m_bot)
4523  continue;
4524 
4525  if (!(ait & AIT_VICTIMSELF) && (ait & AIT_VICTIMNOTSELF) && itr->second.victim == m_bot)
4526  continue;
4527 
4528  if ((ait & AIT_VICTIMNOTSELF) && victim && itr->second.victim != victim)
4529  continue;
4530 
4531  if (!(ait & (AIT_LOWESTTHREAT | AIT_HIGHESTTHREAT)))
4532  return itr->second.attacker;
4533  else
4534  {
4535  if ((ait & AIT_HIGHESTTHREAT) && /*(itr->second.victim==m_bot) &&*/ itr->second.threat >= t)
4536  {
4537  t = itr->second.threat;
4538  a = itr->second.attacker;
4539  }
4540  else if ((ait & AIT_LOWESTTHREAT) && /*(itr->second.victim==m_bot) &&*/ itr->second.threat <= t)
4541  {
4542  t = itr->second.threat;
4543  a = itr->second.attacker;
4544  }
4545  }
4546  }
4547  return a;
4548 }

4637  else if (str == "resistshadow") co = ORDERS_RESIST_SHADOW;
4638  else co = ORDERS_RESET;

4645 void PlayerbotAI::SetCombatOrder(CombatOrderType co, Unit* target)
4646 {
4647  uint32 gTempTarget;
4648  std::string gname;
4649  if (target)
4650  {
4651  gTempTarget = target->GetGUIDLow();
4652  gname = target->GetName();
4653  }
4654 
4655  // reset m_combatOrder after ORDERS_PASSIVE
4656  if (m_combatOrder == ORDERS_PASSIVE)
4657  {
4658  m_combatOrder = ORDERS_NONE;
4659  m_targetAssist = nullptr;
4660  m_targetProtect = nullptr;
4661  }
4662 
4663  switch (co)
4664  {
4665  case ORDERS_TANK: // 1(01)
4666  {
4667  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_MAIN_TANK)
4668  m_combatOrder = (CombatOrderType)((uint32) m_combatOrder & (uint32) ~ORDERS_MAIN_TANK); // ORDERS_TANK and ORDERS_MAIN_TANK exclude one each other, remove one when the other is set
4669  break;
4670  }
4671  case ORDERS_ASSIST: // 2(10)
4672  {
4673  if (!target)
4674  {
4675  TellMaster("The assist command requires a target.");
4676  return;
4677  }
4678  else m_targetAssist = target;
4679  break;
4680  }
4681  case ORDERS_HEAL: // 4(100)
4682  {
4683  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_MAIN_HEAL)
4684  m_combatOrder = (CombatOrderType)((uint32) m_combatOrder & (uint32) ~ORDERS_MAIN_HEAL); // ORDERS_HEAL and ORDERS_MAIN_HEAL exclude one each other, remove one when the other is set
4685  break;
4686  }
4687  case ORDERS_PROTECT: // 10(10000)
4688  {
4689  if (!target)
4690  {
4691  TellMaster("The protect command requires a target.");
4692  return;
4693  }
4694  else m_targetProtect = target;
4695  break;
4696  }
4697  case ORDERS_PASSIVE: // 20(100000)
4698  {
4699  m_combatOrder = ORDERS_PASSIVE;
4700  m_targetAssist = nullptr;
4701  m_targetProtect = nullptr;
4702  return;
4703  }
4704  case ORDERS_MAIN_TANK: // 1000(1000000000000)
4705  {
4706  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_TANK)
4707  m_combatOrder = (CombatOrderType)((uint32) m_combatOrder & (uint32) ~ORDERS_TANK); // ORDERS_TANK and ORDERS_MAIN_TANK exclude one each other, remove one when the other is set
4708  break;
4709  }
4710  case ORDERS_MAIN_HEAL: // 2000(10000000000000)
4711  {
4712  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_HEAL)
4713  m_combatOrder = (CombatOrderType)((uint32) m_combatOrder & (uint32) ~ORDERS_HEAL); // ORDERS_HEAL and ORDERS_MAIN_HEAL exclude one each other, remove one when the other is set
4714  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_NOT_MAIN_HEAL)
4715  m_combatOrder = (CombatOrderType)((uint32) m_combatOrder & (uint32) ~ORDERS_NOT_MAIN_HEAL); // ORDERS_NOT_MAIN_HEAL and ORDERS_MAIN_HEAL exclude one each other, remove one when the other is set
4716  break;
4717  }
4718  case ORDERS_NOT_MAIN_HEAL: // 4000(100000000000000)
4719  {
4720  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_MAIN_HEAL)
4721  m_combatOrder = (CombatOrderType)((uint32) m_combatOrder & (uint32) ~ORDERS_MAIN_HEAL); // ORDERS_NOT_MAIN_HEAL and ORDERS_MAIN_HEAL exclude one each other, remove one when the other is set
4722  break;
4723  }
4724  case ORDERS_RESET: // FFFF(1111111111111111)
4725  {
4726  m_combatOrder = ORDERS_NONE;
4727  m_targetAssist = nullptr;
4728  m_targetProtect = nullptr;
4729  m_DelayAttackInit = CurrentTime();
4730  m_DelayAttack = 0;
4731  CharacterDatabase.DirectPExecute("UPDATE playerbot_saved_data SET combat_order = 0, primary_target = 0, secondary_target = 0, pname = '',sname = '', combat_delay = 0 WHERE guid = '%u'", m_bot->GetGUIDLow());
4732  TellMaster("Orders are cleaned!");
4733  return;
4734  }
4735  default:
4736  break;
4737  }
4738 
4739  // Do your magic
4740  if ((co & ORDERS_PRIMARY))
4741  {
4742  m_combatOrder = (CombatOrderType)(((uint32) m_combatOrder & (uint32) ORDERS_SECONDARY) | (uint32) co);
4743  if (target)
4744  CharacterDatabase.DirectPExecute("UPDATE playerbot_saved_data SET combat_order = '%u', primary_target = '%u', pname = '%s' WHERE guid = '%u'", (m_combatOrder & ~ORDERS_TEMP), gTempTarget, gname.c_str(), m_bot->GetGUIDLow());
4745  else
4746  CharacterDatabase.DirectPExecute("UPDATE playerbot_saved_data SET combat_order = '%u' WHERE guid = '%u'", (m_combatOrder & ~ORDERS_TEMP), m_bot->GetGUIDLow());
4747  }
4748  else
4749  {
4750  m_combatOrder = (CombatOrderType)((uint32)m_combatOrder | (uint32)co);
4751  if (target)
4752  CharacterDatabase.DirectPExecute("UPDATE playerbot_saved_data SET combat_order = '%u', secondary_target = '%u', sname = '%s' WHERE guid = '%u'", (m_combatOrder & ~ORDERS_TEMP), gTempTarget, gname.c_str(), m_bot->GetGUIDLow());
4753  else
4754  CharacterDatabase.DirectPExecute("UPDATE playerbot_saved_data SET combat_order = '%u' WHERE guid = '%u'", (m_combatOrder & ~ORDERS_TEMP), m_bot->GetGUIDLow());
4755  }
4756 }

4758 void PlayerbotAI::ClearCombatOrder(CombatOrderType co)

4760  m_combatOrder = (CombatOrderType)((uint32) m_combatOrder & (uint32) ~co);
4761 
4762  switch (co)
4763  {
4764  case ORDERS_NONE:
4765  case ORDERS_TANK:
4766  case ORDERS_MAIN_TANK:

4773  case ORDERS_SECONDARY:

4789 
4790 void PlayerbotAI::MovementReset()
4791 {
4792  // stop moving...
4793  MovementClear();
4794  if (m_movementOrder == MOVEMENT_FOLLOW)
4795  {
4796  if (!m_followTarget)
4797  return;
4798 
4799  // don't follow while in combat
4800  if (m_bot->IsInCombat())
4801  return;
4802 
4803  Player* pTarget; // target is player
4804  if (m_followTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4805  pTarget = ((Player*) m_followTarget);
4806 
4807  if (pTarget)
4808  {
4809  // check player for follow situations
4810  if (pTarget->IsBeingTeleported() || pTarget->IsTaxiFlying() || pTarget->GetCorpse())
4811  return;
4812  }
4813 
4814  // is bot too far from the follow target
4815  if (!m_bot->IsWithinDistInMap(m_followTarget, 50))
4816  {
4817  DoTeleport(*m_followTarget);
4818  return;
4819  }
4820 
4821  if (m_bot->IsAlive() && !m_bot->IsBeingTeleported())
4822  {
4823  if (DistOverRide != 0)
4824  {
4825  if (m_FollowAutoGo == FOLLOWAUTOGO_OFF)
4826  {
4827  if (IsUpOrDown < DistOverRide)
4828  {
4829  IsUpOrDown = DistOverRide;
4830  gTempDist = (gTempDist + 1.0);
4831  gTempDist2 = (gTempDist2 + 1.0);
4832  }
4833  if (IsUpOrDown > DistOverRide)
4834  {
4835  if (IsUpOrDown >= 2)
4836  {
4837  IsUpOrDown = DistOverRide;
4838  gTempDist = (gTempDist - 1.0);
4839  gTempDist2 = (gTempDist2 - 1.0);
4840  }
4841  }
4842  }
4843  else
4844  {
4845  if (IsUpOrDown < DistOverRide)
4846  {
4847  gTempDist = 1.0;
4848  gTempDist2 = 2.0;
4849  IsUpOrDown = 0;
4850  for (IsUpOrDown = 0; IsUpOrDown < DistOverRide; ++IsUpOrDown)
4851  {
4852  gTempDist = (gTempDist + 1.0);
4853  gTempDist2 = (gTempDist2 + 1.0);
4854  }
4855  IsUpOrDown = DistOverRide;
4856  }
4857  else if (IsUpOrDown > DistOverRide)
4858  {
4859  uint8 getdowndist = (IsUpOrDown - DistOverRide);
4860  for (uint8 getdowndistb = 0; getdowndistb < getdowndist; ++getdowndistb)
4861  {
4862  gTempDist = (gTempDist - 1.0);
4863  gTempDist2 = (gTempDist2 - 1.0);
4864  }
4865  IsUpOrDown = DistOverRide;
4866  }
4867  }
4868  if (m_FollowAutoGo != FOLLOWAUTOGO_RESET)
4869  {
4870  gDist[0] = gTempDist;
4871  gDist[1] = gTempDist2;
4872  }
4873  else
4874  {
4875  gDist[0] = 0.5f;
4876  gDist[1] = 1.0f;
4877  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(3);
4878  m_FollowAutoGo = FOLLOWAUTOGO_INIT;
4879  }
4880  }
4881  float dist = rand_float(m_mgr.m_confFollowDistance[0], m_mgr.m_confFollowDistance[1]);
4882  float bdist = rand_float(gDist[0], gDist[1]);
4883  float angle = rand_float(0, M_PI_F);
4884  float bangle = rand_float(2.8f, 3.6f); // angle is based on radians
4885  float TankAngle = 3.1f;
4886  float AssistAngle = 2.8f;
4887  if (DistOverRide != 0)
4888  {
4889  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_TANK)
4890  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveFollow(m_followTarget, bdist, TankAngle);
4891  else if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_ASSIST)
4892  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveFollow(m_followTarget, bdist, AssistAngle);
4893  else
4894  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveFollow(m_followTarget, bdist, bangle);
4895  }
4896  else
4897  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveFollow(m_followTarget, dist, angle);
4898  if (m_FollowAutoGo == FOLLOWAUTOGO_RUN)
4899  m_FollowAutoGo = FOLLOWAUTOGO_INIT;
4900  }
4901  }
4902 }
4903 
4904 void PlayerbotAI::MovementClear()
4905 {
4906  // stop...
4907  m_bot->clearUnitState(UNIT_STAT_FOLLOW);
4908  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Initialize();
4909 
4910  // stand up...
4911  if (!m_bot->IsStandState())
4912  m_bot->SetStandState(UNIT_STAND_STATE_STAND);
4913 }

5031 void PlayerbotAI::UpdateAI(const uint32 /*p_time*/)
5032 {
5033  if (GetClassAI()->GetWaitUntil() <= CurrentTime())
5034  GetClassAI()->ClearWait();
5035 
5036  if (CurrentTime() < m_ignoreAIUpdatesUntilTime)
5037  return;
5038 
5039  // default updates occur every two seconds
5040  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(2);
5041 
5042  if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_LOADING)
5043  {
5044  if (m_bot->IsBeingTeleported())
5045  return;
5046  else
5047  {
5048  // is bot too far from the follow target
5049  if (!m_bot->IsWithinDistInMap(m_followTarget, 50))
5050  {
5051  DoTeleport(*m_followTarget);
5052  return;
5053  }
5054  else
5055  SetState(BOTSTATE_NORMAL);
5056 
5057  return;
5058  }
5059  }
5060 
5061  if (m_bot->IsBeingTeleported() || m_bot->GetTrader())
5062  return;
5063 
5064  if (m_FollowAutoGo == FOLLOWAUTOGO_INIT)
5065  {
5066  if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_TANK)
5067  DistOverRide = 1;
5068  else if (m_combatOrder & ORDERS_ASSIST)
5069  DistOverRide = 3;
5070  else
5071  DistOverRide = 4;
5072  m_FollowAutoGo = FOLLOWAUTOGO_SET;
5073  SetMovementOrder(MOVEMENT_FOLLOW, GetMaster());
5074  }
5075 
5076  if (!m_bot->IsAlive())
5077  {
5078  if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_DEAD)
5079  {
5080  // become ghost
5081  if (m_bot->GetCorpse())
5082  {
5083  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]: UpdateAI - %s already has a corpse...", m_bot->GetName() );
5084  SetState(BOTSTATE_DEADRELEASED);
5085  return;
5086  }
5087  m_bot->SetBotDeathTimer();
5088  m_bot->BuildPlayerRepop();
5089  // relocate ghost
5090  WorldLocation loc;
5091  Corpse* corpse = m_bot->GetCorpse();
5092  corpse->GetPosition(loc);
5093  m_bot->TeleportTo(loc.mapid, loc.coord_x, loc.coord_y, loc.coord_z, m_bot->GetOrientation());
5094  // set state to released
5095  SetState(BOTSTATE_DEADRELEASED);
5096 
5097  return;
5098  }
5099 
5100  if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_DEADRELEASED)
5101  {
5102  // get bot's corpse
5103  Corpse* corpse = m_bot->GetCorpse();
5104  if (!corpse)
5105  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]: UpdateAI - %s has no corpse!", m_bot->GetName() );
5106  return;
5107 
5108  // check if we are allowed to resurrect now
5109  time_t resurrect_time = corpse->GetGhostTime() + m_bot->GetCorpseReclaimDelay(corpse->GetType() == CORPSE_RESURRECTABLE_PVP);
5110  if (resurrect_time > CurrentTime())
5111  {
5112  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(resurrect_time);
5113  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]: UpdateAI - %s has to wait for %d seconds to revive...", m_bot->GetName(), m_ignoreAIUpdatesUntilTime-CurrentTime());
5114  return;
5115  }
5116  // resurrect now
5117  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]: UpdateAI - Reviving %s to corpse...", m_bot->GetName() );
5118 
5119  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(6);
5120 
5121  PlayerbotChatHandler ch(GetMaster());
5122  if (!ch.revive(*m_bot))
5123  {
5124  ch.sysmessage(".. could not be revived ..");
5125  return;
5126  }
5127  // set back to normal
5128  SetState(BOTSTATE_NORMAL);
5129 
5130  return;
5131  }
5132 
5133  // if (m_botState != BOTSTATE_DEAD && m_botState != BOTSTATE_DEADRELEASED)
5134  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]: UpdateAI - %s died and is not in correct state...", m_bot->GetName());
5135  // clear loot list on death
5136  m_lootTargets.clear();
5137  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
5138  // clear combat orders
5139  m_bot->SetSelectionGuid(ObjectGuid());
5140  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(true);
5141  // set state to dead
5142  SetState(BOTSTATE_DEAD);
5143  // wait 30sec
5144  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(30);
5145 
5146  return;
5147  }
5148 
5149  // If bot is in water, allow it to swim instead of being stuck above water or at the floor until it drowns itself
5150  if (m_bot->IsInWater() && m_bot->GetMap()->GetTerrain()->IsSwimmable(m_bot->GetPositionX(), m_bot->GetPositionY(), m_bot->GetPositionZ(), m_bot->GetCollisionHeight()))
5151  {
5152  if (!m_bot->IsSwimming())
5153  m_bot->m_movementInfo.AddMovementFlag(MOVEFLAG_SWIMMING);
5154  }
5155  else if (m_bot->IsSwimming()) // Clear swimming when going out of water
5156  m_bot->m_movementInfo.RemoveMovementFlag(MOVEFLAG_SWIMMING);
5157 
5158  // bot still alive
5159  if (!m_findNPC.empty())
5160  findNearbyCreature();
5161 
5162  // if we are casting a spell then interrupt it
5163  // unless it is a positive spell then bot is helping a friendly unit and the death of an enemy target should not prevent this
5164  // make sure any actions that cast a spell set a proper m_ignoreAIUpdatesUntilTime!
5165  Spell* const pSpell = GetCurrentSpell();
5166  if (pSpell && !(pSpell->IsChannelActive() || pSpell->IsAutoRepeat()) && !IsPositiveSpell(pSpell->m_spellInfo->Id))
5167  {
5168  // DEBUG_LOG("spell (%s) is being interrupted",pSpell->m_spellInfo->SpellName[0]);
5169  InterruptCurrentCastingSpell();
5170  return;
5171  }
5172 
5173  if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_TAME)
5174  {
5175  Unit* pTarget = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_bot, m_targetGuidCommand);
5176  if (!pTarget)
5177  return;
5178 
5179  m_bot->SetSelectionGuid(m_targetGuidCommand);
5180 
5181  if (!In_Range(pTarget, TAME_BEAST_1))
5182  m_bot->clearUnitState(UNIT_STAT_CHASE);
5183 
5184  if (!m_bot->hasUnitState(UNIT_STAT_CHASE))
5185  {
5186  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveChase(pTarget);
5187  return;
5188  }
5189 
5190  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(TAME_BEAST_1);
5191  if (!spellInfo)
5192  return;
5193 
5194  Spell* spell = new Spell(m_bot, spellInfo, false);
5195  if (!spell)
5196  return;
5197 
5198  if (m_bot->GetPetGuid() || spell->CheckCast(true) != SPELL_CAST_OK || !pTarget ||
5199  pTarget->IsDead() || !m_bot->IsInMap(pTarget) || !(((Creature*) pTarget)->GetCreatureInfo()->CreatureTypeFlags & CREATURE_TYPEFLAGS_TAMEABLE))
5200  {
5201  MovementReset();
5202  m_bot->SetSelectionGuid(ObjectGuid());
5203  SetState(BOTSTATE_NORMAL);
5204  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(0);
5205  }
5206  else if (!m_bot->HasAura(TAME_BEAST_1, EFFECT_INDEX_1))
5207  {
5208  m_bot->SetFacingTo(m_bot->GetAngle(pTarget));
5209  SpellCastTargets targets;
5210  targets.setUnitTarget(pTarget);
5211  spell->SpellStart(&targets);
5212  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(10);
5213  }
5214 
5215  return;
5216  }
5217 
5218  // direct cast command from master
5219  if (m_spellIdCommand != 0)
5220  {
5221  Unit* pTarget = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_bot, m_targetGuidCommand);
5222  if (pTarget)
5223  CastSpell(m_spellIdCommand, *pTarget);
5224  m_spellIdCommand = 0;
5225  m_targetGuidCommand = ObjectGuid();
5226  return;
5227  }
5228 
5229  if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_DELAYED)
5230  {
5231  if (m_CraftSpellId == 0)
5232  {
5233  SetState(BOTSTATE_NORMAL);
5234  AutoUpgradeEquipment();
5235  return;
5236  }
5237 
5238  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(m_CraftSpellId);
5239  if (!spellInfo)
5240  return;
5241 
5242  Spell* spell = new Spell(m_bot, spellInfo, false);
5243  if (!spell)
5244  return;
5245 
5246  if (GetSpellCharges(m_CraftSpellId) == 0 || spell->CheckCast(true) != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5247  {
5248  SetState(BOTSTATE_NORMAL);
5249  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(0);
5250  AutoUpgradeEquipment();
5251  m_CraftSpellId = 0;
5252  }
5253  else
5254  {
5255  SpellCastTargets targets;
5256  spell->SpellStart(&targets);
5257  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(6);
5258  }
5259 
5260  return;
5261  }
5262 
5263  //if master is unmounted, unmount the bot
5264  if (!GetMaster()->IsMounted() && m_bot->IsMounted())
5265  {
5266  WorldPacket emptyPacket;
5267  m_bot->GetSession()->HandleCancelMountAuraOpcode(emptyPacket); //updated code
5268  return;
5269  }
5270 
5271  // handle combat (either self/master/group in combat, or combat state and valid target)
5272  if (IsInCombat() || (m_botState == BOTSTATE_COMBAT && m_targetCombat) || m_ScenarioType == SCENARIO_PVP_DUEL)
5273  {
5274  //check if the bot is Mounted
5275  if (!m_bot->IsMounted())
5276  {
5277  if (!pSpell || !pSpell->IsChannelActive())
5278  {
5279  // DEBUG_LOG("m_DelayAttackInit (%li) + m_DelayAttack (%u) > time(%li)", m_DelayAttackInit, m_DelayAttack, CurrentTime());
5280  if (m_DelayAttackInit + m_DelayAttack > CurrentTime())
5281  return SetIgnoreUpdateTime(1); // short bursts of delay
5282 
5283  return DoNextCombatManeuver();
5284  }
5285  else // channelling a spell
5286  return SetIgnoreUpdateTime(0); // It's better to update AI more frequently during combat
5287  }
5288 
5289  return;
5290  }
5291 
5292  // bot was in combat recently - loot now
5293  if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_COMBAT)
5294  {
5295  if (GetCombatOrder() & ORDERS_TEMP)
5296  {
5297  if (GetCombatOrder() & ORDERS_TEMP_WAIT_TANKAGGRO)
5298  TellMaster("I was still waiting for the tank to gain aggro, but that doesn't make sense anymore...");
5299  if (GetCombatOrder() & ORDERS_TEMP_WAIT_OOC)
5300  TellMaster("I was still waiting OOC but I just got out of combat...");
5301  ClearCombatOrder(ORDERS_TEMP);
5302  }
5303  SetState(BOTSTATE_LOOTING);
5304  m_attackerInfo.clear();
5305  if (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_COMBAT))
5306  m_lootTargets.unique();
5307  else
5308  m_lootTargets.clear();
5309  }
5310 
5311  if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_LOOTING)
5312  return DoLoot();
5313 
5314  if (m_botState == BOTSTATE_FLYING)
5315  {
5316  /* std::ostringstream out;
5317  out << "Taxi: " << m_bot->GetName() << m_ignoreAIUpdatesUntilTime;
5318  TellMaster(out.str().c_str()); */
5319  DoFlight();
5320  SetState(BOTSTATE_NORMAL);
5321  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(0);
5322  return;
5323  }
5324 
5325  // if commanded to follow master and not already following master then follow master
5326  if (!m_bot->IsInCombat() && m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->GetCurrentMovementGeneratorType() == IDLE_MOTION_TYPE)
5327  return MovementReset();
5328 
5329  // do class specific non combat actions
5330  if (GetClassAI() && !m_bot->IsMounted() && !IsRegenerating())
5331  {
5332  GetClassAI()->DoNonCombatActions();
5333 
5334  // have we been told to collect loot after combat
5335  if (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_LOOT))
5336  {
5337  findNearbyCorpse();
5338  // start looting if have targets
5339  if (!m_lootTargets.empty())
5340  SetState(BOTSTATE_LOOTING);
5341  }
5342 
5343  // have we been told to collect GOs
5344  if (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_NEAROBJECT))
5345  {
5346  findNearbyGO();
5347  // start looting if have targets
5348  if (!m_lootTargets.empty())
5349  SetState(BOTSTATE_LOOTING);
5350  }
5351  return;
5352  }
5353 }

5355 Spell* PlayerbotAI::GetCurrentSpell() const
5356 {
5357  if (m_CurrentlyCastingSpellId == 0)
5358  return nullptr;
5359 
5360  Spell* const pSpell = m_bot->FindCurrentSpellBySpellId(m_CurrentlyCastingSpellId);
5361  return pSpell;
5362 }

5364 void PlayerbotAI::TellMaster(const std::string& text) const

5369 void PlayerbotAI::TellMaster(const char* fmt, ...) const
5370 {
5371  char temp_buf[2048];
5372  va_list ap;
5373  va_start(ap, fmt);
5374  vsnprintf(temp_buf, 2048, fmt, ap);
5375  va_end(ap);
5376  std::string str = temp_buf;
5377  TellMaster(str);
5378 }
5379 
5380 void PlayerbotAI::SendWhisper(const std::string& text, Player& player) const
5381 {
5382  if (player.GetPlayerbotAI())
5383  return;
5384 
5385  WorldPacket* const packet = new WorldPacket(CMSG_MESSAGECHAT, 200);
5386  *packet << uint32(CHAT_MSG_WHISPER);
5387  *packet << uint32(LANG_UNIVERSAL);
5388  *packet << player.GetName();
5389  *packet << text;
5390  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket>(packet)); // queue the packet to get around race condition
5391 }

5393 bool PlayerbotAI::canObeyCommandFrom(const Player& player) const
5394 {
5395  return player.GetSession()->GetAccountId() == GetMaster()->GetSession()->GetAccountId();
5396 }
5397 
5398 bool PlayerbotAI::In_Range(Unit* Target, uint32 spellId)
5399 {
5400  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
5401  if (!pSpellInfo)
5402  return false;
5403 
5404  SpellRangeEntry const* TempRange = GetSpellRangeStore()->LookupEntry(pSpellInfo->rangeIndex);
5405 
5406  //Spell has invalid range store so we can't use it
5407  if (!TempRange)
5408  return false;
5409 
5410  if ((TempRange->minRange == 0.0f) && (TempRange->maxRange == 0.0f))
5411  return true;
5412 
5413  //Unit is out of range for this spell
5414  if (!m_bot->IsInRange(Target, TempRange->minRange, TempRange->maxRange))
5415  return false;
5416 
5417  return true;
5418 }
5419 
5420 SpellCastResult PlayerbotAI::CheckBotCast(const SpellEntry* sInfo)
5421 {
5422  if (!sInfo)
5423  return SPELL_FAILED_ERROR;
5424 
5425  // check DoLoot() spells before casting
5426  Spell tmp_spell(m_bot, sInfo, false);
5427 
5428  if (m_lootCurrent.IsCreature())
5429  {
5430  if (Creature* obj = m_bot->GetMap()->GetCreature(m_lootCurrent))
5431  tmp_spell.m_targets.setUnitTarget(obj);
5432  }
5433  else if (m_lootCurrent.IsGameObject())
5434  {
5435  if (GameObject* obj = m_bot->GetMap()->GetGameObject(m_lootCurrent))
5436  tmp_spell.m_targets.setGOTarget(obj);
5437  }
5438 
5439  return tmp_spell.CheckCast(false);
5440 }

5444  uint32 spellId = getSpellId(args);
5445  return (spellId) ? CastSpell(spellId) : SPELL_NOT_FOUND;
5446 }

5448 SpellCastResult PlayerbotAI::CastSpell(uint32 spellId, Unit& target)
5449 {
5450  ObjectGuid oldSel = m_bot->GetSelectionGuid();
5451  m_bot->SetSelectionGuid(target.GetObjectGuid());
5452  SpellCastResult rv = CastSpell(spellId);
5453  m_bot->SetSelectionGuid(oldSel);
5454  return rv;
5455 }
5456 
5457 SpellCastResult PlayerbotAI::CastSpell(uint32 spellId)
5458 {
5459  // some AIs don't check if the bot doesn't have spell before using it
5460  // so just return false when this happens
5461  if (spellId == 0)
5462  return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_KNOWN;
5463 
5464  // see Creature.cpp 1738 for reference
5465  // don't allow bot to cast damage spells on friends
5466  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
5467  if (!pSpellInfo)
5468  {
5469  TellMaster("Missing spell entry in CastSpell for spellid %u.", spellId);
5470  return SPELL_NOT_FOUND;
5471  }
5472 
5473  // check spell cooldown
5474  if (!m_bot->IsSpellReady(*pSpellInfo))
5475  return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
5476 
5477  // for AI debug purpose: uncomment the following line and bot will tell Master of every spell they attempt to cast
5478  // TellMaster("I'm trying to cast %s (spellID %u)", pSpellInfo->SpellName[0], spellId);
5479 
5480  // Power check
5481  // We use Spell::CheckPower() instead of UnitAI::CanCastSpell() because bots are players and have more requirements than mere units
5482  SpellCastResult res = Spell(m_bot, pSpellInfo, false).CheckPower(true); //Find out if it really should be strict
5483  if (res != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5484  return res;
5485 
5486  // set target
5487  ObjectGuid targetGUID = m_bot->GetSelectionGuid();
5488  Unit* pTarget = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_bot, targetGUID);
5489 
5490  if (!pTarget)
5491  pTarget = m_bot;
5492 
5493  if (IsPositiveSpell(spellId))
5494  {
5495  if (pTarget && m_bot->CanAttack(pTarget))
5496  pTarget = m_bot;
5497  }
5498  else
5499  {
5500  if (pTarget && m_bot->CanAssist(pTarget)) // Can't cast hostile spell on friendly unit
5501  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_FRIENDLY;
5502 
5503  m_bot->SetInFront(pTarget);
5504  }
5505 
5506  float CastTime = 0.0f;
5507 
5508  // stop movement to prevent cancel spell casting
5509  SpellCastTimesEntry const* castTimeEntry = sSpellCastTimesStore.LookupEntry(pSpellInfo->CastingTimeIndex);
5510  if (castTimeEntry && castTimeEntry->CastTime)
5511  {
5512  CastTime = (castTimeEntry->CastTime / 1000);
5513  DEBUG_LOG("[PlayerbotAI]: CastSpell - Bot movement reset for casting %s (%u)", pSpellInfo->SpellName[0], spellId);
5514  m_bot->StopMoving();
5515  }
5516 
5517  uint32 target_type = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
5518 
5519  if (pSpellInfo->Effect[0] == SPELL_EFFECT_OPEN_LOCK)
5520  target_type = TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT;
5521 
5522  m_CurrentlyCastingSpellId = spellId;
5523 
5524  if (pSpellInfo->Effect[0] == SPELL_EFFECT_OPEN_LOCK ||
5525  pSpellInfo->Effect[0] == SPELL_EFFECT_SKINNING)
5526  {
5527  if (m_lootCurrent)
5528  {
5529  SpellCastResult castResult = CheckBotCast(pSpellInfo);
5530  if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5531  return castResult;
5532 
5533  std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket> packet(new WorldPacket(CMSG_CAST_SPELL, 1 + 4 + 1 + 4 + 8));
5534  *packet << uint8(0); // spells cast count;
5535  *packet << spellId;
5536  *packet << uint8(0); // unk_flags
5537  *packet << uint32(target_type);
5538  *packet << m_lootCurrent.WriteAsPacked();
5539  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::move(packet)); // queue the packet to get around race condition
5540 
5541  if (target_type == TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT)
5542  {
5543  std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket> packetgouse(new WorldPacket(CMSG_GAMEOBJ_REPORT_USE, 8));
5544  *packetgouse << m_lootCurrent;
5545  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::move(packetgouse)); // queue the packet to get around race condition
5546 
5547  GameObject* obj = m_bot->GetMap()->GetGameObject(m_lootCurrent);
5548  if (!obj)
5549  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5550 
5551  // add other go types here, i.e.:
5552  // GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_CHEST - loot quest items of chest
5553  if (obj->GetGoType() == GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_QUESTGIVER)
5554  {
5555  TurnInQuests(obj);
5556 
5557  // auto accept every available quest this NPC has
5558  m_bot->PrepareQuestMenu(m_lootCurrent);
5559  QuestMenu& questMenu = m_bot->GetPlayerMenu()->GetQuestMenu();
5560  for (uint32 iI = 0; iI < questMenu.MenuItemCount(); ++iI)
5561  {
5562  QuestMenuItem const& qItem = questMenu.GetItem(iI);
5563  uint32 questID = qItem.m_qId;
5564  if (!AddQuest(questID, obj))
5565  TellMaster("Couldn't take quest");
5566  }
5567  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
5568  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(false);
5569  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MoveIdle();
5570  }
5571  }
5572  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5573  }
5574  else
5575  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_IMPLICIT_TARGETS;
5576  }
5577  else
5578  {
5579  // Check spell range
5580  if (!In_Range(pTarget, spellId))
5581  return SPELL_FAILED_OUT_OF_RANGE;
5582 
5583  // Check line of sight
5584  if (!m_bot->IsWithinLOSInMap(pTarget))
5585  return SPELL_FAILED_LINE_OF_SIGHT;
5586 
5587  // Some casting times are negative so set ignore update time to 1 sec to avoid stucking the bot AI
5588  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(std::max(CastTime, 0.0f) + 1);
5589 
5590  if (IsAutoRepeatRangedSpell(pSpellInfo))
5591  return m_bot->CastSpell(pTarget, pSpellInfo, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED); // cast triggered spell
5592  else
5593  return m_bot->CastSpell(pTarget, pSpellInfo, TRIGGERED_NONE); // uni-cast spell
5594  }
5595 }
5596 
5597 SpellCastResult PlayerbotAI::CastPetSpell(uint32 spellId, Unit* target)
5598 {
5599  if (spellId == 0)
5600  return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_KNOWN;
5601 
5602  Pet* pet = m_bot->GetPet();
5603  if (!pet)
5604  return SPELL_FAILED_NO_PET;
5605 
5606  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
5607  if (!pSpellInfo)
5608  {
5609  TellMaster("Missing spell entry in CastPetSpell()");
5610  return SPELL_NOT_FOUND;
5611  }
5612 
5613  if (!pet->IsSpellReady(*pSpellInfo))
5614  return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
5615 
5616  // set target
5617  Unit* pTarget;
5618  if (!target)
5619  {
5620  ObjectGuid targetGUID = m_bot->GetSelectionGuid();
5621  pTarget = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_bot, targetGUID);
5622  }
5623  else
5624  pTarget = target;
5625 
5626  if (IsPositiveSpell(spellId))
5627  {
5628  if (pTarget && m_bot->CanAttack(pTarget))
5629  pTarget = m_bot;
5630  }
5631  else
5632  {
5633  if (pTarget && m_bot->CanAssist(pTarget)) // Can cast hostile spell on friendly unit
5634  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_FRIENDLY;
5635 
5636  if (!pet->isInFrontInMap(pTarget, 10)) // distance probably should be calculated
5637  pet->SetFacingTo(pet->GetAngle(pTarget));
5638  }
5639 
5640  pet->CastSpell(pTarget, pSpellInfo, TRIGGERED_NONE);
5641 
5642  Spell* const pSpell = pet->FindCurrentSpellBySpellId(spellId);
5643  if (!pSpell)
5644  return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_KNOWN;
5645 
5646  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5647 }
5648 
5649 // Perform sanity checks and cast spell
5650 SpellCastResult PlayerbotAI::Buff(uint32 spellId, Unit* target, void (*beforeCast)(Player*))
5651 {
5652  if (spellId == 0)
5653  return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_KNOWN;
5654 
5655  // Target already has aura from spellId, skip for speed. May need to add exceptions
5656  if (target->HasAura(spellId))
5657  return SPELL_FAILED_AURA_BOUNCED;
5658 
5659  SpellEntry const* spellProto = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
5660 
5661  if (!spellProto)
5662  return SPELL_NOT_FOUND;
5663 
5664  if (!target)
5665  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_IMPLICIT_TARGETS;
5666 
5667  // Select appropriate spell rank for target's level
5668  spellProto = sSpellMgr.SelectAuraRankForLevel(spellProto, target->GetLevel());
5669  if (!spellProto)
5670  return SPELL_NOT_FOUND;
5671 
5672  // Check if spell will boost one of already existent auras
5673  bool willBenefitFromSpell = false;
5674  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
5675  {
5676  if (spellProto->EffectApplyAuraName[i] == SPELL_AURA_NONE)
5677  break;
5678 
5679  bool sameOrBetterAuraFound = false;
5680  int32 bonus = m_bot->CalculateSpellEffectValue(target, spellProto, SpellEffectIndex(i));
5681  Unit::AuraList const& auras = target->GetAurasByType(AuraType(spellProto->EffectApplyAuraName[i]));
5682  for (Unit::AuraList::const_iterator it = auras.begin(); it != auras.end(); ++it)
5683  if ((*it)->GetModifier()->m_miscvalue == spellProto->EffectMiscValue[i] && (*it)->GetModifier()->m_amount >= bonus)
5684  {
5685  sameOrBetterAuraFound = true;
5686  break;
5687  }
5688  willBenefitFromSpell = willBenefitFromSpell || !sameOrBetterAuraFound;
5689  }
5690 
5691  if (!willBenefitFromSpell)
5692  return SPELL_FAILED_AURA_BOUNCED;
5693 
5694  // Druids may need to shapeshift before casting
5695  if (beforeCast)
5696  (*beforeCast)(m_bot);
5697 
5698  return CastSpell(spellProto->Id, *target);
5699 }
5700 
5701 // Can be used for personal buffs like Mage Armor and Inner Fire
5702 SpellCastResult PlayerbotAI::SelfBuff(uint32 spellId)
5703 {
5704  if (spellId == 0)
5705  return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_KNOWN;
5706 
5707  if (m_bot->HasAura(spellId))
5708  return SPELL_FAILED_AURA_BOUNCED;
5709 
5710  return CastSpell(spellId, *m_bot);
5711 }

5713 // Checks if spell is single per target per caster and will make any effect on target
5714 bool PlayerbotAI::CanReceiveSpecificSpell(uint8 spec, Unit* target) const
5715 {
5716  if (IsSpellSpecificUniquePerCaster(SpellSpecific(spec)))
5717  {
5718  Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap holders = target->GetSpellAuraHolderMap();
5719  Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap::iterator it;
5720  for (it = holders.begin(); it != holders.end(); ++it)
5721  if ((*it).second->GetCasterGuid() == m_bot->GetObjectGuid() && GetSpellSpecific((*it).second->GetId()) == SpellSpecific(spec))
5722  return false;
5723  }
5724  return true;
5725 }

5727 uint8 PlayerbotAI::_findItemSlot(Item* target)
5728 {
5729  // list out items equipped & in main backpack
5730  //INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START = 23
5731  //INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END = 39
5732 
5733  for (uint8 slot = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; slot++)
5734  {
5735  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]: FindItem - [%s's]backpack slot = %u",m_bot->GetName(),slot); // 23 to 38 = 16
5736  Item* const pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slot); // 255, 23 to 38
5737  if (pItem)
5738  {
5739  const ItemPrototype* const pItemProto = pItem->GetProto();
5740  if (!pItemProto)
5741  continue;
5742 
5743  if (pItemProto->ItemId == target->GetProto()->ItemId) // have required item
5744  return slot;
5745  }
5746  }
5747  // list out items in other removable backpacks
5748  //INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START = 19
5749  //INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END = 23
5750 
5751  for (uint8 bag = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; bag < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++bag) // 20 to 23 = 4
5752  {
5753  const Bag* const pBag = (Bag*) m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, bag); // 255, 20 to 23
5754  if (pBag)
5755  for (uint8 slot = 0; slot < pBag->GetBagSize(); ++slot)
5756  {
5757  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]: FindItem - [%s's]bag[%u] slot = %u", m_bot->GetName(), bag, slot); // 1 to bagsize = ?
5758  Item* const pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(bag, slot); // 20 to 23, 1 to bagsize
5759  if (pItem)
5760  {
5761  const ItemPrototype* const pItemProto = pItem->GetProto();
5762  if (!pItemProto)
5763  continue;
5764 
5765  if (pItemProto->ItemId == target->GetProto()->ItemId) // have required item
5766  return slot;
5767  }
5768  }
5769  }
5770  return 0;
5771 }

5897 bool PlayerbotAI::HasTool(uint32 TC)
5898 {
5899  std::ostringstream out;
5900 
5901  switch (TC)
5902  {
5903  case TC_MINING_PICK: // = 165
5904 
5905  if (m_bot->HasItemTotemCategory(TC))
5906  return true;
5907  else
5908  out << "|cffff0000I do not have a MINING PICK!";
5909  break;
5910 
5911  case TC_ARCLIGHT_SPANNER: // = 14
5912 
5913  if (m_bot->HasItemTotemCategory(TC))
5914  return true;
5915  else
5916  out << "|cffff0000I do not have an ARCLIGHT SPANNER!";
5917  break;
5918 
5919  case TC_BLACKSMITH_HAMMER: // = 162
5920 
5921  if (m_bot->HasItemTotemCategory(TC))
5922  return true;
5923  else
5924  out << "|cffff0000I do not have a BLACKSMITH's HAMMER!";
5925  break;
5926 
5927  case TC_SKINNING_KNIFE: // = 166
5928 
5929  if (m_bot->HasItemTotemCategory(TC))
5930  return true;
5931  else
5932  out << "|cffff0000I do not have a SKINNING KNIFE!";
5933  break;
5934 
5935  case TC_COPPER_ROD: // = 6,
5936  if (m_bot->HasItemTotemCategory(TC))
5937  return true;
5938  else
5939  out << "|cffff0000I do not have a RUNED COPPER ROD!";
5940  break;
5941 
5942  case TC_SILVER_ROD: // = 7,
5943  if (m_bot->HasItemTotemCategory(TC))
5944  return true;
5945  else
5946  out << "|cffff0000I do not have a RUNED SILVER ROD!";
5947  break;
5948 
5949  case TC_GOLDEN_ROD: // = 8,
5950  if (m_bot->HasItemTotemCategory(TC))
5951  return true;
5952  else
5953  out << "|cffff0000I do not have a RUNED GOLDEN ROD!";
5954  break;
5955 
5956  case TC_TRUESILVER_ROD: // = 9,
5957  if (m_bot->HasItemTotemCategory(TC))

6026 bool PlayerbotAI::PickPocket(Unit* pTarget)
6027 {
6028  if (!pTarget)
6029  return false;
6030 
6031  ObjectGuid markGuid = pTarget->GetObjectGuid();
6032  Creature* c = m_bot->GetMap()->GetCreature(markGuid);
6033  if (c)
6034  {
6035  Loot*& loot = c->m_loot;
6036  if (!loot)
6037  loot = new Loot(m_bot, c, LOOT_PICKPOCKETING);
6038  else
6039  {
6040  if (loot->GetLootType() != LOOT_PICKPOCKETING)
6041  {
6042  delete loot;
6043  loot = new Loot(m_bot, c, LOOT_PICKPOCKETING);
6044  }
6045  }
6046 
6047  if (loot->GetGoldAmount())
6048  {
6049  m_bot->ModifyMoney(loot->GetGoldAmount());
6050 
6051  if (m_mgr.m_confDebugWhisper)
6052  {
6053  std::ostringstream out;
6054 
6055  // calculate how much money bot loots
6056  uint32 copper = loot->GetGoldAmount();
6057  uint32 gold = uint32(copper / 10000);
6058  copper -= (gold * 10000);
6059  uint32 silver = uint32(copper / 100);
6060  copper -= (silver * 100);
6061 
6062  out << "|r|cff009900" << m_bot->GetName() << " loots: " << "|h|cffffffff[|r|cff00ff00" << gold
6063  << "|r|cfffffc00g|r|cff00ff00" << silver
6064  << "|r|cffcdcdcds|r|cff00ff00" << copper
6065  << "|r|cff993300c"
6066  << "|h|cffffffff]";
6067 
6068  TellMaster(out.str().c_str());
6069  }
6070 
6071  // send the money to the bot and remove it from the creature
6072  loot->SendGold(m_bot);
6073  }
6074 
6075  if (!loot->AutoStore(m_bot, false, NULL_BAG, NULL_SLOT))
6076  sLog.outDebug("PLAYERBOT Debug: Failed to get loot from pickpocketed NPC");
6077 
6078  // release the loot whatever happened
6079  loot->Release(m_bot);
6080  }
6081  return false; // ensures that the rogue only pick pockets target once
6082 }

6084 bool PlayerbotAI::HasSpellReagents(uint32 spellId)
6085 {
6086  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
6087  if (!pSpellInfo)
6088  return false;
6089 
6090  if (m_bot->CanNoReagentCast(pSpellInfo))
6091  return true;
6092 
6093  for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_REAGENTS; ++i)
6094  {
6095  if (pSpellInfo->Reagent[i] <= 0)
6096  continue;
6097 
6098  uint32 itemid = pSpellInfo->Reagent[i];
6099  uint32 count = pSpellInfo->ReagentCount[i];
6100 
6101  if (!m_bot->HasItemCount(itemid, count))
6102  return false;
6103  }
6104 
6105  return true;
6106 }

6108 uint32 PlayerbotAI::GetSpellCharges(uint32 spellId)
6109 {
6110  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
6111  if (!pSpellInfo)
6112  return 0;
6113 
6114  if (m_bot->CanNoReagentCast(pSpellInfo))
6115  return 0;
6116 
6117  uint32 charges = 0;
6118  std::list<uint32> chargeList;
6119  for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_REAGENTS; ++i)
6120  {
6121  if (pSpellInfo->Reagent[i] <= 0)
6122  continue;
6123 
6124  uint32 totalcount = 0;
6125  uint32 itemid = pSpellInfo->Reagent[i];
6126  uint32 count = pSpellInfo->ReagentCount[i];
6127  ItemCountInInv(itemid, totalcount);
6128  chargeList.push_back((totalcount / count));
6129  }
6130 
6131  for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_TOTEM_CATEGORIES; ++i)
6132  {
6133  if (pSpellInfo->TotemCategory[i] == 0)
6134  continue;
6135 
6136  if (!m_bot->HasItemTotemCategory(pSpellInfo->TotemCategory[i]))
6137  {
6138  m_noToolList.push_back(pSpellInfo->TotemCategory[i]);
6139  return 0;
6140  }
6141  }
6142 
6143  if (!chargeList.empty())
6144  {
6145  charges = chargeList.front();
6146  chargeList.pop_front();
6147  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = chargeList.begin(); it != chargeList.end(); ++it)
6148  if (*it < charges)
6149  charges = *it;
6150  }
6151  return charges;
6152 }

6154 void PlayerbotAI::ItemCountInInv(uint32 itemid, uint32& count)
6155 {
6156  for (int i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++i)
6157  {
6158  Item* pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
6159  if (pItem && pItem->GetEntry() == itemid && !pItem->IsInTrade())
6160  count += pItem->GetCount();
6161  }
6162 
6163  for (int i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
6164  {
6165  if (Bag* pBag = (Bag*) m_bot->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
6166  for (uint32 j = 0; j < pBag->GetBagSize(); ++j)
6167  {
6168  Item* pItem = m_bot->GetItemByPos(i, j);
6169  if (pItem && pItem->GetEntry() == itemid && !pItem->IsInTrade())
6170  count += pItem->GetCount();
6171  }
6172  }
6173 }
6174 
6175 // extracts all item ids in format below
6176 // I decided to roll my own extractor rather then use the one in ChatHandler
6177 // because this one works on a const string, and it handles multiple links
6178 // |color|linkType:key:something1:...:somethingN|h[name]|h|r
6179 void PlayerbotAI::extractItemIds(const std::string& text, std::list<uint32>& itemIds) const
6180 {
6181  uint8 pos = 0;
6182  while (true)
6183  {
6184  int i = text.find("Hitem:", pos);
6185  if (i == -1)
6186  break;
6187  pos = i + 6;
6188  int endPos = text.find(':', pos);
6189  if (endPos == -1)
6190  break;
6191  std::string idC = text.substr(pos, endPos - pos);
6192  uint32 id = atol(idC.c_str());
6193  pos = endPos;
6194  if (id)
6195  itemIds.push_back(id);
6196  }
6197 }
6198

6206  break;

6208  int endPos = text.find('|', pos);
6209  if (endPos == -1)
6210  break;
6211  std::string idC = text.substr(pos, endPos - pos);
6212  uint32 id = atol(idC.c_str());
6213  pos = endPos;
6214  if (id)
6215  mailIds.push_back(id);
6216  }

6292  {

6294  {

6321  TellMaster("In fact, according to our records, it's no glyph at all");
6322 
6323  delete result;
6324  return ts_id;
6325  }
6326  }

6333  TellMaster("In fact, according to our records, it's no glyph at all");
6334

6463 TalentSpec PlayerbotAI::GetTalentSpec(long specClass, long choice)
6464 {

6472  for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) ts.glyphIdMinor[i] = 0;

6475  if (0 >= choice || (long) GetTalentSpecsAmount(specClass) < choice) return ts;

6506  */

6509  ts.specClass = fields[2].GetInt16();
6510  if (ts.specClass != CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT && ts.specClass != CLASS_DRUID && ts.specClass != CLASS_HUNTER && ts.specClass != CLASS_MAGE && ts.specClass != CLASS_PALADIN && ts.specClass != CLASS_PRIEST && ts.specClass != CLASS_ROGUE && ts.specClass != CLASS_SHAMAN && ts.specClass != CLASS_WARLOCK && ts.specClass != CLASS_WARRIOR &&
6511  ts.specClass != CLASS_PET_CUNNING && ts.specClass != CLASS_PET_FEROCITY && ts.specClass != CLASS_PET_TENACITY)
6512  {
