9537 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandPull(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
9538 {
9539  bool bReadyCheck = false;
9540 
9541  if (!m_bot) return;
9542 
9543  if (ExtractCommand("test", text)) // switch to automatic follow distance
9544  {
9545  if (CanPull(fromPlayer))
9546  SendWhisper("Looks like I am capable of pulling. Ask me 'pull ready' with a target for a more precise check.", fromPlayer);
9547  return;
9548  }
9549  if (ExtractCommand("ready", text)) // switch to automatic follow distance
9550  {
9551  bReadyCheck = true;
9552  }
9553  else if (!text.empty())
9554  {
9555  SendWhisper("See 'help pull' for details on using the pull command.", fromPlayer);
9556  return;
9557  }
9558 
9559  // This function also takes care of error reporting
9560  if (!CanPull(fromPlayer))
9561  return;
9562 
9563  // Check for valid target
9564  m_bot->SetSelectionGuid(fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid());
9565  ObjectGuid attackOnGuid = m_bot->GetSelectionGuid();
9566  if (!attackOnGuid)
9567  {
9568  SendWhisper("No target is selected.", fromPlayer);
9569  return;
9570  }
9571 
9572  Unit* thingToAttack = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_bot, attackOnGuid);
9573  if (!thingToAttack)
9574  {
9575  SendWhisper("No target is selected.", fromPlayer);
9576  return;
9577  }
9578 
9579  if (m_bot->CanAssist(thingToAttack))
9580  {
9581  SendWhisper("Where I come from we don't attack our friends.", fromPlayer);
9582  return;
9583  }
9584  // TODO: Okay, this one should actually be fixable. InMap should return, but LOS (Line of Sight) should result in moving, well, into LoS.
9585  if (!m_bot->IsWithinLOSInMap(thingToAttack))
9586  {
9587  SendWhisper("I can't see that target!", fromPlayer);
9588  return;
9589  }
9590  GetCombatTarget(thingToAttack);
9591  if (!GetCurrentTarget())
9592  {
9593  SendWhisper("Failed to set target, cause unknown.", fromPlayer);
9594  return;
9595  }
9596 
9597  if (bReadyCheck)
9598  {
9599  SendWhisper("All checks have been passed and I am ready to pull! ... Are you sure you wouldn't like a smaller target?", fromPlayer);
9600  return;
9601  }
9602 
9603  // All healers which have it available will cast any applicable HoT (Heal over Time) spell on the tank
9604  GroupHoTOnTank();
9605 
9606  /* Technically the tank should wait a bit if/until the HoT has been applied
9607  but the above function immediately casts it rather than wait for an UpdateAI tick
9608 
9609  There is no need to take into account that GroupHoTOnTank() may fail due to global cooldown. Either you're prepared for a difficult
9610  pull in which case it won't fail due to global cooldown, or you're chaining easy pulls in which case you don't care.
9611  */
9612  /* So have the group wait for the tank to take action (and aggro) - this way it will be easy to see if tank has aggro or not without having to
9613  worry about tank not being the first to have UpdateAI() called
9614  */
9615 
9616  // Need to have a group and a tank, both checked in "CanPull()" call above
9617  //if (!(GetGroupTank()->GetPlayerbotAI()->GetClassAI()->Pull()))
9618  // I've been told to pull and a check was done above whether I'm actually a tank, so *I* will try to pull:
9619  if (!CastPull())
9620  {
9621  SendWhisper("I did my best but I can't actually pull. How odd.", fromPlayer);
9622  return;
9623  }
9624 
9625  // Sets Combat Orders to PULL
9626  SetGroupCombatOrder(ORDERS_TEMP_WAIT_TANKAGGRO);
9627 
9628  SetGroupIgnoreUpdateTime(2);
9629 
9630  // Set all group members (save this tank) to wait 10 seconds. They will wait until the tank says so, until any non-tank gains aggro or 10 seconds - whichever is shortest
9631  if (m_bot->GetGroup()) // one last sanity check, should be unnecessary
9632  {
9633  Group::MemberSlotList const& groupSlot = m_bot->GetGroup()->GetMemberSlots();
9634  for (Group::member_citerator itr = groupSlot.begin(); itr != groupSlot.end(); itr++)
9635  {
9636  Player* groupMember = sObjectMgr.GetPlayer(itr->guid);
9637  if (!groupMember || !groupMember->GetPlayerbotAI() || groupMember == m_bot)
9638  continue;
9639  groupMember->GetPlayerbotAI()->GetClassAI()->SetWait(10);
9640  }
9641  }
9642 
9643  //(4a) if tank, deactivate any attack (such as 'shoot (bow/gun)' for warriors), wait until in melee range, attack
9644  //(4b) if dps, wait until the target is in melee range of the tank +2seconds or until tank no longer holds aggro
9645  //(4c) if healer, do healing checks
9646  //(5) when target is in melee range of tank, wait 2 seconds (healers continue to do group heal checks, all do self-heal checks), then return to normal functioning
9647 }

9649 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandNeutralize(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
9650 {
9651  if (!m_bot) return;
9652 
9653  if (!text.empty())
9654  {
9655  SendWhisper("See 'help neutralize' for details on using the neutralize command.", fromPlayer);
9656  return;
9657  }
9658 
9659  // Check for valid target
9660  m_bot->SetSelectionGuid(fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid());
9661  ObjectGuid selectOnGuid = m_bot->GetSelectionGuid();
9662  if (!selectOnGuid)
9663  {
9664  SendWhisper("No target is selected.", fromPlayer);
9665  return;

9669  if (!thingToNeutralize)
9670  {
9671  SendWhisper("No valid target is selected.", fromPlayer);
9672  return;
9673  }
9674 
9675  if (m_bot->CanAssist(thingToNeutralize))
9676  {
9677  SendWhisper("I can't neutralize that target: this is a friend to me.", fromPlayer);

9685  }

9688  {
9689  SendWhisper("Target is already neutralized.", fromPlayer);
9690  return;
9691  }
9692

9694 
9695  // All checks passed: call the Neutralize function of each bot class
9696  // to define what spellid to use if available and if creature type is correct
9697  // m_spellIdCommand will be defined there and UpdateAI will then handle the cast
9698  if (!CastNeutralize())
9699  {
9700  SendWhisper("Something went wrong: I can't neutralize that target.", fromPlayer);
9701  return;

9705 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandCast(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
9706 {
9707  if (text.empty())
9708  {
9709  SendWhisper("cast must be used with a single spell link (shift + click the spell).", fromPlayer);
9710  return;
9711  }
9712 
9713  std::string spellStr = text;
9714  uint32 spellId = (uint32) atol(spellStr.c_str());
9715 
9716  // try and get spell ID by name
9717  if (spellId == 0)
9718  {
9719  spellId = getSpellId(spellStr.c_str(), true);
9720 
9721  // try link if text NOT (spellid OR spellname)
9722  if (spellId == 0)
9723  extractSpellId(text, spellId);
9724  }
9725 
9726  if (m_bot->HasAura(spellId))
9727  {
9728  m_bot->RemoveAurasByCasterSpell(spellId, m_bot->GetObjectGuid());
9729  return;
9730  }
9731 
9732  ObjectGuid castOnGuid = fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid();
9733  if (spellId != 0 && m_bot->HasSpell(spellId))
9734  {
9735  m_spellIdCommand = spellId;
9736  if (castOnGuid)
9737  m_targetGuidCommand = castOnGuid;
9738  else
9739  m_targetGuidCommand = m_bot->GetObjectGuid();
9740  }
9741 }

9793 // _HandleCommandDrop: Handle dropping items
9794 // drop [Item Link][Item Link] .. -- Drops item(s) from bot's inventory
9795 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandDrop(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
9796 {
9797  if (ExtractCommand("all", text)) // switch to auto drop low level white items
9798  {
9799  std::ostringstream msg;
9800  if (!text.empty())
9801  {
9802  SendWhisper("Invalid subcommand for 'drop all'", fromPlayer);
9803  return;

9806  msg << "I will " << (m_dropWhite ? "" : "no longer ") << "drop my low level normal items.";

9809  }

9811  {

9813  return;

9817  std::list<uint32> itemIds;
9818  extractItemIds(text, itemIds);
9819  report << "Dropped ";
9820  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = itemIds.begin(); it != itemIds.end(); ++it)
9821  report << DropItem(*it);
9822 
9823  if (report.str() == "Dropped ")
9824  {
9825  SendWhisper("No items were dropped. It would appear something has gone hinky.", fromPlayer);
9826  return;
9827  }
9828 
9829  report << ".";
9830  SendWhisper(report.str(), fromPlayer);
9831 }

9861 // _HandleCommandAuction: Handle auctions:
9862 // auction -- Lists bot(s) active auctions.
9863 // auction add [Item Link][Item Link] .. -- Create bot(s) active auction.
9864 // auction remove [Auction Link][Auction Link] .. -- Cancel bot(s) active auction. ([Auction Link] from auction)
9865 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandAuction(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
9866 {
9867  FollowAutoReset();
9868  if (text == "")
9869  m_findNPC.push_back(UNIT_NPC_FLAG_AUCTIONEER); // list all bot auctions
9870  else if (ExtractCommand("add", text))
9871  {
9872  std::list<uint32> itemIds;
9873  extractItemIds(text, itemIds);
9874  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = itemIds.begin(); it != itemIds.end(); ++it)
9875  m_tasks.push_back(std::pair<enum TaskFlags, uint32>(ADD_AUCTION, *it));
9876  m_findNPC.push_back(UNIT_NPC_FLAG_AUCTIONEER);
9877  }
9878  else if (ExtractCommand("remove", text))
9879  {
9880  std::list<uint32> auctionIds;
9881  extractAuctionIds(text, auctionIds);
9882  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = auctionIds.begin(); it != auctionIds.end(); ++it)
9883  m_tasks.push_back(std::pair<enum TaskFlags, uint32>(REMOVE_AUCTION, *it));
9884  m_findNPC.push_back(UNIT_NPC_FLAG_AUCTIONEER);
9885  }
9886  else
9887  SendWhisper("I don't understand what you're trying to do", fromPlayer);
9888 }

9890 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandMail(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
9891 {
9892  ChatHandler ch(&fromPlayer);
9893 
9894  if (text.empty())
9895  {
9896  ch.SendSysMessage("Syntax: mail <inbox [Mailbox] | getcash [mailid].. | getitem [mailid].. | delete [mailid]..>");
9897  return;
9898  }
9899  else if (ExtractCommand("inbox", text))
9900  {
9901  uint32 mail_count = 0;
9902  extractGOinfo(text, m_lootTargets);
9903 
9904  if (m_lootTargets.empty())
9905  {
9906  ch.SendSysMessage("Syntax: mail <inbox [Mailbox]>");
9907  return;
9908  }
9909

9911  m_lootTargets.pop_front();
9912  m_lootTargets.clear();
9913

9917  return;
9918  }

9925  ++mail_count;
9926 
9927  msg << "|cffffcccc|Hmail:" << (*itr)->messageID << "|h[" << (*itr)->messageID << "]|h|r ";
9928 
9929  switch ((*itr)->messageType)
9930  {
9931  case MAIL_NORMAL:
9932  {
9933  msg << "|cffffffff"; // white
9934  if ((*itr)->subject != "")
9935  msg << "Subject: " << (*itr)->subject << "\n";
9936 
9937  if ((*itr)->body != "")
9938  msg << (*itr)->body << "\n";
9939  break;
9940  }
9941  case MAIL_CREATURE:
9942  msg << "|cffccffccMAIL_CREATURE\n"; // green
9943  break;
9944  case MAIL_GAMEOBJECT:
9945  msg << "|cffccffccMAIL_GAMEOBJECT\n"; // green
9946  break;
9947  case MAIL_AUCTION:
9948  {
9949  msg << "|cffccffff"; // blue
9950  msg << AuctionResult((*itr)->subject, (*itr)->body) << "\n";
9951  break;
9952  }
9953  case MAIL_CALENDAR:
9954  msg << "|cffccffccMAIL_ITEM\n"; // green
9955  break;
9956  }
9957 
9958  if ((*itr)->money)
9959  msg << "[To Collect: " << Cash((*itr)->money) << " ]\n";
9960 
9961  uint8 item_count = (*itr)->items.size(); // max count is MAX_MAIL_ITEMS (12)
9962  if (item_count > 0)
9963  {
9964  msg << "Items: ";
9965  for (uint8 i = 0; i < item_count; ++i)
9966  {

9968  if (item)
9969  MakeItemLink(item, msg, true);
9970  }
9971  }
9972  msg << "\n";
9973  ch.SendSysMessage(msg.str().c_str());
9974  }
9975 
9976  if (mail_count == 0)
9977  ch.SendSysMessage("|cff009900My inbox is empty.");
9978  }
9979  else if (ExtractCommand("getcash", text))
9980  {
9981  std::ostringstream msg;
9982  std::list<uint32> mailIds;
9983  extractMailIds(text, mailIds);
9984  mailIds.unique();
9985  mailIds.sort();
9986  uint32 total = 0;
9987 
9988  if (mailIds.empty())
9989  {
9990  ch.SendSysMessage("Syntax: mail <getcash [mailId]..>");
9991  return;
9992  }
9993 
9994  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = mailIds.begin(); it != mailIds.end(); ++it)
9995  {
9996  Mail* m = m_bot->GetMail(*it);
9997  if (!m || m->state == MAIL_STATE_DELETED || m->deliver_time > CurrentTime())
9998  {
9999  m_bot->SendMailResult(*it, MAIL_MONEY_TAKEN, MAIL_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR);
10000  return;
10001  }
10002 
10003  m_bot->SendMailResult(*it, MAIL_MONEY_TAKEN, MAIL_OK);
10004  m_bot->ModifyMoney(m->money);
10005  total += m->money;
10006  m->money = 0;
10007  m->state = MAIL_STATE_CHANGED;
10008  m_bot->m_mailsUpdated = true;
10009  m_bot->UpdateMail();
10010  }
10011  if (total > 0)
10012  {
10013  msg << "|cff009900" << "I received: |r" << Cash(total);
10014  ch.SendSysMessage(msg.str().c_str());
10015  }
10016  }
10017  else if (ExtractCommand("getitem", text))
10018  {
10019  std::list<uint32> mailIds;
10020  extractMailIds(text, mailIds);
10021  mailIds.unique();
10022  mailIds.sort();
10023 
10024  if (mailIds.empty())
10025  {
10026  ch.SendSysMessage("Syntax: mail <getitem [mailId]..>");
10027  return;
10028  }
10029

10031  {
10032  Mail* m = m_bot->GetMail(*it);
10033  if (!m || m->state == MAIL_STATE_DELETED || m->deliver_time > CurrentTime())
10034  {
10035  m_bot->SendMailResult(*it, MAIL_ITEM_TAKEN, MAIL_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR);
10036  return;
10037  }
10038 
10039  // prevent cheating with skip client money check
10040  if (m_bot->GetMoney() < m->COD)
10041  {
10042  m_bot->SendMailResult(*it, MAIL_ITEM_TAKEN, MAIL_ERR_NOT_ENOUGH_MONEY);
10043  return;
10044  }
10045 
10046  if (m->HasItems())
10047  {
10048  bool has_items = true;
10049  std::ostringstream msg;

10056  if (!item)
10057  {
10058  ch.SendSysMessage("item not found");
10059  return;
10060  }
10061 
10062  ItemPosCountVec dest;
10063

10065  if (res == EQUIP_ERR_OK)
10066  {
10067  m->removedItems.push_back(itr->item_guid);
10068 
10069  if (m->COD > 0) // if there is COD, take COD money from player and send them to sender by mail
10070  {
10071  ObjectGuid sender_guid = ObjectGuid(HIGHGUID_PLAYER, m->sender);
10072  Player* sender = sObjectMgr.GetPlayer(sender_guid);
10073 
10074  uint32 sender_accId = 0;

10077  {

10079  if (sender)
10080  {
10081  sender_accId = sender->GetSession()->GetAccountId();
10082  sender_name = sender->GetName();
10083  }
10084  else if (sender_guid)
10085  {
10086  // can be calculated early
10087  sender_accId = sObjectMgr.GetPlayerAccountIdByGUID(sender_guid);
10088

10090  sender_name = sObjectMgr.GetMangosStringForDbcLocale(LANG_UNKNOWN);
10091  }

10093  GetMaster()->GetSession()->GetPlayerName(), GetMaster()->GetSession()->GetAccountId(), item->GetProto()->Name1, item->GetEntry(), item->GetCount(), m->COD, sender_name.c_str(), sender_accId);
10094  }
10095  else if (!sender)
10096  sender_accId = sObjectMgr.GetPlayerAccountIdByGUID(sender_guid);
10097 
10098  // check player existence
10099  if (sender || sender_accId)
10100  MailDraft(m->subject, "")
10101  .SetMoney(m->COD)
10102  .SendMailTo(MailReceiver(sender, sender_guid), m_bot, MAIL_CHECK_MASK_COD_PAYMENT);
10103 
10104  m_bot->ModifyMoney(-int32(m->COD));
10105  }
10106  m->COD = 0;
10107  m->state = MAIL_STATE_CHANGED;
10108  m_bot->m_mailsUpdated = true;
10109  m_bot->RemoveMItem(item->GetGUIDLow());

10113  m_bot->UpdateMail();

10117  MakeItemLink(item, msg, true);
10118  has_items = false;

10137  {

10161  return;

10171  msg << "|cffffcccc|h[" << *it << "]|h|r";
10172  }
10173  }
10174  msg << "|cff009900 has been deleted..";
10175  ch.SendSysMessage(msg.str().c_str());
10176  }

10179 // _HandleCommandBank: Handle bank:
10180 // bank -- Lists bot(s) bank balance.
10181 // bank deposit [Item Link][Item Link] .. -- Deposit item(s) in bank.
10182 // bank withdraw [Item Link][Item Link] .. -- Withdraw item(s) from bank. ([Item Link] from bank)
10183 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandBank(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
10184 {
10185  FollowAutoReset();
10186  if (text == "")
10187  m_findNPC.push_back(UNIT_NPC_FLAG_BANKER); // list all bot balance
10188  else if (ExtractCommand("deposit", text))
10189  {
10190  std::list<uint32> itemIds;
10191  extractItemIds(text, itemIds);
10192  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = itemIds.begin(); it != itemIds.end(); ++it)
10193  m_tasks.push_back(std::pair<enum TaskFlags, uint32>(BANK_DEPOSIT, *it));
10194  m_findNPC.push_back(UNIT_NPC_FLAG_BANKER);
10195  }
10196  else if (ExtractCommand("withdraw", text))
10197  {
10198  std::list<uint32> itemIds;
10199  extractItemIds(text, itemIds);
10200  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = itemIds.begin(); it != itemIds.end(); ++it)
10201  m_tasks.push_back(std::pair<enum TaskFlags, uint32>(BANK_WITHDRAW, *it));
10202  m_findNPC.push_back(UNIT_NPC_FLAG_BANKER);
10203  }
10204  else
10205  SendWhisper("I don't understand what you're trying to do", fromPlayer);
10206 }

10208 // _HandleCommandTalent: Handle talents & glyphs:
10209 // talent -- Lists bot(s) active talents [TALENT LINK] & glyphs [GLYPH LINK], unspent points & cost to reset
10210 // talent learn [TALENT LINK] .. -- Learn selected talent from bot client 'inspect' dialog -> 'talent' tab or from talent command (shift click icon/link)
10211 // talent reset -- Resets all talents
10212 // talent spec -- Lists various talentspecs for this bot's class
10213 // talent spec # -- Sets talent spec # as active talentspec
10214 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandTalent(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
10215 {
10216  std::ostringstream out;
10217  if (ExtractCommand("learn", text))
10218  {
10219  std::list<talentPair>talents;
10220  extractTalentIds(text, talents);
10221 
10222  for (std::list<talentPair>::iterator itr = talents.begin(); itr != talents.end(); itr++)
10223  {
10224  uint32 talentid;
10225  uint32 rank;
10226 
10227  talentid = itr->first;
10228  rank = itr->second;
10229 
10230  m_bot->LearnTalent(talentid, ++rank);
10231  m_bot->SendTalentsInfoData(false);
10232  InspectUpdate();
10233  }
10234 
10235  m_bot->MakeTalentGlyphLink(out);
10236  SendWhisper(out.str(), fromPlayer);
10237  }
10238  else if (ExtractCommand("reset", text))
10239  {
10240  FollowAutoReset();
10241  m_tasks.push_back(std::pair<enum TaskFlags, uint32>(RESET_TALENTS, 0));
10242  m_findNPC.push_back(UNIT_NPC_FLAG_TRAINER_CLASS);
10243  }
10244  else if (ExtractCommand("spec", text))
10245  {
10246  if (0 == GetTalentSpecsAmount())
10247  {
10248  SendWhisper("Database does not contain any Talent Specs (for any classes).", fromPlayer);
10249  return;
10250  }
10251  if (text.size() == 0) // no spec chosen nor other subcommand
10252  {
10253  std::list<TalentSpec> classSpecs = GetTalentSpecs((long) m_bot->getClass());
10254  std::list<TalentSpec>::iterator it;
10255  int count = 0;
10256 
10257  SendWhisper("Please select a talent spec to activate (reply 'talent spec #'):", fromPlayer);
10258  for (it = classSpecs.begin(); it != classSpecs.end(); it++)
10259  {
10260  count++;
10261 
10262  std::ostringstream oss;
10263  oss << count << ". " << it->specName;
10264  SendWhisper(oss.str(), fromPlayer);
10265  }
10266  if (count == 0)
10267  {
10268  std::ostringstream oss;
10269  oss << "Error: No TalentSpecs listed. Specs retrieved from DB for this class: %u" << m_bot->getClass();
10270  SendWhisper(oss.str(), fromPlayer);
10271  }
10272  }
10273  else
10274  {
10275  uint32 chosenSpec = strtoul(text.c_str(), nullptr, 0); // non-int returns 0; too big returns UINT MAX (or somesuch)
10276 
10277  // Warning: also catches non-int sub2command's - e.g. 'talent spec foobar'
10278  if (0 == chosenSpec)
10279  {
10280  ClearActiveTalentSpec();
10281  SendWhisper("The talent spec has been cleared.", fromPlayer);
10282  }
10283  else if (chosenSpec > GetTalentSpecsAmount((long) m_bot->getClass()))
10284  SendWhisper("The talent spec you have chosen is invalid. Please select one from the valid range (reply 'talent spec' for options).", fromPlayer);
10285  else
10286  {
10287  TalentSpec ts = GetTalentSpec((long) m_bot->getClass(), chosenSpec);
10288 
10289  // no use setting it to an invalid (and probably - hopefully - empty) TalentSpec
10290  if (0 != ts.specClass && TSP_NONE != ts.specPurpose)
10291  {
10292  out << "Activated talent spec: " << chosenSpec << ". " << ts.specName;
10293  SendWhisper(out.str(), fromPlayer);
10294  SetActiveTalentSpec(ts);
10295  if (!ApplyActiveTalentSpec())
10296  {
10297  SendWhisper("The talent spec has been set active but could not be applied. It appears something has gone awry.", fromPlayer);
10298  DEBUG_LOG("[PlayerbotAI]: Could set TalentSpec but could not apply it - 'talent spec #': Class: %u; chosenSpec: %u", m_bot->getClass(), chosenSpec);
10299  }
10300  InspectUpdate();
10301  }
10302  else
10303  {
10304  SendWhisper("An error has occured. Please let a Game Master know. This error has been logged.", fromPlayer);
10305  DEBUG_LOG("[PlayerbotAI]: Could not GetTalentSpec to set & apply - 'talent spec #': Class: %u; chosenSpec: %u", m_bot->getClass(), chosenSpec);
10306  }
10307  }
10308  }
10309  }
10310  // no valid subcommand found for command 'talent'
10311  else
10312  {
10313  uint32 gold = uint32(m_bot->resetTalentsCost() / 10000);
10314 
10315  if (gold > 0)
10316  out << "Cost to reset all Talents is " << gold << " |TInterface\\Icons\\INV_Misc_Coin_01:8|t";
10317 
10318  m_bot->MakeTalentGlyphLink(out);
10319  SendWhisper(out.str(), fromPlayer);
10320  }
10321 }

10323 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandProcess(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
10324 {
10325  uint32 spellId;
10326 
10327  if (ExtractCommand("disenchant", text, true)) // true -> "process disenchant" OR "process d"
10328  {
10329  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ENCHANTING))
10330  spellId = DISENCHANTING_1;
10331  else
10332  {
10333  SendWhisper("|cffff0000I can't disenchant, I don't have the skill.", fromPlayer);
10334  return;
10335  }
10336  }
10337  else if (ExtractCommand("mill", text, true)) // true -> "process mill" OR "process m"
10338  {
10339  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_INSCRIPTION))
10340  spellId = MILLING_1;
10341  else
10342  {
10343  SendWhisper("|cffff0000I can't mill, I don't have the skill.", fromPlayer);
10344  return;
10345  }
10346  }
10347  else if (ExtractCommand("prospect", text, true)) // true -> "process prospect" OR "process p"
10348  {
10349  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_JEWELCRAFTING) && m_bot->GetSkillValuePure(SKILL_JEWELCRAFTING) >= 20)
10350  spellId = PROSPECTING_1;
10351  else
10352  {
10353  SendWhisper("|cffff0000I can't prospect, I don't have the skill.", fromPlayer);
10354  return;
10355  }
10356  }
10357  else
10358  return;
10359 
10360  std::list<uint32> itemIds;
10361  std::list<Item*> itemList;
10362  extractItemIds(text, itemIds);
10363  findItemsInInv(itemIds, itemList);
10364 
10365  if (itemList.empty())
10366  {
10367  SendWhisper("|cffff0000I can't process that!", fromPlayer);
10368  return;
10369  }
10370 
10371  Item* reagent = itemList.back();
10372  itemList.pop_back();
10373 
10374  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
10375  if (!spellInfo)
10376  return;
10377 
10378  if (reagent)
10379  {
10380  SpellCastTargets targets;
10381  m_itemTarget = reagent->GetProto()->ItemId;
10382  targets.setItemTarget(reagent);
10383  Spell* spell = new Spell(m_bot, spellInfo, false);
10384  spell->SpellStart(&targets);
10385  }
10386 }

10388 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandUse(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
10389 {
10390  std::list<uint32> itemIds;
10391  std::list<Item*> itemList;
10392  extractItemIds(text, itemIds);
10393  findItemsInInv(itemIds, itemList);
10394 
10395  if (itemList.empty())
10396  {
10397  SendWhisper("|cffff0000I can't use that!", fromPlayer);
10398  return;
10399  }
10400 
10401  Item* tool = itemList.back();
10402  itemList.pop_back();
10403  if (tool)
10404  {
10405  // set target
10406  Unit* unit = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_bot, fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid());
10407  findItemsInEquip(itemIds, itemList);
10408  extractGOinfo(text, m_lootTargets);
10409  // DEBUG_LOG("tool (%s)",tool->GetProto()->Name1);
10410 
10411  if (!itemList.empty())
10412  {
10413  Item* itarget = itemList.back();
10414  if (itarget)
10415  {
10416  // DEBUG_LOG("target (%s)",itarget->GetProto()->Name1);
10417  UseItem(tool, _findItemSlot(itarget)); // on equipped item
10418  SetState(BOTSTATE_DELAYED);
10419  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(1);
10420  }
10421  }
10422  else if (!m_lootTargets.empty())
10423  {
10424  ObjectGuid gotarget = m_lootTargets.front();
10425  m_lootTargets.pop_front();
10426 
10427  GameObject* go = m_bot->GetMap()->GetGameObject(gotarget);
10428  if (go)
10429  // DEBUG_LOG("tool (%s) on target gameobject (%s)",tool->GetProto()->Name1,go->GetGOInfo()->name);
10430  UseItem(tool, TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT, gotarget); // on gameobject
10431  }
10432  else if (unit)
10433  // DEBUG_LOG("tool (%s) on selected target unit",tool->GetProto()->Name1);
10434  UseItem(tool, unit); // on unit
10435  else
10436  // DEBUG_LOG("tool (%s) on self",tool->GetProto()->Name1);
10437  UseItem(tool); // on self
10438  }
10439  return;
10440 }
10441 
10442 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandEquip(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
10443 {
10444  if (ExtractCommand("auto", text))
10445  {
10446  bool bOnce = false;
10447  bool bWasToggleOn = m_AutoEquipToggle;
10448 
10449  // run autoequip cycle once - right now - turning off after
10450  if (ExtractCommand("once", text))
10451  {
10452  bWasToggleOn = m_AutoEquipToggle;
10453  m_AutoEquipToggle = true;
10454  bOnce = true;
10455  }
10456  else if (ExtractCommand("on", text))
10457  m_AutoEquipToggle = true;
10458  else if (ExtractCommand("off", text))
10459  m_AutoEquipToggle = false;
10460  else // subcommand not found, assume toggle
10461  m_AutoEquipToggle = !m_AutoEquipToggle;
10462 
10463  CharacterDatabase.DirectPExecute("UPDATE playerbot_saved_data SET autoequip = '%u' WHERE guid = '%u'", m_AutoEquipToggle, m_bot->GetGUIDLow());
10464 
10465  if (m_AutoEquipToggle)
10466  AutoUpgradeEquipment();
10467 
10468  // feedback
10469  if (bOnce)
10470  {
10471  if (bWasToggleOn)
10472  SendWhisper("Equip Auto has run once, switching it off.", fromPlayer);
10473  else
10474  SendWhisper("Running Equip Auto once.", fromPlayer);
10475 
10476  m_AutoEquipToggle = false;
10477  }
10478  else if (m_AutoEquipToggle)
10479  {
10480  SendWhisper("Equip Auto has run and is |h|cff1eff00ON|h|r", fromPlayer);
10481  }
10482  else
10483  SendWhisper("Equip Auto is |h|cffff0000OFF|h|r", fromPlayer);
10484  return;
10485  }
10486  else if (ExtractCommand("info", text))
10487  {
10488  m_AutoEquipToggle ? SendWhisper("Auto Equip is |h|cff1eff00ON|h|r", fromPlayer) : SendWhisper("Auto Equip is |h|cffff0000OFF|h|r", fromPlayer);
10489  return;
10490  }
10491 
10492  // handle 'equip' command, expected in the form of 'equip [ITEM(s)]'
10493  std::list<uint32> itemIds;
10494  std::list<Item*> itemList;
10495  extractItemIds(text, itemIds);
10496  findItemsInInv(itemIds, itemList);
10497  for (std::list<Item*>::iterator it = itemList.begin(); it != itemList.end(); ++it)
10498  EquipItem(*it);
10499  InspectUpdate();
10500  SendNotEquipList(*m_bot);
10501 }
10502 
10503 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandFind(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
10504 {
10505  m_lootTargets.clear();
10506  extractGOinfo(text, m_lootTargets);
10507 
10508  if (m_lootTargets.empty())
10509  {
10510  SendWhisper("|cffff0000I can't find that!", fromPlayer);
10511  return;
10512  }
10513 
10514  m_lootCurrent = m_lootTargets.front();
10515  m_lootTargets.pop_front();
10516 
10517  GameObject* go = m_bot->GetMap()->GetGameObject(m_lootCurrent);
10518  if (!go)
10519  {
10520  m_lootTargets.clear();
10521  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
10522  return;
10523  }
10524 
10525  SetMovementOrder(MOVEMENT_STAY);
10526  m_bot->GetMotionMaster()->MovePoint(go->GetMapId(), go->GetPositionX(), go->GetPositionY(), go->GetPositionZ(), FORCED_MOVEMENT_RUN);
10527  m_lootTargets.clear();
10528  m_lootCurrent = ObjectGuid();
10529 }
10530 
10531 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandGet(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
10532 {
10533  if (!text.empty())
10534  {
10535  extractGOinfo(text, m_lootTargets);
10536  SetState(BOTSTATE_LOOTING);
10537  return;
10538  }
10539 
10540  // get a selected lootable corpse
10541  ObjectGuid getOnGuid = fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid();
10542  if (getOnGuid)
10543  {
10544  Creature* c = m_bot->GetMap()->GetCreature(getOnGuid);
10545  if (!c)
10546  return;
10547 
10548  uint32 skillId = 0;
10549  if (c->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE))
10550  skillId = c->GetCreatureInfo()->GetRequiredLootSkill();
10551 
10552  if (c->HasFlag(UNIT_DYNAMIC_FLAGS, UNIT_DYNFLAG_LOOTABLE) ||
10553  (c->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE) && m_bot->HasSkill(skillId)))
10554  {
10555  m_lootTargets.push_back(getOnGuid);
10556  SetState(BOTSTATE_LOOTING);
10557  }
10558  else
10559  SendWhisper("Target is not lootable by me.", fromPlayer);
10560  }
10561  else
10562  {
10563  SendWhisper("No target is selected.", fromPlayer);
10564  m_bot->HandleEmoteCommand(EMOTE_ONESHOT_TALK);
10565  }
10566 }
10567 
10568 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandCollect(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
10569 {
10570  while (text.size() > 0)
10571  {
10572  if (ExtractCommand("combat", text))
10573  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_COMBAT);
10574  else if (ExtractCommand("loot", text))
10575  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_LOOT);
10576  else if (ExtractCommand("quest", text))
10577  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_QUEST);
10578  else if (ExtractCommand("profession", text) || ExtractCommand("skill", text))
10579  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_PROFESSION);
10580  else if (ExtractCommand("skin", text) && m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_SKINNING)) // removes skin even if bot does not have skill
10581  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_SKIN);
10582  else if (ExtractCommand("objects", text) || ExtractCommand("nearby", text))
10583  {
10584  SetCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_NEAROBJECT);
10585  if (!HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_NEAROBJECT))
10586  m_collectObjects.clear();
10587  }
10588  else if (ExtractCommand("distance:", text))
10589  {
10590  uint32 distance;
10591  sscanf(text.c_str(), "distance:%u", &distance);
10592  if (distance > 0 && distance <= m_mgr.m_confCollectDistanceMax)
10593  {
10594  m_collectDist = distance;
10595  std::ostringstream oss;
10596  oss << "I will now collect items within " << m_collectDist << " yards.";
10597  SendWhisper(oss.str(), fromPlayer);
10598  }
10599  else
10600  {
10601  m_collectDist = m_mgr.m_confCollectDistanceMax;
10602  std::stringstream oss;
10603  oss << "I will now collect items within " << m_mgr.m_confCollectDistanceMax << " yards. " << distance << " yards is just too far away.",
10604  SendWhisper(oss.str(), fromPlayer);
10605  }
10606  }
10607  else if (ExtractCommand("none", text) || ExtractCommand("nothing", text))
10608  {
10609  m_collectionFlags = 0;
10610  m_collectObjects.clear();
10611  break; // because none is an exclusive choice
10612  }
10613  else
10614  {
10615  std::ostringstream oss;
10616  oss << "Collect <collectable(s)>: none | distance:<1-" << m_mgr.m_confCollectDistanceMax << ">, combat, loot, quest, profession, objects";
10617  if (m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_SKINNING))
10618  oss << ", skin";
10619  // TODO: perhaps change the command syntax, this way may be lacking in ease of use
10620  SendWhisper(oss.str(), fromPlayer);
10621  break;
10622  }
10623  }
10624 
10625  std::string collset = "";
10626  if (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_LOOT))
10627  collset += ", all loot";
10628  if (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_PROFESSION))
10629  collset += ", profession";
10630  if (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_QUEST))
10631  collset += ", quest";
10632  if (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_SKIN))
10633  collset += ", skin";
10634  if (collset.length() > 1)
10635  {
10636  if (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_COMBAT))
10637  collset += " items after combat";
10638  else
10639  collset += " items";
10640  }
10641 
10642  if (HasCollectFlag(COLLECT_FLAG_NEAROBJECT))
10643  {
10644  if (collset.length() > 1)
10645  collset += " and ";
10646  else
10647  collset += " "; // padding for substr
10648  collset += "nearby objects (";
10649  if (!m_collectObjects.empty())
10650  {
10651  std::string strobjects = "";
10652  for (BotEntryList::iterator itr = m_collectObjects.begin(); itr != m_collectObjects.end(); ++itr)
10653  {
10654  uint32 objectentry = *(itr);
10655  GameObjectInfo const* gInfo = ObjectMgr::GetGameObjectInfo(objectentry);
10656  strobjects += ", ";
10657  strobjects += gInfo->name;
10658  }
10659  collset += strobjects.substr(2);
10660  }
10661  else
10662  collset += "use survey and get to set";
10663  collset += ")";
10664  }
10665 
10666  if (collset.length() > 1)
10667  SendWhisper("I'm collecting " + collset.substr(2), fromPlayer);
10668  else
10669  SendWhisper("I'm collecting nothing.", fromPlayer);
10670 }

10672 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandEnchant(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
10673 {
10674  // DEBUG_LOG("Enchant (%s)",text.c_str());
10675 
10676  if (!m_bot->HasSkill(SKILL_ENCHANTING))
10677  {
10678  SendWhisper("|cffff0000I can't enchant, I don't have the skill.", fromPlayer);
10679  return;
10680  }
10681 
10682  if (text.size() > 0)
10683  {
10684  uint32 spellId;
10685  extractSpellId(text, spellId);
10686 
10687  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
10688  if (!spellInfo)
10689  return;
10690 
10691  std::list<uint32> itemIds;
10692  std::list<Item*> itemList;
10693  extractItemIds(text, itemIds);
10694  findItemsInEquip(itemIds, itemList);
10695  findItemsInInv(itemIds, itemList);
10696 
10697  if (itemList.empty())
10698  {
10699  SendWhisper("|cffff0000I can't enchant that!", fromPlayer);
10700  return;
10701  }
10702 
10703  Item* iTarget = itemList.back();
10704  itemList.pop_back();
10705 
10706  if (iTarget)
10707  {
10708  SpellCastTargets targets;
10709  targets.setItemTarget(iTarget);
10710  Spell* spell = new Spell(m_bot, spellInfo, false);
10711  spell->SpellStart(&targets);
10712  SetState(BOTSTATE_DELAYED);
10713  SetIgnoreUpdateTime(1);
10714  }
10715  return;
10716  }
10717  else
10718  {
10719  std::ostringstream msg;
10720  uint32 charges;
10721  uint32 linkcount = 0;
10722 
10723  m_spellsToLearn.clear();
10724  m_bot->skill(m_spellsToLearn);
10725  SendWhisper("I can enchant:\n", fromPlayer);
10726  ChatHandler ch(&fromPlayer);
10727  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = m_spellsToLearn.begin(); it != m_spellsToLearn.end(); ++it)
10728  {
10729  SkillLineEntry const* SkillLine = sSkillLineStore.LookupEntry(*it);
10730 
10731  if (SkillLine->categoryId == SKILL_CATEGORY_PROFESSION && *it == SKILL_ENCHANTING)
10732  for (uint32 j = 0; j < sSkillLineAbilityStore.GetNumRows(); ++j)
10733  {
10734  SkillLineAbilityEntry const* SkillAbility = sSkillLineAbilityStore.LookupEntry(j);
10735  if (!SkillAbility)
10736  continue;
10737 
10738  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(SkillAbility->spellId);
10739  if (!spellInfo)
10740  continue;
10741 
10742  if (IsPrimaryProfessionSkill(*it) && spellInfo->Effect[EFFECT_INDEX_0] != SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_ITEM)
10743  continue;
10744 
10745  if (SkillAbility->skillId == *it && m_bot->HasSpell(SkillAbility->spellId) && SkillAbility->forward_spellid == 0 && ((SkillAbility->classmask & m_bot->getClassMask()) == 0))
10746  {
10747  MakeSpellLink(spellInfo, msg);
10748  ++linkcount;
10749  if ((charges = GetSpellCharges(SkillAbility->spellId)) > 0)
10750  msg << "[" << charges << "]";
10751  if (linkcount >= 10)
10752  {
10753  ch.SendSysMessage(msg.str().c_str());
10754  linkcount = 0;
10755  msg.str("");
10756  }
10757  }
10758  }
10759  }
10760  m_noToolList.unique();
10761  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = m_noToolList.begin(); it != m_noToolList.end(); it++)
10762  HasTool(*it);
10763  ch.SendSysMessage(msg.str().c_str());
10764  m_noToolList.clear();
10765  m_spellsToLearn.clear();
10766  }
10767 }

10951  if (SkillAbility->skillId == *it && m_bot->HasSpell(SkillAbility->spellId) && SkillAbility->forward_spellid == 0 && ((SkillAbility->classmask & m_bot->getClassMask()) == 0))

10971  m_spellsToLearn.clear();

10974 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandQuest(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
10975 {
10976  std::ostringstream msg;
10977 
10978  if (ExtractCommand("add", text, true)) // true -> "quest add" OR "quest a"
10979  {
10980  FollowAutoReset();
10981  std::list<uint32> questIds;
10982  extractQuestIds(text, questIds);
10983  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = questIds.begin(); it != questIds.end(); it++)
10984  m_tasks.push_back(std::pair<enum TaskFlags, uint32>(TAKE_QUEST, *it));
10985  m_findNPC.push_back(UNIT_NPC_FLAG_QUESTGIVER);
10986  }
10987  else if (ExtractCommand("drop", text, true)) // true -> "quest drop" OR "quest d"
10988  {
10989  fromPlayer.SetSelectionGuid(m_bot->GetObjectGuid());
10990  PlayerbotChatHandler ch(GetMaster());
10991  int8 linkStart = text.find("|");
10992  if (text.find("|") != std::string::npos)
10993  {
10994  if (!ch.dropQuest((char*) text.substr(linkStart).c_str()))
10995  {
10996  ch.sysmessage("ERROR: could not drop quest");
10997  }
10998  else
10999  {
11000  SetQuestNeedItems();
11001  SetQuestNeedCreatures();
11002  }
11003  }
11004  }
11005  else if (ExtractCommand("fetch", text, true)) // true -> "quest fetch"
11006  {
11007  FollowAutoReset();
11008  gQuestFetch = 1;
11009  m_tasks.push_back(std::pair<enum TaskFlags, uint32>(LIST_QUEST, 0));
11010  m_findNPC.push_back(UNIT_NPC_FLAG_QUESTGIVER);
11011  }
11012  else if (ExtractCommand("list", text, true)) // true -> "quest list" OR "quest l"
11013  {
11014  FollowAutoReset();
11015  m_tasks.push_back(std::pair<enum TaskFlags, uint32>(LIST_QUEST, 0));
11016  m_findNPC.push_back(UNIT_NPC_FLAG_QUESTGIVER);
11017  }
11018  else if (ExtractCommand("report", text))
11019  SendQuestNeedList();
11020  else if (ExtractCommand("end", text, true)) // true -> "quest end" OR "quest e"
11021  {
11022  FollowAutoReset();
11023  m_tasks.push_back(std::pair<enum TaskFlags, uint32>(END_QUEST, 0));
11024  m_findNPC.push_back(UNIT_NPC_FLAG_QUESTGIVER);
11025  }
11026  else if (ExtractCommand("complete", text))
11027  {
11028  ChatHandler ch(&fromPlayer);
11029 
11030  std::list<uint32> questIds;
11031  extractQuestIds(text, questIds);
11032 
11033  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = questIds.begin(); it != questIds.end(); it++)
11034  {
11035  uint32 entry = *it;
11036 
11037  Quest const* pQuest = sObjectMgr.GetQuestTemplate(entry);
11038  if (!pQuest)
11039  continue;
11040 
11041  // Compare quest entry from [Quest Link] with quest ids listed DB table
11042  // if found the quest is autocompleted
11043  QueryResult* result = CharacterDatabase.PQuery("SELECT * FROM playerbot_quest_data WHERE autocomplete='%u'", entry);
11044  if (!result)
11045  {
11046  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, msg);
11047  msg << " can't be autocompleted\n";
11048  continue;
11049  }
11050  else
11051  {
11052  Group::MemberSlotList const& groupSlot = GetMaster()->GetGroup()->GetMemberSlots();
11053  for (Group::member_citerator itr = groupSlot.begin(); itr != groupSlot.end(); itr++)
11054  {
11055  Player* groupMember = sObjectMgr.GetPlayer(itr->guid);
11056 
11057  // If bot doesn't have the quest
11058  if (groupMember->GetQuestStatus(entry) == QUEST_STATUS_NONE)
11059  {
11060  msg << "|cFFD569CE[|r" << groupMember->GetName() << "|cFFD569CE]|r doesn't have that quest\n";
11061  continue;
11062  }
11063 
11064  // Add quest items for quests that require items
11065  for (uint8 x = 0; x < QUEST_ITEM_OBJECTIVES_COUNT; ++x)
11066  {
11067  uint32 id = pQuest->ReqItemId[x];
11068  uint32 count = pQuest->ReqItemCount[x];
11069  if (!id || !count)
11070  continue;
11071 
11072  uint32 curItemCount = groupMember->GetItemCount(id, true);
11073 
11074  ItemPosCountVec dest;
11075  uint8 res = groupMember->CanStoreNewItem(NULL_BAG, NULL_SLOT, dest, id, count - curItemCount);
11076  if (res == EQUIP_ERR_OK)
11077  {
11078  Item* item = groupMember->StoreNewItem(dest, id, true);
11079  groupMember->SendNewItem(item, count - curItemCount, true, false);
11080  }
11081  }
11082 
11083  // All creature/GO slain/casted (not required, but otherwise it will display "Creature slain 0/10")
11084  for (uint8 i = 0; i < QUEST_OBJECTIVES_COUNT; ++i)
11085  {
11086  int32 creature = pQuest->ReqCreatureOrGOId[i];
11087  uint32 creaturecount = pQuest->ReqCreatureOrGOCount[i];
11088 
11089  if (uint32 spell_id = pQuest->ReqSpell[i])
11090  {
11091  for (uint16 z = 0; z < creaturecount; ++z)
11092  groupMember->CastedCreatureOrGO(creature, ObjectGuid(), spell_id);
11093  }
11094  else if (creature > 0)
11095  {
11096  if (CreatureInfo const* cInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(creature))
11097  for (uint16 z = 0; z < creaturecount; ++z)
11098  groupMember->KilledMonster(cInfo, nullptr);
11099  }
11100  else if (creature < 0)
11101  {
11102  for (uint16 z = 0; z < creaturecount; ++z)
11103  groupMember->CastedCreatureOrGO(-creature, ObjectGuid(), 0);
11104  }
11105  }
11106 
11107  // If the quest requires reputation to complete
11108  if (uint32 repFaction = pQuest->GetRepObjectiveFaction())
11109  {
11110  uint32 repValue = pQuest->GetRepObjectiveValue();
11111  uint32 curRep = groupMember->GetReputationMgr().GetReputation(repFaction);
11112  if (curRep < repValue)
11113  if (FactionEntry const* factionEntry = sFactionStore.LookupEntry(repFaction))
11114  groupMember->GetReputationMgr().SetReputation(factionEntry, repValue);
11115  }
11116 
11117  // If the quest requires money
11118  int32 ReqOrRewMoney = pQuest->GetRewOrReqMoney();
11119  if (ReqOrRewMoney < 0)
11120  groupMember->ModifyMoney(-ReqOrRewMoney);
11121 
11122  groupMember->CompleteQuest(entry);
11123  msg << "|cFFD569CE[|r" << groupMember->GetName() << "|cFFD569CE]|r completed quest ";
11124  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, msg);
11125  msg << "\n";
11126  }
11127  delete result;
11128  }
11129  }
11130  ch.SendSysMessage(msg.str().c_str());
11131  }
11132  else
11133  {
11134  bool hasIncompleteQuests = false;
11135  std::ostringstream incomout;
11136  incomout << "my incomplete quests are:";
11137  bool hasCompleteQuests = false;
11138  std::ostringstream comout;
11139  comout << "my complete quests are:";
11140  for (uint16 slot = 0; slot < MAX_QUEST_LOG_SIZE; ++slot)
11141  {
11142  if (uint32 questId = m_bot->GetQuestSlotQuestId(slot))
11143  {
11144  Quest const* pQuest = sObjectMgr.GetQuestTemplate(questId);
11145 
11146  if (m_bot->GetQuestStatus(questId) == QUEST_STATUS_COMPLETE)
11147  {
11148  hasCompleteQuests = true;
11149  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, comout);
11150  }
11151  else
11152  {
11153  Item* qitem = FindItem(pQuest->GetSrcItemId());
11154  if (qitem)
11155  {
11156  incomout << " use ";
11157  MakeItemLink(qitem->GetProto(), incomout);
11158  incomout << " on ";
11159  }
11160  hasIncompleteQuests = true;
11161  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, incomout);
11162  }
11163  }
11164  }
11165  if (hasCompleteQuests)
11166  SendWhisper(comout.str(), fromPlayer);
11167  if (hasIncompleteQuests)
11168  SendWhisper(incomout.str(), fromPlayer);
11169  if (!hasCompleteQuests && !hasIncompleteQuests)
11170  SendWhisper("I have no quests.", fromPlayer);
11171  }
11172 }
11173 
11174 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandPet(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
11175 {
11176  if (ExtractCommand("tame", text))
11177  {
11178  if (m_bot->GetPetGuid())
11179  {
11180  SendWhisper("I already have a pet!", fromPlayer);
11181  return;
11182  }
11183 
11184  ObjectGuid castOnGuid = fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid();
11185  if (castOnGuid && m_bot->HasSpell(TAME_BEAST_1))
11186  {
11187  if (ASPECT_OF_THE_MONKEY > 0 && !m_bot->HasAura(ASPECT_OF_THE_MONKEY, EFFECT_INDEX_0))
11188  CastSpell(ASPECT_OF_THE_MONKEY, *m_bot);
11189  m_targetGuidCommand = castOnGuid;
11190  SetState(BOTSTATE_TAME);
11191  }
11192  else
11193  SendWhisper("I can't tame that!", fromPlayer);
11194  return;
11195  }
11196 
11197  Pet* pet = m_bot->GetPet();
11198  if (!pet)
11199  {
11200  SendWhisper("I have no pet.", fromPlayer);
11201  return;
11202  }
11203 
11204  if (ExtractCommand("abandon", text))
11205  {
11206  // abandon pet
11207  std::unique_ptr<WorldPacket> packet(new WorldPacket(CMSG_PET_ABANDON, 8));
11208  *packet << pet->GetObjectGuid();
11209  m_bot->GetSession()->QueuePacket(std::move(packet));
11210 
11211  }
11212  else if (ExtractCommand("react", text))
11213  {
11214  if (ExtractCommand("aggressive", text, true))
11215  pet->AI()->SetReactState(REACT_AGGRESSIVE);
11216  else if (ExtractCommand("defensive", text, true))
11217  pet->AI()->SetReactState(REACT_DEFENSIVE);
11218  else if (ExtractCommand("passive", text, true))
11219  pet->AI()->SetReactState(REACT_PASSIVE);
11220  else
11221  _HandleCommandHelp("pet react", fromPlayer);
11222  }
11223  else if (ExtractCommand("state", text))
11224  {
11225  if (!text.empty())
11226  {
11227  SendWhisper("'pet state' does not support subcommands.", fromPlayer);
11228  return;
11229  }
11230 
11231  if(!pet || !pet->AI())
11232  return;
11233 
11234  switch (pet->AI()->GetReactState())
11235  {
11236  case REACT_AGGRESSIVE:
11237  SendWhisper("My pet is aggressive.", fromPlayer);
11238  break;
11239  case REACT_DEFENSIVE:
11240  SendWhisper("My pet is defensive.", fromPlayer);
11241  break;
11242  case REACT_PASSIVE:
11243  SendWhisper("My pet is passive.", fromPlayer);
11244  }
11245  }
11246  else if (ExtractCommand("cast", text))
11247  {
11248  if (text.empty())
11249  {
11250  _HandleCommandHelp("pet cast", fromPlayer);
11251  return;
11252  }
11253 
11254  if(!pet)
11255  return;
11256 
11257  uint32 spellId = (uint32) atol(text.c_str());
11258 
11259  if (spellId == 0)
11260  {
11261  spellId = getPetSpellId(text.c_str());
11262  if (spellId == 0)
11263  extractSpellId(text, spellId);
11264  }
11265 
11266  if (spellId != 0 && pet->HasSpell(spellId))
11267  {
11268  if (pet->HasAura(spellId))
11269  {
11270  pet->RemoveAurasByCasterSpell(spellId, pet->GetObjectGuid());
11271  return;
11272  }
11273 
11274  ObjectGuid castOnGuid = fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid();
11275  Unit* pTarget = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_bot, castOnGuid);
11276  CastPetSpell(spellId, pTarget);
11277  }
11278  }
11279  else if (ExtractCommand("toggle", text))
11280  {
11281  if (text.empty())
11282  {
11283  _HandleCommandHelp("pet toggle", fromPlayer);
11284  return;
11285  }
11286 
11287  if(!pet)
11288  return;
11289 
11290  uint32 spellId = (uint32) atol(text.c_str());
11291 
11292  if (spellId == 0)
11293  {
11294  spellId = getPetSpellId(text.c_str());
11295  if (spellId == 0)
11296  extractSpellId(text, spellId);
11297  }
11298 
11299  if (spellId != 0 && pet->HasSpell(spellId))
11300  {
11301  PetSpellMap::iterator itr = pet->m_spells.find(spellId);
11302  if (itr != pet->m_spells.end())
11303  {
11304  if (itr->second.active == ACT_ENABLED)
11305  {
11306  pet->ToggleAutocast(spellId, false);
11307  if (pet->HasAura(spellId))
11308  pet->RemoveAurasByCasterSpell(spellId, pet->GetObjectGuid());
11309  }
11310  else
11311  pet->ToggleAutocast(spellId, true);
11312  }
11313  }
11314  }
11315  else if (ExtractCommand("spells", text))
11316  {
11317  if (!text.empty())
11318  {
11319  SendWhisper("'pet spells' does not support subcommands.", fromPlayer);
11320  return;
11321  }
11322 
11323  if(!pet)
11324  return;
11325 
11326  int loc = GetMaster()->GetSession()->GetSessionDbcLocale();
11327 
11328  std::ostringstream posOut;
11329  std::ostringstream negOut;
11330 
11331  for (PetSpellMap::iterator itr = pet->m_spells.begin(); itr != pet->m_spells.end(); ++itr)
11332  {
11333  const uint32 spellId = itr->first;
11334 
11335  if (itr->second.state == PETSPELL_REMOVED || IsPassiveSpell(spellId))
11336  continue;
11337 
11338  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
11339  if (!pSpellInfo)
11340  continue;
11341 
11342  std::string color;
11343  switch (itr->second.active)
11344  {
11345  case ACT_ENABLED:
11346  color = "cff35d22d"; // Some flavor of green
11347  break;
11348  default:
11349  color = "cffffffff";
11350  }
11351 
11352  if (IsPositiveSpell(spellId))
11353  posOut << " |" << color << "|Hspell:" << spellId << "|h["
11354  << pSpellInfo->SpellName[loc] << "]|h|r";
11355  else
11356  negOut << " |" << color << "|Hspell:" << spellId << "|h["
11357  << pSpellInfo->SpellName[loc] << "]|h|r";
11358  }
11359 
11360  ChatHandler ch(&fromPlayer);
11361  SendWhisper("Here's my pet's non-attack spells:", fromPlayer);
11362  ch.SendSysMessage(posOut.str().c_str());
11363  SendWhisper("and here's my pet's attack spells:", fromPlayer);
11364  ch.SendSysMessage(negOut.str().c_str());
11365  }
11366 }
11367 
11368 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandSpells(std::string& /*text*/, Player& fromPlayer)
11369 {
11370  int loc = GetMaster()->GetSession()->GetSessionDbcLocale();
11371 
11372  std::ostringstream posOut;
11373  std::ostringstream negOut;
11374 
11375  typedef std::map<std::string, uint32> spellMap;
11376 
11377  spellMap posSpells, negSpells;
11378  std::string spellName;
11379 
11380  uint32 ignoredSpells[] = {1843, 5019, 2479, 6603, 3365, 8386, 21651, 21652, 6233, 6246, 6247,
11381  61437, 22810, 22027, 45927, 7266, 7267, 6477, 6478, 7355, 68398
11382  };
11383  uint32 ignoredSpellsCount = sizeof(ignoredSpells) / sizeof(uint32);
11384 
11385  for (PlayerSpellMap::iterator itr = m_bot->GetSpellMap().begin(); itr != m_bot->GetSpellMap().end(); ++itr)
11386  {
11387  const uint32 spellId = itr->first;
11388 
11389  if (itr->second.state == PLAYERSPELL_REMOVED || itr->second.disabled || IsPassiveSpell(spellId))
11390  continue;
11391 
11392  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
11393  if (!pSpellInfo)
11394  continue;
11395 
11396  spellName = pSpellInfo->SpellName[loc];
11397 
11398  SkillLineAbilityMapBounds const bounds = sSpellMgr.GetSkillLineAbilityMapBoundsBySpellId(spellId);
11399 
11400  bool isProfessionOrRidingSpell = false;
11401  for (SkillLineAbilityMap::const_iterator skillIter = bounds.first; skillIter != bounds.second; ++skillIter)
11402  {
11403  if (IsProfessionOrRidingSkill(skillIter->second->skillId) && skillIter->first == spellId)
11404  {
11405  isProfessionOrRidingSpell = true;
11406  break;
11407  }
11408  }
11409  if (isProfessionOrRidingSpell)
11410  continue;
11411 
11412  bool isIgnoredSpell = false;
11413  for (uint8 i = 0; i < ignoredSpellsCount; ++i)
11414  {
11415  if (spellId == ignoredSpells[i])
11416  {
11417  isIgnoredSpell = true;
11418  break;
11419  }
11420  }
11421  if (isIgnoredSpell)
11422  continue;
11423 
11424  if (IsPositiveSpell(spellId))
11425  {
11426  if (posSpells.find(spellName) == posSpells.end())
11427  posSpells[spellName] = spellId;
11428  else if (posSpells[spellName] < spellId)
11429  posSpells[spellName] = spellId;
11430  }
11431  else
11432  {
11433  if (negSpells.find(spellName) == negSpells.end())
11434  negSpells[spellName] = spellId;
11435  else if (negSpells[spellName] < spellId)
11436  negSpells[spellName] = spellId;
11437  }
11438  }
11439 
11440  for (spellMap::const_iterator iter = posSpells.begin(); iter != posSpells.end(); ++iter)
11441  {
11442  posOut << " |cffffffff|Hspell:" << iter->second << "|h[" << iter->first << "]|h|r";
11443  }
11444 
11445  for (spellMap::const_iterator iter = negSpells.begin(); iter != negSpells.end(); ++iter)
11446  {
11447  negOut << " |cffffffff|Hspell:" << iter->second << "|h[" << iter->first << "]|h|r";
11448  }
11449 
11450  ChatHandler ch(&fromPlayer);
11451  SendWhisper("here's my non-attack spells:", fromPlayer);
11452  ch.SendSysMessage(posOut.str().c_str());
11453  SendWhisper("and here's my attack spells:", fromPlayer);
11454  ch.SendSysMessage(negOut.str().c_str());
11455 }
11456 
11457 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandSurvey(std::string& /*text*/, Player& fromPlayer)
11458 {
11459  uint32 count = 0;
11460  std::ostringstream detectout;
11461  QueryResult* result;
11462  GameEventMgr::ActiveEvents const& activeEventsList = sGameEventMgr.GetActiveEventList();
11463  std::ostringstream eventFilter;
11464  eventFilter << " AND (event IS NULL ";
11465  bool initString = true;
11466 
11467  for (GameEventMgr::ActiveEvents::const_iterator itr = activeEventsList.begin(); itr != activeEventsList.end(); ++itr)
11468  {
11469  if (initString)
11470  {
11471  eventFilter << "OR event IN (" << *itr;
11472  initString = false;
11473  }
11474  else
11475  eventFilter << "," << *itr;
11476  }
11477 
11478  if (!initString)
11479  eventFilter << "))";
11480  else
11481  eventFilter << ")";
11482 
11483  result = WorldDatabase.PQuery("SELECT gameobject.guid, id, position_x, position_y, position_z, map, "
11484  "(POW(position_x - %f, 2) + POW(position_y - %f, 2) + POW(position_z - %f, 2)) AS order_ FROM gameobject "
11485  "LEFT OUTER JOIN game_event_gameobject on gameobject.guid=game_event_gameobject.guid WHERE map = '%i' %s ORDER BY order_ ASC LIMIT 10",
11486  m_bot->GetPositionX(), m_bot->GetPositionY(), m_bot->GetPositionZ(), m_bot->GetMapId(), eventFilter.str().c_str());
11487 
11488  if (result)
11489  {
11490  do
11491  {
11492  Field* fields = result->Fetch();
11493  uint32 guid = fields[0].GetUInt32();
11494  uint32 entry = fields[1].GetUInt32();
11495 
11496  GameObject* go = m_bot->GetMap()->GetGameObject(ObjectGuid(HIGHGUID_GAMEOBJECT, entry, guid));
11497  if (!go)
11498  continue;
11499 
11500  if (!go->IsSpawned())
11501  continue;
11502 
11503  detectout << "|cFFFFFF00|Hfound:" << guid << ":" << entry << ":" << "|h[" << go->GetGOInfo()->name << "]|h|r";
11504  ++count;
11505  }
11506  while (result->NextRow());
11507 
11508  delete result;
11509  }
11510  SendWhisper(detectout.str().c_str(), fromPlayer);
11511 }
11512 
11513 // _HandleCommandSkill: Handle class & professions training:
11514 // skill -- Lists bot(s) Primary profession skills & weapon skills
11515 // skill learn -- List available class or profession (Primary or Secondary) skills, spells & abilities from selected trainer.
11516 // skill learn all -- Learn all skills and spells available from selected trainer.
11517 // skill learn [HLINK][HLINK] .. -- Learn selected skill and spells, from selected trainer ([HLINK] from skill learn).
11518 // skill unlearn [HLINK][HLINK] .. -- Unlearn selected primary profession skill(s) and all associated spells ([HLINK] from skill)
11519 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandSkill(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
11520 {
11521  uint32 rank[8] = {0, 75, 150, 225, 300, 375, 450, 525};
11522 
11523  std::ostringstream msg;
11524  if (ExtractCommand("learn", text))
11525  {
11526  uint32 totalCost = 0;
11527 
11528  Unit* unit = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_bot, fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid());
11529  if (!unit)
11530  {
11531  SendWhisper("Please select the trainer!", fromPlayer);
11532  return;
11533  }
11534 
11535  if (!unit->isTrainer())
11536  {
11537  SendWhisper("This is not a trainer!", fromPlayer);
11538  return;
11539  }
11540 
11541  Creature* creature = m_bot->GetMap()->GetCreature(fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid());
11542  if (!creature)
11543  return;
11544 
11545  if (!creature->IsTrainerOf(m_bot, false))
11546  {
11547  SendWhisper("This trainer can not teach me anything!", fromPlayer);
11548  return;
11549  }
11550 
11551  // check present spell in trainer spell list
11552  TrainerSpellData const* cSpells = creature->GetTrainerSpells();
11553  TrainerSpellData const* tSpells = creature->GetTrainerTemplateSpells();
11554  TrainerSpellMap allSpells;
11555 
11556  if (cSpells && tSpells)
11557  {
11558  allSpells.insert(cSpells->spellList.begin(), cSpells->spellList.end());
11559  allSpells.insert(tSpells->spellList.begin(), tSpells->spellList.end());
11560  }
11561  else if (cSpells)
11562  allSpells.insert(cSpells->spellList.begin(), cSpells->spellList.end());
11563  else if (tSpells)
11564  allSpells.insert(tSpells->spellList.begin(), tSpells->spellList.end());
11565  else
11566  {
11567  SendWhisper("No spells can be learnt from this trainer", fromPlayer);
11568  return;
11569  }
11570 
11571  // reputation discount
11572  float fDiscountMod = m_bot->GetReputationPriceDiscount(creature);
11573 
11574  // Handle: Learning class or profession (primary or secondary) skill & spell(s) for selected trainer, skill learn [HLINK][HLINK][HLINK].. ([HLINK] from skill train)
11575  if (text.size() > 0)
11576  {
11577  msg << "I have learned the following spells:\n";
11578  uint32 totalSpellLearnt = 0;
11579  bool visuals = true;
11580  m_spellsToLearn.clear();
11581  if (ExtractCommand("all", text))
11582  {
11583  for (TrainerSpellMap::const_iterator itr = allSpells.begin(); itr != allSpells.end(); ++itr)
11584  {
11585  TrainerSpell const* trainer_spell = &itr->second;
11586 
11587  uint32 spellId = trainer_spell->spell;
11588 
11589  if (!spellId)
11590  break;
11591 
11592  // apply reputation discount
11593  uint32 cost = uint32(floor(trainer_spell->spellCost * fDiscountMod));
11594  if (!_HandleCommandSkillLearnHelper(trainer_spell, spellId, cost))
11595  continue;
11596 
11597  ++totalSpellLearnt;
11598  totalCost += cost;
11599  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
11600  if (!pSpellInfo)
11601  continue;
11602 
11603  if (visuals)
11604  {
11605  visuals = false;
11606  WorldPacket data(SMSG_PLAY_SPELL_VISUAL, 12); // visual effect on trainer
11607  data << ObjectGuid(fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid());
11608  data << uint32(0xB3); // index from SpellVisualKit.dbc
11609  GetMaster()->GetSession()->SendPacket(data);
11610 
11611  data.Initialize(SMSG_PLAY_SPELL_IMPACT, 12); // visual effect on player
11612  data << m_bot->GetObjectGuid();
11613  data << uint32(0x016A); // index from SpellVisualKit.dbc
11614  GetMaster()->GetSession()->SendPacket(data);
11615  }
11616 
11617  WorldPacket data(SMSG_TRAINER_BUY_SUCCEEDED, 12);
11618  data << ObjectGuid(fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid());
11619  data << uint32(spellId); // should be same as in packet from client
11620  GetMaster()->GetSession()->SendPacket(data);
11621  MakeSpellLink(pSpellInfo, msg);
11622  msg << " ";
11623  msg << Cash(cost) << " ";
11624  }
11625  }
11626  else
11627  {
11628  extractSpellIdList(text, m_spellsToLearn);
11629 
11630  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = m_spellsToLearn.begin(); it != m_spellsToLearn.end(); it++)
11631  {
11632  uint32 spellId = *it;
11633 
11634  if (!spellId)
11635  break;
11636 
11637  // Try find spell in npc_trainer
11638  TrainerSpell const* trainer_spell = cSpells ? cSpells->Find(spellId) : nullptr;
11639 
11640  // Not found, try find in npc_trainer_template
11641  if (!trainer_spell && tSpells)
11642  trainer_spell = tSpells->Find(spellId);
11643 
11644  // apply reputation discount
11645  uint32 cost = uint32(floor(trainer_spell->spellCost * fDiscountMod));
11646 
11647  if (!_HandleCommandSkillLearnHelper(trainer_spell, spellId, cost))
11648  continue;
11649 
11650  ++totalSpellLearnt;
11651  totalCost += cost;
11652  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
11653  if (!pSpellInfo)
11654  continue;
11655 
11656  if (visuals)
11657  {
11658  visuals = false;
11659  WorldPacket data(SMSG_PLAY_SPELL_VISUAL, 12); // visual effect on trainer
11660  data << ObjectGuid(fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid());
11661  data << uint32(0xB3); // index from SpellVisualKit.dbc
11662  GetMaster()->GetSession()->SendPacket(data);
11663 
11664  data.Initialize(SMSG_PLAY_SPELL_IMPACT, 12); // visual effect on player
11665  data << m_bot->GetObjectGuid();
11666  data << uint32(0x016A); // index from SpellVisualKit.dbc
11667  GetMaster()->GetSession()->SendPacket(data);
11668  }
11669 
11670  WorldPacket data(SMSG_TRAINER_BUY_SUCCEEDED, 12);
11671  data << ObjectGuid(fromPlayer.GetSelectionGuid());
11672  data << uint32(spellId); // should be same as in packet from client
11673  GetMaster()->GetSession()->SendPacket(data);
11674  MakeSpellLink(pSpellInfo, msg);
11675  msg << " ";
11676  msg << Cash(cost) << " ";
11677  }
11678  }
11679  ReloadAI();
11680  if (totalSpellLearnt == 0) msg.clear();
11681  else msg << "\n";
11682  msg << "Total of " << totalSpellLearnt << " spell";
11683  if (totalSpellLearnt != 1) msg << "s";
11684  msg << " learnt, ";
11685  msg << Cash(totalCost) << " spent.";
11686  }
11687  // Handle: List class or profession skills, spells & abilities for selected trainer
11688  else
11689  {
11690  msg << "The spells I can learn and their cost:\r";
11691 
11692  for (TrainerSpellMap::const_iterator itr = allSpells.begin(); itr != allSpells.end(); ++itr)
11693  {
11694  TrainerSpell const* tSpell = &itr->second;
11695 
11696  if (!tSpell)
11697  break;
11698 
11699  uint32 reqLevel = 0;
11700  if (!tSpell->learnedSpell && !m_bot->IsSpellFitByClassAndRace(tSpell->learnedSpell, &reqLevel))
11701  continue;
11702 
11703  if (sSpellMgr.IsPrimaryProfessionFirstRankSpell(tSpell->learnedSpell) && m_bot->HasSpell(tSpell->learnedSpell))
11704  continue;
11705 
11706  reqLevel = tSpell->isProvidedReqLevel ? tSpell->reqLevel : std::max(reqLevel, tSpell->reqLevel);
11707 
11708  TrainerSpellState state = m_bot->GetTrainerSpellState(tSpell, reqLevel);
11709  if (state != TRAINER_SPELL_GREEN)
11710  continue;
11711 
11712  uint32 spellId = tSpell->spell;
11713  const SpellEntry* const pSpellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
11714  if (!pSpellInfo)
11715  continue;
11716  uint32 cost = uint32(floor(tSpell->spellCost * fDiscountMod));
11717  totalCost += cost;
11718  MakeSpellLink(pSpellInfo, msg);
11719  msg << " ";
11720  msg << Cash(cost) << " ";
11721  }
11722 
11723  if (totalCost == 0)
11724  {
11725  msg.clear();
11726  msg << "I have learned all I can from this trainer. Perhaps I can learn more once I grow stronger.";
11727  }
11728  else
11729  {
11730  int32 moneyDiff = m_bot->GetMoney() - totalCost;
11731  if (moneyDiff >= 0)
11732  msg << "\n" << Cash(moneyDiff) << " left after learning all the spells.";
11733  else
11734  {
11735  Announce(CANT_AFFORD);
11736  moneyDiff *= -1;
11737  msg << "\nI need " << Cash(moneyDiff) << " more to learn all the spells!";
11738  }
11739  }
11740  }
11741  }
11742  // Handle: Unlearning selected primary profession skill(s) and all associated spells, skill unlearn [HLINK][HLINK].. ([HLINK] from skill)
11743  else if (ExtractCommand("unlearn", text))
11744  {
11745  m_spellsToLearn.clear();
11746  extractSpellIdList(text, m_spellsToLearn);
11747  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = m_spellsToLearn.begin(); it != m_spellsToLearn.end(); ++it)
11748  {
11749  if (sSpellMgr.IsPrimaryProfessionSpell(*it))
11750  {
11751  SpellLearnSkillNode const* spellLearnSkill = sSpellMgr.GetSpellLearnSkill(*it);
11752 
11753  uint32 prev_spell = sSpellMgr.GetPrevSpellInChain(*it);
11754  if (!prev_spell) // first rank, remove skill
11755  GetPlayer()->SetSkill(spellLearnSkill->skill, 0, 0);
11756  else
11757  {
11758  // search prev. skill setting by spell ranks chain
11759  SpellLearnSkillNode const* prevSkill = sSpellMgr.GetSpellLearnSkill(prev_spell);
11760  while (!prevSkill && prev_spell)
11761  {
11762  prev_spell = sSpellMgr.GetPrevSpellInChain(prev_spell);
11763  prevSkill = sSpellMgr.GetSpellLearnSkill(sSpellMgr.GetFirstSpellInChain(prev_spell));
11764  }
11765  if (!prevSkill) // not found prev skill setting, remove skill
11766  GetPlayer()->SetSkill(spellLearnSkill->skill, 0, 0);
11767  }
11768  }
11769  }
11770  }
11771  // Handle: Lists bot(s) primary profession skills & weapon skills.
11772  else
11773  {
11774  m_spellsToLearn.clear();
11775  m_bot->skill(m_spellsToLearn);
11776  msg << "My Primary Professions: ";
11777  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = m_spellsToLearn.begin(); it != m_spellsToLearn.end(); ++it)
11778  {
11779  if (IsPrimaryProfessionSkill(*it))
11780  for (uint32 j = 0; j < sSkillLineAbilityStore.GetNumRows(); ++j)
11781  {
11782  SkillLineAbilityEntry const* skillLine = sSkillLineAbilityStore.LookupEntry(j);
11783  if (!skillLine)
11784  continue;
11785 
11786  // has skill
11787  if (skillLine->skillId == *it && skillLine->learnOnGetSkill == 0)
11788  {
11789  uint32 SpellId;
11790  m_bot->HasSpell(skillLine->forward_spellid) ? SpellId = skillLine->forward_spellid : SpellId = skillLine->spellId;
11791 
11792  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(SpellId);
11793  if (!spellInfo)
11794  continue;
11795 
11796  if (m_bot->GetSkillValue(*it) <= rank[sSpellMgr.GetSpellRank(SpellId)] && m_bot->HasSpell(SpellId))
11797  {
11798  // DEBUG_LOG ("[PlayerbotAI]: HandleCommand - skill (%u)(%u)(%u):",skillLine->spellId, rank[sSpellMgr.GetSpellRank(skillLine->spellId)], m_bot->GetSkillValue(*it));
11799  msg << "\n[" << m_bot->GetSkillValue(*it) << " / " << rank[sSpellMgr.GetSpellRank(SpellId)] << "]: ";
11800  MakeSpellLink(spellInfo, msg);
11801  break;
11802  }
11803  }
11804  }
11805  }
11806 
11807  msg << "\nMy Weapon skills: ";
11808  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = m_spellsToLearn.begin(); it != m_spellsToLearn.end(); ++it)
11809  {
11810  SkillLineEntry const* SkillLine = sSkillLineStore.LookupEntry(*it);
11811  // has weapon skill
11812  if (SkillLine->categoryId == SKILL_CATEGORY_WEAPON)
11813  for (uint32 j = 0; j < sSkillLineAbilityStore.GetNumRows(); ++j)
11814  {
11815  SkillLineAbilityEntry const* skillLine = sSkillLineAbilityStore.LookupEntry(j);
11816  if (!skillLine)
11817  continue;
11818 
11819  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(skillLine->spellId);
11820  if (!spellInfo)
11821  continue;
11822 
11823  if (skillLine->skillId == *it && spellInfo->Effect[0] == SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON)
11824  MakeWeaponSkillLink(spellInfo, msg, *it);
11825  }
11826  }
11827  }
11828  SendWhisper(msg.str(), fromPlayer);
11829  m_spellsToLearn.clear();
11830  m_bot->GetPlayerbotAI()->GetClassAI();
11831 }
11832 
11833 bool PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandSkillLearnHelper(TrainerSpell const* tSpell, uint32 spellId, uint32 cost)
11834 {
11835  // Not found anywhere, cheating?
11836  if (!tSpell)
11837  return false;
11838 
11839  uint32 reqLevel = 0;
11840  if (!tSpell->learnedSpell && !m_bot->IsSpellFitByClassAndRace(tSpell->learnedSpell, &reqLevel))
11841  return false;
11842 
11843  if (sSpellMgr.IsPrimaryProfessionFirstRankSpell(tSpell->learnedSpell) && m_bot->HasSpell(tSpell->learnedSpell))
11844  return false;
11845 
11846  reqLevel = tSpell->isProvidedReqLevel ? tSpell->reqLevel : std::max(reqLevel, tSpell->reqLevel);
11847 
11848  TrainerSpellState state = m_bot->GetTrainerSpellState(tSpell, reqLevel);
11849  if (state != TRAINER_SPELL_GREEN)
11850  return false;
11851 
11852  // check money requirement
11853  if (m_bot->GetMoney() < cost)
11854  {
11855  Announce(CANT_AFFORD);
11856  return false;
11857  }
11858 
11859  m_bot->ModifyMoney(-int32(cost));
11860  // learn explicitly
11861  m_bot->learnSpell(spellId, false);
11862 
11863  return true;
11864 }

11866 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandStats(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
11867 {
11868  if (!text.empty())
11869  {
11870  SendWhisper("'stats' does not have subcommands", fromPlayer);
11871  return;
11872  }
11873 
11874  std::ostringstream out;
11875 
11876  uint32 totalfree = GetFreeBagSpace();
11877 
11878  // estimate how much item damage the bot has
11879  out << "|cffffffff[|h|cff00ffff" << m_bot->GetName() << "|h|cffffffff] has |cff00ff00";
11880  out << totalfree << " |h|cffffffff bag slots,|h" << " |cff00ff00";
11881  out << Cash(EstRepairAll());
11882 
11883  // calculate how much money bot has
11884  uint32 copper = m_bot->GetMoney();
11885  out << "|h|cffffffff item damage & has " << "|r|cff00ff00";
11886  out << Cash(copper);
11887  ChatHandler ch(&fromPlayer);
11888  ch.SendSysMessage(out.str().c_str());
11889 }

11891 void PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandGM(std::string& text, Player& fromPlayer)
11892 {
11893  // Check should happen OUTSIDE this function, but this is account security we're talking about, so let's be doubly sure
11894  if (fromPlayer.GetSession()->GetSecurity() <= SEC_PLAYER)
11895  return; // no excuses, no warning
11896 
11897  if (text.empty())
11898  {
11899  SendWhisper("gm must have a subcommand.", fromPlayer);
11900  return;
11901  }
11902  else if (ExtractCommand("quest", text))
11903  {
11904  std::ostringstream out;
11905  ChatHandler ch(&fromPlayer);
11906 
11907  size_t add = text.find("add");
11908  size_t del = text.find("del");
11909 
11910  std::list<uint32> questIds;
11911  extractQuestIds(text, questIds);
11912 
11913  for (std::list<uint32>::iterator it = questIds.begin(); it != questIds.end(); it++)
11914  {
11915 
11916  uint32 entry = *it;
11917 
11918  Quest const* pQuest = sObjectMgr.GetQuestTemplate(entry);
11919 
11920  if (!pQuest)
11921  {
11922  out << "quest [" << entry << "] not found\n";
11923  continue;
11924  }
11925 
11926  //check whether entry is already in database
11927  QueryResult* result = CharacterDatabase.PQuery("SELECT * FROM playerbot_quest_data WHERE autocomplete='%u'", entry);
11928 
11929  if (add != std::string::npos)
11930  {
11931  if (!result)
11932  {
11933  // add new entry
11934  out << "adding quest ";
11935  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, out);
11936  out << " to table\n";
11937  CharacterDatabase.DirectPExecute("INSERT INTO playerbot_quest_data (autocomplete) VALUES('%u')", entry);
11938  }
11939  else
11940  {
11941  // entry found in table
11942  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, out);
11943  out << " already in table\n";
11944  delete result;
11945  continue;
11946  }
11947  }
11948  else if (del != std::string::npos)
11949  {
11950  if (result)
11951  {
11952  // delete entry
11953  out << "deleting ";
11954  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, out);
11955  out << " from table\n";
11956  CharacterDatabase.DirectPExecute("DELETE FROM playerbot_quest_data WHERE autocomplete='%u'", entry);
11957  delete result;
11958  }
11959  else
11960  {
11961  // entry not found in table
11962  MakeQuestLink(pQuest, out);
11963  out << " not in table\n";
11964  continue;
11965  }
11966  }
11967  else
11968  {
11969  out << "'gm quest' does not have that subcommand.";
11970  break;
11971  }
11972  }
11973  ch.SendSysMessage(out.str().c_str());
11974  }
11975  else if (ExtractCommand("check", text))
11976  {
11977  if (ExtractCommand("talent", text))
11978  {
11979  if (ExtractCommand("spec", text))
11980  {
11981  uint32 tsDBError = TalentSpecDBContainsError();
11982  if (0 != tsDBError)
11983  {
11984  std::ostringstream oss;
11985  oss << "Error found in TalentSpec: " << tsDBError;
11986  SendWhisper(oss.str(), fromPlayer);
11987  }
11988  else
11989  SendWhisper("No errors found. High five!", fromPlayer);
11990  }
11991  }
11992  else
11993  SendWhisper("'gm check' does not have that subcommand.", fromPlayer);
11994  }
11995  else if (ExtractCommand("target", text))
11996  {
11997  if (ExtractCommand("combat", text))
11998  {
11999  for (AttackerInfoList::iterator i = m_attackerInfo.begin(); i != m_attackerInfo.end(); ++i)
12000  DEBUG_LOG("[Attacker]:{ %s, victim:%s, threat:%.2f, highest-threat:%.2f, count:%d }",
12001  i->second.attacker->GetName(),
12002  i->second.victim->GetName(),
12003  i->second.threat,
12004  i->second.threat2,
12005  i->second.count);
12006  DEBUG_LOG("[Attacker]:{ };");
12007  }
12008  else if (ExtractCommand("loot", text))
12009  {
12010  for (std::list<ObjectGuid>::iterator it = m_lootTargets.begin(); it != m_lootTargets.end(); ++it)
12011  DEBUG_LOG("[Looter]:{ %s loots [%s] }", m_bot->GetName(), (*it).GetString().c_str());
12012  DEBUG_LOG("[Looter]:{ }");
12013  }
12014  else
12015  SendWhisper("'gm target' does not have that subcommand.", fromPlayer);
12016  }
12017  else if (ExtractCommand("chat", text))
12018  {
12019  m_bDebugCommandChat = !m_bDebugCommandChat;
12020  if (m_bDebugCommandChat)
12021  SendWhisper("I will now output all commands received.", fromPlayer);
12022  else
12023  SendWhisper("I will no longer output commands received.", fromPlayer);
12024  }
12025  else
12026  SendWhisper("'gm' does not have that subcommand.", fromPlayer);
12027 }

12610 
12611 std::string PlayerbotAI::_HandleCommandHelpHelper(std::string sCommand, std::string sExplain, HELPERLINKABLES reqLink, bool bReqLinkMultiples, bool bCommandShort)
12612 {
12613  if (sCommand.empty())
12614  {
12615  DEBUG_LOG("[PlayerbotAI] _HandleCommandHelpHelper called with an empty sCommand. Ignoring call.");
12616  return "";
12617  }
12618 
12619  std::ostringstream oss;
12620  oss << "'|cffffffff";
12621  if (bCommandShort)
12622  oss << "(" << sCommand.at(0) << ")" << sCommand.substr(1);
12623  else
12624  oss << sCommand;
12625 
12626  if (reqLink != HL_NONE)
12627  {
12628  if (reqLink == HL_PROFESSION)
12629  {
12630  oss << " [PROFESSION]";
12631  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12632  oss << " [PROFESSION] ..";
12633  }
12634  else if (reqLink == HL_ITEM)
12635  {
12636  oss << " [ITEM]";
12637  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12638  oss << " [ITEM] ..";
12639  }
12640  else if (reqLink == HL_TALENT)
12641  {
12642  oss << " [TALENT]";
12643  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12644  oss << " [TALENT] ..";
12645  }
12646  else if (reqLink == HL_SKILL)
12647  {
12648  oss << " [SKILL]";
12649  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12650  oss << " [SKILL] ..";
12651  }
12652  else if (reqLink == HL_OPTION)
12653  {
12654  oss << " <OPTION>";
12655  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12656  oss << " <OPTION> ..";
12657  }
12658  else if (reqLink == HL_PETAGGRO)
12659  {
12660  oss << " <(a)ggressive | (d)efensive | (p)assive>";
12661  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12662  DEBUG_LOG("[PlayerbotAI] _HandleCommandHelpHelper: sCommand \"pet\" with bReqLinkMultiples \"true\". ... Why? Bug, surely.");
12663  }
12664  else if (reqLink == HL_QUEST)
12665  {
12666  oss << " [QUEST]";
12667  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12668  oss << " [QUEST] ..";
12669  }
12670  else if (reqLink == HL_GAMEOBJECT)
12671  {
12672  oss << " [GAMEOBJECT]";
12673  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12674  oss << " [GAMEOBJECT] ..";
12675  }
12676  else if (reqLink == HL_SPELL)
12677  {
12678  oss << " <Id# | (part of) name | [SPELL]>";
12679  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12680  oss << " <Id# | (part of) name | [SPELL]> ..";
12681  }
12682  else if (reqLink == HL_TARGET)
12683  {
12684  oss << " (TARGET)";
12685  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12686  oss << " (TARGET) ..";
12687  }
12688  else if (reqLink == HL_NAME)
12689  {
12690  oss << " <NAME>";
12691  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12692  oss << " <NAME> ..";
12693  }
12694  else if (reqLink == HL_AUCTION)
12695  {
12696  oss << " [AUCTION]";
12697  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12698  oss << " [AUCTION] ..";
12699  }
12700  else if (reqLink == HL_RECIPE)
12701  {
12702  oss << " [RECIPE]";
12703  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12704  oss << " [RECIPE] ..";
12705  }
12706  else if (reqLink == HL_MAIL)
12707  {
12708  oss << " [MAILID]";
12709  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12710  oss << " [MAILID] ..";
12711  }
12712  else
12713  {
12714  oss << " {unknown}";
12715  if (bReqLinkMultiples)
12716  oss << " {unknown} ..";
12717  DEBUG_LOG("[PlayerbotAI]: _HandleCommandHelpHelper - Uncaught case");
12718  }
12719  }
12720 
12721  oss << "|r': " << sExplain;
12722 
12723  return oss.str();
12724 }
